{"type":"text","timestamp":1781762495856,"sessionID":"ses_126af6eadffeKdnQM4mriL3y8K","part":{"id":"prt_ed9520604001MWw8SLwb40eV8Z","messageID":"msg_ed951f9a5001ysEsw3IOF6NfYQ","sessionID":"ses_126af6eadffeKdnQM4mriL3y8K","type":"text","text":"I’ll create the lineage packet from the workflow templates rather than running the artifact-root resolver, then run one focused review pass and synthesize the report from persisted state.","time":{"start":1781762491908,"end":1781762495849},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0769505bcbd63f22016a3389bbe1ac819195e9b40da4612b0d","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781762495914,"sessionID":"ses_126af6eadffeKdnQM4mriL3y8K","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_WI9YZe9nipux05eTaQQ58rnH","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","offset":634,"limit":1200},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n634:       step_emit_blocked_stop:\n635:         action: \"Persist blocked-stop evidence whenever the review legal-stop decision tree vetoes STOP\"\n636:         if_blocked:\n637:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergenceGate\":{\"pass\":{convergence_gate_pass},\"score\":{convergence_gate_score}},\"dimensionCoverageGate\":{\"pass\":{dimension_coverage_gate_pass},\"covered\":{dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json},\"missing\":{dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json}},\"p0ResolutionGate\":{\"pass\":{p0_resolution_gate_pass},\"activeP0\":{active_p0_count}},\"evidenceDensityGate\":{\"pass\":{evidence_density_gate_pass},\"avgEvidencePerFinding\":{avg_evidence_per_finding}},\"hotspotSaturationGate\":{\"pass\":{hotspot_saturation_gate_pass}},\"claimAdjudicationGate\":{\"pass\":{claim_adjudication_gate_pass},\"activeP0P1\":{claim_adjudication_active_count}},\"fixCompletenessReplayGate\":{\"pass\":{fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass},\"securitySensitive\":{security_sensitive_fix_scope},\"requiredRows\":{fix_completeness_replay_required_rows},\"passingRows\":{fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows}},\"candidateCoverageGate\":{\"pass\":{candidate_coverage_gate_pass},\"searchDebt\":{candidate_coverage_search_debt_json},\"missing\":{candidate_coverage_missing_json}},\"graphlessFallbackGate\":{\"pass\":{graphless_fallback_gate_pass},\"mode\":\"{graphless_fallback_mode}\",\"missing\":{graphless_fallback_missing_json},\"unavailabilityReason\":\"{graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason}\"}},\"graphBlockerDetail\":{graph_blockers_json},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n638:           log: \"Blocked STOP persisted for review loop. Failed gates: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n639:         if_not_blocked:\n640:           proceed: true\n641: \n642:       step_handle_convergence:\n643:         action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n644:         if_stop:\n645:           log: \"Loop stopping. Reason: {reason}\"\n646:           skip_to: phase_synthesis\n647:         if_blocked:\n648:           log: \"Legal-stop gates blocked STOP. Failed gates: {blocked_by_csv}. Continuing review.\"\n649:         if_stuck_recovery:\n650:           log: \"Stuck detected ({stuck_count} consecutive no-progress). Entering recovery.\"\n651:           recovery_strategies:\n652:             - \"Change granularity: file-level → function-level → line-level review\"\n653:             - \"Traceability protocol replay: re-run unresolved core or overlay checks\"\n654:             - \"Escalate severity review: re-examine P2 findings for potential P1 upgrades\"\n655:           pivot_target: \"Pivot to the least-covered dimension (the review dimension with the fewest iteration passes and lowest coverage ratio).\"\n656:           set:\n657:             next_dimension: \"RECOVERY: {recovery_strategy}. Least-covered dimension: {least_explored}\"\n658:             pending_stop_event: \"stuck_recovery\"\n659:             pending_stop_reason: \"stuckRecovery\"\n660:             pending_stop_detail: \"Recovery path activated after repeated no-progress iterations\"\n661:           reset: { stuck_count: 0 }\n662:         if_continue:\n663:           log: \"Iteration {current_iteration}: Continuing. Dimension: {next_dimension}\"\n664: \n665:       step_normalize_pause_events:\n666:         action: \"Rewrite raw pause and recovery events to the frozen STOP_REASONS enum at emission time: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused\"\n667:         if_pending_pause_event:\n668:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"reason\":\"{pending_stop_detail}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n669:           message: \"Review paused. Delete review/.deep-review-pause to resume.\"\n670:           reset:\n671:             pending_stop_event: null\n672:             pending_stop_reason: null\n673:             pending_stop_detail: null\n674:           halt: true\n675:         if_pending_stuck_recovery:\n676:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"strategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"targetDimension\":\"{least_explored}\",\"outcome\":\"pending\",\"reason\":\"{pending_stop_detail}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n677:           reset:\n678:             pending_stop_event: null\n679:             pending_stop_reason: null\n680:             pending_stop_detail: null\n681:         if_no_pending_event:\n682:           proceed: true\n683: \n684:       step_generate_state_summary:\n685:         action: \"Generate compact state summary for dispatch context (~200 tokens)\"\n686:         generate: |\n687:           STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n688:           Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n689:           Dimension: {next_dimension}\n690:           Prior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n691:           Dimension Coverage: {dimensions_covered_list} ({dimension_coverage})\n692:           Traceability: core={core_protocol_status} overlay={overlay_protocol_status}\n693:           {resource_map_prompt_line}\n694:           Coverage Age: {coverage_age}\n695:           Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest}\n696:           Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n697:           Provisional Verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n698: \n699:       step_marker_scan:\n700:         action: \"H-2 loop-prevention guard: scan previous iteration's rendered prompt for nested review marker\"\n701:         algorithm: |\n702:           if current_iteration > 1:\n703:             PREV_PROMPT_PATH = \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{previous_iteration}.md\"\n704:             if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n705:               PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n706:               if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n707:                 log \"ERROR: nested review-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n708:                 halt with exit code 2\n709:         note: |\n710:           False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n711:           three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n712:           True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n713:           starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested review-of-review dispatch.\n714: \n715:       step_dispatch_iteration:\n716:         action: \"Dispatch @deep-review agent for one review iteration\"\n717:         resolve_executor:\n718:           source: \"config.executor\"\n719:           loader: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n720:         pre_dispatch:\n721:           generate_summary: |\n722:             STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n723:             Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n724:             Dimension: {next_dimension}\n725:             Prior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n726:             Dimension Coverage: {dimensions_covered_list} ({dimension_coverage})\n727:             Traceability: core={core_protocol_status} overlay={overlay_protocol_status}\n728:             {resource_map_prompt_line}\n729:             Coverage Age: {coverage_age}\n730:             Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest}\n731:             Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n732:             Provisional Verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n733:           render_prompt_pack:\n734:             template_path: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl\"\n735:             renderer: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n736:             output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n737:             variables:\n738:               state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n739:               current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n740:               max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n741:               next_dimension: \"{next_dimension}\"\n742:               review_target: \"{review_target}\"\n743:               review_scope_files: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n744:               p0_count: \"{p0_count}\"\n745:               p1_count: \"{p1_count}\"\n746:               p2_count: \"{p2_count}\"\n747:               state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n748:               state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n749:               state_paths_findings_registry: \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n750:               state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n751:               state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n752:               state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n753:         pre_dispatch_audit:\n754:           skip_when: \"config.executor.kind == 'native'\"\n755:           call: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n756:           args:\n757:             stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n758:             executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n759:             iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n760:         branch_on: \"config.executor.kind\"\n761:         if_native:\n762:           dispatch:\n763:             agent: deep-review\n764:             model: opus\n765:             context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n766:           wait_for_completion: true\n767:         if_cli_codex:\n768:           command: |\n769:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n770:             import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n771: \n772:             import { runAuditedExecutorCommandAsync } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n773:             import { resolveCodexSandboxMode } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n774: \n775:             const executor = {\n776:               kind: 'cli-codex',\n777:               model: '{config.executor.model}',\n778:               configDir: '{config.executor.configDir}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.configDir}',\n779:               reasoningEffort: '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}',\n780:               serviceTier: '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}',\n781:               sandboxMode: '{config.executor.sandboxMode}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.sandboxMode}',\n782:               timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n783:             };\n784: \n785:             process.exit(await runAuditedExecutorCommandAsync({\n786:               command: 'codex',\n787:               args: [\n788:                 'exec',\n789:                 '--model',\n790:                 executor.model,\n791:                 '-c',\n792:                 `model_reasoning_effort=${executor.reasoningEffort}`,\n793:                 '-c',\n794:                 `service_tier=${executor.serviceTier}`,\n795:                 '-c',\n796:                 'approval_policy=never',\n797:                 '--sandbox',\n798:                 resolveCodexSandboxMode(executor.sandboxMode),\n799:                 '-',\n800:               ],\n801:               cwd: '{repo_root}',\n802:               timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n803:               stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n804:               executor,\n805:               iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n806:               input: readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n807:             }));\n808:             EOF\n809:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n810:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n811:           wait_for_completion: true\n812:         if_cli_copilot:\n813:           command: |\n814:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n815:             import { readFileSync, writeFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n816:             import { spawnSync } from 'node:child_process';\n817: \n818:             import { buildCopilotPromptArg } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n819: \n820:             const promptPath = '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md';\n821:             const prompt = readFileSync(promptPath, 'utf8');\n822: \n823:             // Workflow-resolved spec folder is the only legal write authority.\n824:             // The helper (`validateSpecFolder` inside `buildCopilotPromptArg`)\n825:             // is the single source of truth for rejecting empty / unresolved\n826:             // template / whitespace-only / string-coerced empty values. The\n827:             // YAML hands the raw `{spec_folder}` directly; on rejection the\n828:             // helper safe-fails to `type:\"missing\", writeIntent:true` (Gate-3\n829:             // enforcement, --allow-all-tools stripped).\n830:             const specFolderRaw = '{spec_folder}';\n831:             const targetAuthority = { type: 'approved', specFolder: specFolderRaw };\n832: \n833:             const baseArgs = [\n834:               '-p',\n835:               prompt,\n836:               '--model',\n837:               '{config.executor.model}',\n838:               '--allow-all-tools',\n839:               '--no-ask-user',\n840:             ];\n841: \n842:             const built = buildCopilotPromptArg({\n843:               promptPath,\n844:               prompt,\n845:               targetAuthority,\n846:               baseArgv: baseArgs,\n847:             });\n848: \n849:             // Large-prompt @PROMPT_PATH wrapper: helper emits a `promptFileBody`\n850:             // containing `<TARGET AUTHORITY preamble>\\n\\n---\\n\\n<original>`.\n851:             // Write it to disk so the file Copilot reads via @path opens with\n852:             // the authority block. Without this, recovered/bootstrap folder\n853:             // mentions inside the file could still anchor the model.\n854:             if (built.promptFileBody !== undefined) {\n855:               writeFileSync(promptPath, built.promptFileBody, 'utf8');\n856:             }\n857: \n858:             const result = spawnSync('copilot', built.argv, {\n859:               cwd: '{repo_root}',\n860:               stdio: 'inherit',\n861:               timeout: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}') * 1000,\n862:             });\n863:             process.exit(result.status ?? 1);\n864:             EOF\n865:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n866:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n867:           wait_for_completion: true\n868:           notes:\n869:             - \"copilot has no stdin support; prompt is positional\"\n870:             - \"Size check uses 16KB threshold; above that uses @PROMPT_PATH wrapper prompt\"\n871:             - \"Large-prompt path relies on copilot honoring @path references within its prompt string\"\n872:             - \"buildCopilotPromptArg attaches a TARGET AUTHORITY preamble bound to the workflow-approved spec folder; recovered context cannot override it (authority guard source: .opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_deep-review_auto.yaml)\"\n873:             - \"If spec_folder is missing/malformed/unresolved on a write-intent dispatch, the helper enforces plan-only by replacing the prompt with a Gate-3 question and stripping --allow-all-tools\"\n874:             - \"Large-prompt wrapper mode rewrites the prompt file at promptPath to include the TARGET AUTHORITY preamble (prefix + divider + original body); the argv becomes a bare @promptPath reference\"\n875:         if_cli_claude_code:\n876:           command: |\n877:             if [ -n \"{optional_claude_config_dir}\" ]; then export CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR=\"{optional_claude_config_dir}\"; fi\n878:             claude \\\n879:               -p \"$(cat '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md')\" \\\n880:               --model \"{config.executor.model}\" \\\n881:               --permission-mode acceptEdits \\\n882:               --output-format text \\\n883:               {optional_effort_flag}\n884:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n885:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n886:           wait_for_completion: true\n887:           render_hint:\n888:             optional_claude_config_dir: |\n889:               If config.executor.configDir is set and non-null, expand a leading ~ to HOME and bind that path.\n890:               Otherwise expand to empty string.\n891:             optional_effort_flag: |\n892:               If config.executor.reasoningEffort is set and non-null, expand to: --effort {config.executor.reasoningEffort}\n893:               Otherwise expand to empty string.\n894:           notes:\n895:             - \"claude-code default permission-mode is 'plan' (read-only); we override to 'acceptEdits' for iteration writes\"\n896:             - \"config.executor.configDir maps to CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR for account-specific Claude Code routing\"\n897:             - \"claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n898:             - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n899:         if_cli_opencode:\n900:           command: |\n901:             opencode run \\\n902:               --model \"{config.executor.model}\" \\\n903:               --format json \\\n904:               --dangerously-skip-permissions \\\n905:               --pure \\\n906:               --dir \"{repo_root}\" \\\n907:               {optional_variant_flag} \\\n908:               \"$(cat '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md')\" \\\n909:               </dev/null\n910:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n911:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n912:           wait_for_completion: true\n913:           render_hint:\n914:             optional_variant_flag: |\n915:               If config.executor.reasoningEffort is set and non-null, expand to: --variant {config.executor.reasoningEffort}\n916:               Otherwise expand to empty string.\n917:           notes:\n918:             - \"opencode run takes a positional message; prompt is fed via command substitution\"\n919:             - \"--variant maps reasoningEffort to opencode's provider-specific reasoning lever (e.g., high, medium, minimal)\"\n920:             - \"--dangerously-skip-permissions enables hands-off automation; sandboxMode='read-only' is not currently honored (no opencode equivalent)\"\n921:             - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude/Codex/raw shell). The cli-opencode skill SKILL.md §SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n922:             - \"</dev/null required: opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation. Without explicit closed stdin, automation that redirects stdout/stderr hangs at 0% CPU after `+60s snapshot prune cleanup`. See cli-opencode SKILL.md §4 ALWAYS rule + memory feedback_opencode_run_requires_dev_null_stdin.md.\"\n923:         post_dispatch_validate:\n924:           validator: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts#validateIterationOutputs\"\n925:           assert_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n926:           assert_appended: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n927:           assert_jsonl_fields: [type, iteration, mode, run, status, focus, dimensions, filesReviewed, findingsCount, findingsSummary, findingsNew, findingDetails, newFindingsRatio, sessionId, generation, lineageMode, timestamp, durationMs]\n928:           assert_canonical_type: \"iteration\"\n929:           assert_delta_file_exists: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n930:           assert_delta_file_has_iteration_record: true\n931:           failure_reasons:\n932:             - iteration_file_missing\n933:             - iteration_file_empty\n934:             - jsonl_not_appended\n935:             - jsonl_missing_fields\n936:             - jsonl_parse_error\n937:             - jsonl_wrong_type\n938:             - delta_file_missing\n939:             - delta_file_empty\n940:             - delta_file_missing_iteration_record\n941:             - executor_missing\n942:             - dispatch_failure_logged\n943:             - v2_missing_ledger\n944:             - v2_uncited_ledger_row\n945:             - v2_broken_linked_finding\n946:             - v2_shallow_finding_details\n947:             - delta_iteration_id_mismatch\n948:             - state_delta_iteration_mismatch\n949:           warning_surface:\n950:             source: \"result.warnings\"\n951:             action: \"emit schema_advisory canonical conflict event\"\n952:             severity: \"advisory\"\n953:             event_shape: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"schema_advisory\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"iteration\":{current_iteration},\"warnings\":{result.warnings},\"severity\":\"advisory\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n954:             note: \"Warnings do not fail dispatch. Hard failures still emit schema_mismatch through on_failure.\"\n955:           on_failure:\n956:             action: \"emit schema_mismatch canonical conflict event\"\n957:             escalation: \"After 3 consecutive failures, trigger stuck_recovery event with diagnostic context\"\n958:         record_executor_audit:\n959:           skip_when: \"config.executor.kind == 'native'\"\n960:           target: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n961:           field: \"executor\"\n962:           value:\n963:             kind: \"{config.executor.kind}\"\n964:             model: \"{config.executor.model}\"\n965:             reasoningEffort: \"{config.executor.reasoningEffort}\"\n966:             serviceTier: \"{config.executor.serviceTier}\"\n967: \n968:       step_evaluate_results:\n969:         action: \"Verify iteration outputs and extract metrics\"\n970:         verify:\n971:           - file_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n972:           - jsonl_appended: \"New iteration record in state.jsonl\"\n973:           - strategy_updated: \"Strategy.md has been modified\"\n974:         extract:\n975:           - newFindingsRatio: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n976:           - findings_count: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n977:           - severity_counts: \"From latest JSONL iteration record (P0, P1, P2)\"\n978:           - dimensions: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n979:           - files_reviewed: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n980:           - status: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n981:           - reviewed_artifacts: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n982:           - traceability_checks: \"From latest JSONL iteration record when present\"\n983:         on_missing_outputs:\n984:           action: \"Mark iteration as 'error', continue to next\"\n985:           # <!-- F-010-B5-03 -->\n986:           # Canonical iteration record: include sessionId, generation, durationMs so the reducer can persist\n987:           # the failure without dropping the iteration. Schema source: state_format.md §Iteration Records.\n988:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":{current_iteration},\"run\":{current_iteration},\"mode\":\"review\",\"status\":\"error\",\"focus\":\"{next_dimension}\",\"dimensions\":[\"{next_dimension}\"],\"filesReviewed\":[],\"findingsCount\":0,\"findingsSummary\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"findingsNew\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"findingDetails\":[],\"traceabilityChecks\":{\"summary\":{\"required\":0,\"executed\":0,\"pass\":0,\"partial\":0,\"fail\":0,\"blocked\":0,\"notApplicable\":0,\"gatingFailures\":0},\"results\":[]},\"newFindingsRatio\":0.0,\"durationMs\":0,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation},\"lineageMode\":\"{config.lineage.lineageMode}\"}'\n989: \n990:       step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication:\n991:         action: \"Validate typed claim-adjudication packets for any new P0/P1 findings and persist the result to state.jsonl so the next iteration's claimAdjudicationGate can read it\"\n992:         verify:\n993:           - typed_packets_present: \"Every new P0/P1 finding in review/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md contains a claim-adjudication JSON block\"\n994:           - packet_fields: \"Each packet includes claim, evidenceRefs, counterevidenceSought, alternativeExplanation, finalSeverity, confidence, downgradeTrigger\"\n995:           - missing_packet_ids: \"List of new P0/P1 finding IDs that are missing a typed packet or field; empty array when all packets validate\"\n996:         on_pass:\n997:           set:\n998:             claim_adjudication_passed: true\n999:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"passed\":true,\"activeP0P1\":{active_p0_p1_count},\"missingPackets\":[],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n1000:           log: \"Claim adjudication passed for iteration {current_iteration}. All new P0/P1 findings have typed packets.\"\n1001:         on_fail:\n1002:           action: \"Mark the iteration as invalid for convergence. The next iteration's claimAdjudicationGate (step_check_convergence step 0) reads the persisted `passed: false` event and vetoes STOP until a follow-up iteration rewrites the packets.\"\n1003:           set:\n1004:             claim_adjudication_passed: false\n1005:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"passed\":false,\"activeP0P1\":{active_p0_p1_count},\"missingPackets\":{missing_packet_ids},\"reason\":\"Missing typed packet fields for new P0/P1 findings\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n1006:           log: \"Claim adjudication incomplete for new P0/P1 findings. Event persisted. The next iteration's step_check_convergence claim-adjudication pre-check will veto STOP while `passed: false` remains the latest event and active P0/P1 > 0.\"\n1007: \n1008:       step_reduce_review_state:\n1009:         action: \"Run reducer to refresh the canonical findings registry before dashboard generation\"\n1010:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n1011:         read:\n1012:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1013:           - \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1014:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1015:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1016:         write:\n1017:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1018:           - \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n1019:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1020:         failure_modes:\n1021:           malformed_delta: \"skip + warn\"\n1022:           missing_iteration_file: \"no-op + error\"\n1023:           schema_mismatch: \"reject + conflict event\"\n1024:         guarantee: \"Idempotent for identical inputs\"\n1025:         note: \"Reducer outputs findingsRegistry, dashboardMetrics, and strategyUpdates. Re-running the same inputs must be idempotent.\"\n1026: \n1027:       step_graph_upsert:\n1028:         action: \"Transform the latest iteration graphEvents delta into review graph nodes and edges, then upsert it\"\n1029:         read:\n1030:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1031:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1032:         transform: |\n1033:           1. Read the latest iteration JSONL record after reducer completion.\n1034:           2. If graphEvents is absent or empty, set graph_nodes_json = [] and graph_edges_json = [] and skip the upsert.\n1035:           3. For each graph event without relation/source/target, normalize type = uppercase(event.type || event.nodeKind || event.type) and keep only DIMENSION, FILE, FINDING, EVIDENCE, REMEDIATION, BUG_CLASS, INVARIANT, PRODUCER, CONSUMER, TEST.\n1036:           4. Emit nodes as { id, type, name, iteration, metadata } using the event label (or id fallback) and review metadata for run/current focus.\n1037:           5. For each graph event with relation + source + target, normalize relation = uppercase(event.relation) and keep only COVERS, EVIDENCE_FOR, CONTRADICTS, RESOLVES, CONFIRMS, ESCALATES, IN_DIMENSION, IN_FILE.\n1038:           6. Emit edges as { id, relation, sourceId, targetId, metadata } and deduplicate the batch by id.\n1039:           7. Discard malformed or unknown graph events instead of failing the review iteration.\n1040:         bash: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"review\\\" --session-id \\\"{session_id}\\\" --nodes '{graph_nodes_json}' --edges '{graph_edges_json}'\"\n1041:         note: \"Invoke the runtime script directly. Upsert only the latest iteration graph delta.\"\n1042:         outputs:\n1043:           - graph_nodes_json: \"JSON array of normalized review graph nodes for the latest iteration\"\n1044:           - graph_edges_json: \"JSON array of normalized review graph edges for the latest iteration\"\n1045:         skip_conditions:\n1046:           - \"Latest iteration record has no graphEvents array\"\n1047: \n1048:       step_generate_dashboard:\n1049:         action: \"Generate or refresh the review dashboard\"\n1050:         read:\n1051:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1052:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1053:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1054:         content: |\n1055:           # Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n1056: \n1057:           Auto-generated from JSONL state log and strategy file. Regenerated after every iteration evaluation.\n1058: \n1059:           ## Status\n1060:           - Review Target: {review_target} ({review_target_type})\n1061:           - Status: [ITERATING | CONVERGING | STUCK_RECOVERY | COMPLETE]\n1062:           - Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n1063:           - Provisional Verdict: [PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL | PENDING]\n1064:           - hasAdvisories: {has_advisories}\n1065: \n1066:           ## Findings Summary\n1067:           | Severity | Count | Trend |\n1068:           |----------|------:|-------|\n1069:           | P0 (Blockers) | {p0_count} | {p0_trend} |\n1070:           | P1 (Required) | {p1_count} | {p1_trend} |\n1071:           | P2 (Suggestions) | {p2_count} | {p2_trend} |\n1072: \n1073:           ## Dimension Coverage\n1074:           | Dimension | Status | Iteration | Findings |\n1075:           |-----------|--------|-----------|----------|\n1076:           | [per dimension from strategy + JSONL] |\n1077: \n1078:           ## Traceability Coverage\n1079:           | Protocol | Level | Status | Findings |\n1080:           |----------|-------|--------|----------|\n1081:           | [per protocol from traceabilityChecks] |\n1082: \n1083:           ## Progress\n1084:           | # | Dimension | Ratio | P0/P1/P2 | Status |\n1085:           |---|-----------|-------|----------|--------|\n1086:           | [per iteration from JSONL] |\n1087: \n1088:           ## Trend\n1089:           - Last 3 ratios: [{ratios}] [{trend}]\n1090:           - Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n1091:           - Gate violations: {guard_violations}\n1092: \n1093:           ## Next Focus\n1094:           {next_dimension}\n1095:         output: \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n1096:         note: \"Auto-generated from JSONL + strategy. Never manually edited.\"\n1097: \n1098:       step_update_tracking:\n1099:         action: \"Update loop tracking variables\"\n1100:         set:\n1101:           current_iteration: \"{current_iteration + 1}\"\n1102:           p0_count: \"Accumulate from severity_counts\"\n1103:           p1_count: \"Accumulate from severity_counts\"\n1104:           p2_count: \"Accumulate from severity_counts\"\n1105:           stuck_count: |\n1106:             if status == 'thought': unchanged (skip)\n1107:             if status == 'insight': 0 (reset)\n1108:             if newFindingsRatio <= 0.05: stuck_count + 1\n1109:             else: 0\n1110:         log: \"Iteration {N} complete. Dimensions: {dimensions}. newFindingsRatio: {newFindingsRatio}. Findings: P0={severity_counts.P0} P1={severity_counts.P1} P2={severity_counts.P2}. Stuck count: {stuck_count}.\"\n1111: \n1112:       step_loop_decision:\n1113:         action: \"Return to step_read_state for next iteration\"\n1114:         goto: step_read_state\n1115: \n1116:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1117:   # PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n1118:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1119:   phase_synthesis:\n1120:     purpose: Compile all iteration findings into review/review-report.md\n1121:     steps:\n1122: \n1123:       step_fanout_merge:\n1124:         description: \"Merge N lineage registries with strongest-restriction; bind p0/p1/p2 counts for step_derive_verdict; skip when single-executor\"\n1125:         skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n1126:         command: |\n1127:           node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs \\\n1128:             --loop-type review \\\n1129:             --artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n1130:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1131:         wait_for_completion: true\n1132:         bind_from_output:\n1133:           p0_count: \"active_p0\"\n1134:           p1_count: \"active_p1\"\n1135:           p2_count: \"active_p2\"\n1136: \n1137:       step_hydrate_summary_metrics:\n1138:         action: \"Hydrate summary metrics before synthesis\"\n1139:         read:\n1140:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1141:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1142:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1143:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1144:         extract:\n1145:           - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n1146:           - p0_count: \"Total P0 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n1147:           - p1_count: \"Total P1 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n1148:           - p2_count: \"Total P2 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n1149:           - dimensions_covered: \"List of reviewed dimensions\"\n1150:           - dimension_coverage: \"covered / total\"\n1151:           - ac_coverage_signal: \"For spec-folder targets only: if level is 2+ and checklist.md exists and implementation-summary.md is in-progress or later, surface the AC_COVERAGE advisory status; otherwise mark exempt.\"\n1152:           - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records\"\n1153:           - reason: \"Use the latest stop reason if present, else the frozen default 'converged'. (Must be a member of the STOP_REASONS enum: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused.)\"\n1154: \n1155:       # H-1 verdict derivation: parse findings JSONL, map highest severity to verdict\n1156:       # - PASS: no P0 or P1 findings (P2-only or clean)\n1157:       # - CONDITIONAL: any P1 findings (no P0)\n1158:       # - FAIL: any P0 findings\n1159:       # Final line of iteration-NNN.md MUST be exactly: \"Review verdict: PASS\" / \"Review verdict: CONDITIONAL\" / \"Review verdict: FAIL\"\n1160:       step_derive_verdict:\n1161:         action: \"Derive review verdict from accumulated findings\"\n1162:         algorithm: |\n1163:           if p0_count > 0:\n1164:             verdict = \"FAIL\"\n1165:           elif p1_count > 0:\n1166:             verdict = \"CONDITIONAL\"\n1167:           else:\n1168:             verdict = \"PASS\"\n1169:           has_advisories = (verdict == \"PASS\" and p2_count > 0)\n1170:           ac_coverage_signal is advisory while the validation rule is INFO/default-off; include it in synthesis traceability, but do not change the exact verdict enum from this signal alone.\n1171:         outputs:\n1172:           - verdict: \"PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL\"\n1173:           - has_advisories: \"Boolean true when verdict is PASS and any active P2 findings exist\"\n1174:           - ac_coverage_signal: \"exempt | disabled | pass | advisory-shortfall\"\n1175:         contract: |\n1176:           Every iteration-NNN.md must end with exactly: \"Review verdict: PASS\" (or CONDITIONAL or FAIL).\n1177:           Downstream automation parses this final line via exact string match — do not vary the format.\n1178: \n1179:       step_read_all_iterations:\n1180:         action: \"Read all iteration files and strategy\"\n1181:         read_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n1182:         read_also: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1183: \n1184:       step_build_finding_registry:\n1185:         action: \"Build deduplicated finding registry from all iterations\"\n1186:         algorithm: |\n1187:           1. Extract all findings from iteration JSONL delta files\n1188:           2. Compute content_hash for each finding (emission requirement):\n1189:              content_hash = sha256(file_path + \"\\u001f\" + line_range + \"\\u001f\" + finding_type + \"\\u001f\" + normalized_description_80chars)\n1190:              Normalized description = whitespace-collapsed, lowercased, first 80 chars of the finding description.\n1191:           3. Two-tier dedup:\n1192:              PRIMARY: group by content_hash field\n1193:                - Same content_hash, multiple dimensions → single finding, merged `dimensions: [<all>]` array\n1194:                - Keep highest severity on duplicates\n1195:              FALLBACK (legacy records lacking content_hash): file:line + normalized_title\n1196:                - Same file:line, multiple dimensions → single finding, multiple dimension tags\n1197:                - Keep highest severity on duplicates\n1198:           4. Track finding lifecycle:\n1199:              - status: active | duplicate | upgraded | downgraded | contested | resolved_false_positive\n1200:              - Record first_seen, upgraded_in, previous_severity for severity changes\n1201:              - Record dimensions array reflecting all dimensions that emitted this finding\n1202:           5. Resolve contradictions:\n1203:              - Findings marked contested across iterations → referee pass\n1204:              - Determine final severity and status\n1205:           6. Count only 'active' findings for totals\n1206:         outputs:\n1207:           - finding_registry: \"Deduplicated list of all findings with metadata\"\n1208:           - active_p0: \"Count of active P0 findings\"\n1209:           - active_p1: \"Count of active P1 findings\"\n1210:           - active_p2: \"Count of active P2 findings\"\n1211: \n1212:       step_adversarial_selfcheck:\n1213:         action: \"Final adversarial self-check on all P0 and P1 findings\"\n1214:         algorithm: |\n1215:           For each active P0/P1 finding:\n1216:             1. Hunter: Re-verify finding against source code (re-read file:line)\n1217:             2. Skeptic: Challenge severity — is this really P0/P1? Could it be P2?\n1218:             3. Referee: Final call — confirm, downgrade, or mark false_positive\n1219:           Update finding_registry with adjudicated results.\n1220: \n1221:       step_emit_resource_map:\n1222:         action: \"Emit {state_paths.resource_map_output} from converged review deltas unless config.resource_map.emit is false\"\n1223:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} --emit-resource-map\"\n1224:         read:\n1225:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1226:           - \"{state_paths.delta_dir}/iter-*.jsonl\"\n1227:         write:\n1228:           - \"{state_paths.resource_map_output}\"\n1229:         guarantee: \"Reducer skips cleanly when config.resource_map.emit == false and writes a deterministic resource-map when enabled.\"\n1230: \n1231:       step_resource_map_coverage_gate:\n1232:         action: \"If resource_map_present, compute the Resource Map Coverage Gate synthesis inputs; otherwise preserve the skip note\"\n1233:         note: \"Cross-check target_files from {spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md against {spec_folder}/resource-map.md. Report touched entries, untouched entries split into expected-by-scope vs gap, and implementation paths absent from the map. Findings raised here use category resource-map-coverage with severity calibrated to the gate outcome.\"\n1234: \n1235:       step_compile_review_report:\n1236:         action: \"Compile review/review-report.md with 9 core sections, a conditional Resource Map Coverage Gate section, and an embedded Planning Packet\"\n1237:         instructions: |\n1238:           Create review/review-report.md with the following sections:\n1239: \n1240:           1. **Executive Summary**\n1241:              - Overall verdict: PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL\n1242:              - hasAdvisories: true when PASS carries active P2 items\n1243:              - P0/P1/P2 counts (active only)\n1244:              - Review scope summary\n1245: \n1246:           2. **Planning Trigger**\n1247:              - State whether `/speckit:plan` is required\n1248:              - Include a fenced `json` block labeled `Planning Packet`\n1249:              - The packet MUST include: `triggered`, `verdict`, `hasAdvisories`, `activeFindings`, `remediationWorkstreams`, `specSeed`, `planSeed`, `findingClasses`, `affectedSurfacesSeed`, `fixCompletenessRequired`\n1250:              - Build `activeFindings`, `findingClasses`, and `affectedSurfacesSeed` from reducer-owned state plus iteration JSONL `findingDetails`; if a field is missing, mark it `UNKNOWN` instead of inferring it from prose\n1251: \n1252:           3. **Active Finding Registry**\n1253:              - Unified registry for active P0/P1/P2 findings\n1254:              - For each: ID, severity, title, dimension, file:line, evidence, impact, fix recommendation, disposition, findingClass, scopeProof, affectedSurfaceHints\n1255: \n1256:           4. **Remediation Workstreams**\n1257:              - Ordered action groups: P0 first, then P1, with P2 advisories separated\n1258: \n1259:           5. **Spec Seed**\n1260:              - Concrete seed bullets for follow-on spec updates\n1261: \n1262:           6. **Plan Seed**\n1263:              - Concrete starter tasks for `/speckit:plan`\n1264: \n1265:            7. **Traceability Status**\n1266:               - Summarize required core protocols first, then applicable overlay protocols\n1267:               - Include status, evidence, and any unresolved drift per protocol\n1268:               - Include `AC_COVERAGE` status for lifecycle-active spec-folder targets: exempt, disabled, pass, or advisory-shortfall, with covered/total and floor when available\n1269: \n1270:           If `resource_map_present` is true, insert **## Resource Map Coverage Gate** after `Traceability Status` with exactly three bullets:\n1271:              - `Entries touched`: count of resource-map paths that appear in applied reports\n1272:              - `Entries not touched`: paths in resource-map not in implementation, labeled `expected-by-scope` or `gap`\n1273:              - `Implementation paths absent from resource-map`: `target_files` in applied reports not on the map\n1274: \n1275:           8. **Deferred Items**\n1276:              - Advisory-only or backlog-worthy follow-ups that do not block the current verdict\n1277: \n1278:           9. **Search Ledger**\n1279:              - Always include this section before the appendix.\n1280:              - Render reducer-owned `searchCoverage`, `candidateCoverage`, `searchDebt`, `ruledOutCandidates`, and `cleanSearchProof`.\n1281:              - If all arrays are empty or absent, include: `*No search-depth state captured (legacy v1 record)*`.\n1282:              - When `searchDebt` is non-empty, state `hasSearchDebt: true` and carry the dashboard verdict as CONDITIONAL unless active P0 findings make it FAIL.\n1283: \n1284:           10. **Audit Appendix**\n1285:              - Convergence summary, coverage summary, ruled-out claims, sources reviewed\n1286:              - Cross-reference appendix MUST be split into `Core Protocols` and `Overlay Protocols`\n1287: \n1288:           Preserve machine-owned markers so the reducer-owned registry, dashboard, and strategy anchors can be refreshed on re-run without mutating prior synthesis. (Note: `completed-continue` lineage branch is deferred — see `deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches`.)\n1289:         output: \"{state_paths.review_output}\"\n1290: \n1291:       step_convergence_report:\n1292:         action: \"Append convergence report to JSONL\"\n1293:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"totalIterations\":{iteration_count},\"activeP0\":{active_p0},\"activeP1\":{active_p1},\"activeP2\":{active_p2},\"dimensionCoverage\":{dimension_coverage},\"verdict\":\"{verdict}\",\"releaseReadinessState\":\"{release_readiness_state}\",\"stopReason\":\"{reason}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n1294:         note: \"Emit as numeric ratio (e.g., 0.75), not quoted string. Compute: dimensions_covered / total_dimensions.\"\n1295: \n1296:       step_update_config_status:\n1297:         action: \"Mark config as complete\"\n1298:         edit: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1299:         set_field: { status: \"complete\" }\n1300: \n1301:       step_stage_artifact_dir:\n1302:         action: \"Stage all skill-owned artifacts under artifact_dir for the operator's next git commit\"\n1303:         command: \"git add {state_paths.packet_dir}\"\n1304:         note: \"Skill-owned contract fix (028): without this stage step, operators who do `git add review-report.md` lose the iteration trail (iterations/, deltas/, state.jsonl, strategy, findings-registry, etc.). Staging the whole artifact_dir keeps the audit trail intact. Operators retain commit authority and can `git restore --staged {path}` to unstage anything before commit. Failure is non-fatal — log warning and continue.\"\n1305:         on_fail: \"Log warning. Do not block synthesis. The artifact_dir may be outside a git repo (e.g., temp test fixture) which is a valid case.\"\n1306: \n1307:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1308:   # PHASE 4: SAVE\n1309:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1310:   phase_save:\n1311:     purpose: Preserve review context to memory system\n1312:     steps:\n1313: \n1314:       step_compose_save_payload:\n1315:         action: \"Compose the structured JSON payload consumed by generate-context.js\"\n1316:         output: \"/tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json\"\n1317:         requirements:\n1318:           - \"Write this file before invoking generate-context.js; the loader fails closed if the explicit JSON file is absent.\"\n1319:           - \"Include `specFolder`, a concise `sessionSummary`, curated `observations`, `recent_context`, `toolCalls`, and `exchanges` from the completed review loop.\"\n1320:           - \"Use a session-scoped temp filename; do not use the retired shared `/tmp/save-context-data.json` path.\"\n1321:         example_payload: |\n1322:           {\n1323:             \"specFolder\": \"{spec_folder}\",\n1324:             \"sessionSummary\": \"Deep review completed; see review/review-report.md for verdict, findings, and workstreams.\",\n1325:             \"observations\": [\"Summarize the active findings, verdict, and remediation guidance.\"],\n1326:             \"recent_context\": [\"Point to the generated review artifacts and next action.\"],\n1327:             \"exchanges\": [],\n1328:             \"toolCalls\": []\n1329:           }\n1330: \n1331:       step_generate_context:\n1332:         action: \"Route continuity content into the correct canonical spec document via generate-context.js\"\n1333:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json {spec_folder}\"\n1334:         critical_rule: \"NEVER manually author files under retired memory/ paths (the runtime rejects them); use generate-context.js so the save routes into decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md\"\n1335: \n1336:       step_index_memory:\n1337:         action: \"Index the routed canonical spec document with memory_save when immediate MCP visibility is required\"\n1338:         mcp_tool: memory_save\n1339:         invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"[routed-canonical-spec-doc-path]\" })'\n1340:         note: \"Use the actual canonical spec-doc path returned by generate-context.js (decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md); memory_index_scan remains the bulk fallback\"\n1341: \n1342:       step_verify_save:\n1343:         action: \"Verify canonical save routed content into the correct spec document\"\n1344:         check: \"Does {spec_folder}/implementation-summary.md, {spec_folder}/decision-record.md, or {spec_folder}/handover.md carry the new continuity update?\"\n1345:         on_fail: \"Log warning but do not block completion\"\n1346: \n1347:       step_release_lock:\n1348:         action: \"Release the single-writer lock after save, skip-save, or cancellation cleanup has resolved\"\n1349:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}\"\n1350:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"lock_released\",\"path\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"releasePhase\":\"save\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n1351: \n1352:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1353:   # COMPLETION\n1354:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1355:   completion:\n1356:     message: |\n1357:       Deep review complete.\n1358:       Iterations: {iteration_count} | Stop reason: {reason}\n1359:       Findings: P0={active_p0} P1={active_p1} P2={active_p2}\n1360:       Verdict: {verdict} | hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n1361: \n1362:       Artifacts:\n1363:         - review/review-report.md (compiled from {iteration_count} iterations)\n1364:         - {iteration_count} iteration files in review/iterations/\n1365:         - State files in review/: deep-review-config.json, deep-review-state.jsonl, deep-review-findings-registry.json, deep-review-strategy.md, deep-review-dashboard.md\n1366:         - Memory context saved\n1367: \n1368:       STATUS=OK PATH={spec_folder}\n1369:     next_steps:\n1370:       - \"/speckit:plan [remediation] (if FAIL or CONDITIONAL verdict)\"\n1371:       - \"/create:changelog (if PASS, including PASS with hasAdvisories=true)\"\n1372:       - \"/deep:review [target] (for another review)\"\n1373:       - \"/memory:save {spec_folder} (refresh canonical continuity before the next session)\"\n1374: \n1375: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1376: # ERROR RECOVERY\n1377: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1378: error_recovery:\n1379:   agent_dispatch_timeout: \"Retry once with reduced scope (fewer files per iteration). If second timeout, mark as 'timeout' and continue.\"\n1380:   state_file_missing: \"If JSONL missing during loop, reconstruct from iteration files. If strategy missing, create minimal version.\"\n1381:   consecutive_failures: \"After 3 consecutive errors, halt loop and enter synthesis with partial findings.\"\n1382:   memory_save_failure: \"Preserve the review packet in review/ as backup. Log warning.\"\n1383: \n1384: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1385: # RULES\n1386: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1387: rules:\n1388:   ALWAYS:\n1389:     - follow_workflow_phases_in_order\n1390:     - dispatch_deep_review_agent_per_iteration\n1391:     - check_convergence_before_each_iteration\n1392:     - write_all_state_to_files\n1393:     - save_memory_context_after_synthesis\n1394:     - respect_max_iterations_cap\n1395:     - treat_review_target_as_read_only\n1396:     - deduplicate_findings_before_synthesis\n1397:     - run_adversarial_selfcheck_on_p0_p1\n1398:   NEVER:\n1399:     - skip_convergence_check\n1400:     - dispatch_non_leaf_agents\n1401:     - hold_iteration_findings_in_memory_only\n1402:     - modify_config_after_initialization\n1403:     - overwrite_jsonl_state_log\n1404:     - proceed_without_state_file_verification\n1405:     - modify_files_under_review\n1406:     - report_p0_without_file_line_evidence\n1407: \n1408: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1409: # REFERENCE-ONLY APPENDIX\n1410: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1411: reference_only_appendix:\n1412:   checkpoint_commit:\n1413:     note: \"Checkpoint commits are intentionally excluded from workflow.steps.\"\n1414:     commands:\n1415:       - \"git add {state_paths.iteration_pattern} {state_paths.state_log} {state_paths.findings_registry} {state_paths.strategy} {state_paths.review_output}\"\n1416:       - 'git commit -m \"chore(deep-review): iteration {NNN} complete\"'\n1417:   severity_weights:\n1418:     note: \"Severity weights for newFindingsRatio calculation\"\n1419:     weights:\n1420:       P0: 10.0\n1421:       P1: 5.0\n1422:       P2: 1.0\n1423:     p0_override: \"If ANY new P0 discovered → newFindingsRatio = max(calculated, 0.50). A single new P0 blocks convergence.\"\n1424:     clean_pass: \"If total_findings == 0 (clean pass) → newFindingsRatio = 0.0\"\n1425:   review_dimensions:\n1426:     note: \"All 4 default review dimensions with priority ordering\"\n1427:     dimensions:\n1428:       - { priority: 1, name: \"correctness\", checks: \"Logic, state flow, edge cases, error handling\" }\n1429:       - { priority: 2, name: \"security\", checks: \"Auth, input/output safety, data exposure, permissions\" }\n1430:       - { priority: 3, name: \"traceability\", checks: \"Spec/checklist alignment, cross-reference integrity, evidence coverage\" }\n1431:       - { priority: 4, name: \"maintainability\", checks: \"Patterns, documentation quality, safe follow-on change clarity\" }\n1432:   cross_reference_protocols:\n1433:     note: \"Cross-reference verification protocols split into core and overlay classes\"\n1434:     core_protocols:\n1435:       - { check: \"Spec vs Code\", source: \"spec.md claims\", target: \"implementation\" }\n1436:       - { check: \"Checklist vs Evidence\", source: \"[x] items\", target: \"cited evidence\" }\n1437:     overlay_protocols:\n1438:       - { check: \"SKILL.md vs Agent\", source: \"Skill contracts\", target: \"agent files\" }\n1439:       - { check: \"Agent Cross-Runtime\", source: \".claude\", target: \".codex/.opencode/.agents\" }\n1440:       - { check: \"Feature Catalog vs Code\", source: \"Catalog claims\", target: \"implementation\" }\n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 634-1440. Use offset=1441 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"      step_emit_blocked_stop:\n        action: \"Persist blocked-stop evidence whenever the review legal-stop decision tree vetoes STOP\"\n        if_blocked:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergenceGate\":{\"pass\":{convergence_gate_pass},\"score\":{convergence_gate_score}},\"dimensionCoverageGate\":{\"pass\":{dimension_coverage_gate_pass},\"covered\":{dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json},\"missing\":{dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json}},\"p0ResolutionGate\":{\"pass\":{p0_resolution_gate_pass},\"activeP0\":{active_p0_count}},\"evidenceDensityGate\":{\"pass\":{evidence_density_gate_pass},\"avgEvidencePerFinding\":{avg_evidence_per_finding}},\"hotspotSaturationGate\":{\"pass\":{hotspot_saturation_gate_pass}},\"claimAdjudicationGate\":{\"pass\":{claim_adjudication_gate_pass},\"activeP0P1\":{claim_adjudication_active_count}},\"fixCompletenessReplayGate\":{\"pass\":{fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass},\"securitySensitive\":{security_sensitive_fix_scope},\"requiredRows\":{fix_completeness_replay_required_rows},\"passingRows\":{fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows}},\"candidateCoverageGate\":{\"pass\":{candidate_coverage_gate_pass},\"searchDebt\":{candidate_coverage_search_debt_json},\"missing\":{candidate_coverage_missing_json}},\"graphlessFallbackGate\":{\"pass\":{graphless_fallback_gate_pass},\"mode\":\"{graphless_fallback_mode}\",\"missing\":{graphless_fallback_missing_json},\"unavailabilityReason\":\"{graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason}\"}},\"graphBlockerDetail\":{graph_blockers_json},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          log: \"Blocked STOP persisted for review loop. Failed gates: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n        if_not_blocked:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_handle_convergence:\n        action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n        if_stop:\n          log: \"Loop stopping. Reason: {reason}\"\n          skip_to: phase_synthesis\n        if_blocked:\n          log: \"Legal-stop gates blocked STOP. Failed gates: {blocked_by_csv}. Continuing review.\"\n        if_stuck_recovery:\n          log: \"Stuck detected ({stuck_count} consecutive no-progress). Entering recovery.\"\n          recovery_strategies:\n            - \"Change granularity: file-level → function-level → line-level review\"\n            - \"Traceability protocol replay: re-run unresolved core or overlay checks\"","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","text":"      step_emit_blocked_stop:\n        action: \"Persist blocked-stop evidence whenever the review legal-stop decision tree vetoes STOP\"\n        if_blocked:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergenceGate\":{\"pass\":{convergence_gate_pass},\"score\":{convergence_gate_score}},\"dimensionCoverageGate\":{\"pass\":{dimension_coverage_gate_pass},\"covered\":{dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json},\"missing\":{dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json}},\"p0ResolutionGate\":{\"pass\":{p0_resolution_gate_pass},\"activeP0\":{active_p0_count}},\"evidenceDensityGate\":{\"pass\":{evidence_density_gate_pass},\"avgEvidencePerFinding\":{avg_evidence_per_finding}},\"hotspotSaturationGate\":{\"pass\":{hotspot_saturation_gate_pass}},\"claimAdjudicationGate\":{\"pass\":{claim_adjudication_gate_pass},\"activeP0P1\":{claim_adjudication_active_count}},\"fixCompletenessReplayGate\":{\"pass\":{fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass},\"securitySensitive\":{security_sensitive_fix_scope},\"requiredRows\":{fix_completeness_replay_required_rows},\"passingRows\":{fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows}},\"candidateCoverageGate\":{\"pass\":{candidate_coverage_gate_pass},\"searchDebt\":{candidate_coverage_search_debt_json},\"missing\":{candidate_coverage_missing_json}},\"graphlessFallbackGate\":{\"pass\":{graphless_fallback_gate_pass},\"mode\":\"{graphless_fallback_mode}\",\"missing\":{graphless_fallback_missing_json},\"unavailabilityReason\":\"{graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason}\"}},\"graphBlockerDetail\":{graph_blockers_json},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          log: \"Blocked STOP persisted for review loop. Failed gates: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n        if_not_blocked:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_handle_convergence:\n        action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n        if_stop:\n          log: \"Loop stopping. Reason: {reason}\"\n          skip_to: phase_synthesis\n        if_blocked:\n          log: \"Legal-stop gates blocked STOP. Failed gates: {blocked_by_csv}. Continuing review.\"\n        if_stuck_recovery:\n          log: \"Stuck detected ({stuck_count} consecutive no-progress). Entering recovery.\"\n          recovery_strategies:\n            - \"Change granularity: file-level → function-level → line-level review\"\n            - \"Traceability protocol replay: re-run unresolved core or overlay checks\"\n            - \"Escalate severity review: re-examine P2 findings for potential P1 upgrades\"\n          pivot_target: \"Pivot to the least-covered dimension (the review dimension with the fewest iteration passes and lowest coverage ratio).\"\n          set:\n            next_dimension: \"RECOVERY: {recovery_strategy}. Least-covered dimension: {least_explored}\"\n            pending_stop_event: \"stuck_recovery\"\n            pending_stop_reason: \"stuckRecovery\"\n            pending_stop_detail: \"Recovery path activated after repeated no-progress iterations\"\n          reset: { stuck_count: 0 }\n        if_continue:\n          log: \"Iteration {current_iteration}: Continuing. Dimension: {next_dimension}\"\n\n      step_normalize_pause_events:\n        action: \"Rewrite raw pause and recovery events to the frozen STOP_REASONS enum at emission time: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused\"\n        if_pending_pause_event:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"reason\":\"{pending_stop_detail}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          message: \"Review paused. Delete review/.deep-review-pause to resume.\"\n          reset:\n            pending_stop_event: null\n            pending_stop_reason: null\n            pending_stop_detail: null\n          halt: true\n        if_pending_stuck_recovery:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"strategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"targetDimension\":\"{least_explored}\",\"outcome\":\"pending\",\"reason\":\"{pending_stop_detail}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          reset:\n            pending_stop_event: null\n            pending_stop_reason: null\n            pending_stop_detail: null\n        if_no_pending_event:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_generate_state_summary:\n        action: \"Generate compact state summary for dispatch context (~200 tokens)\"\n        generate: |\n          STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n          Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n          Dimension: {next_dimension}\n          Prior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n          Dimension Coverage: {dimensions_covered_list} ({dimension_coverage})\n          Traceability: core={core_protocol_status} overlay={overlay_protocol_status}\n          {resource_map_prompt_line}\n          Coverage Age: {coverage_age}\n          Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest}\n          Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n          Provisional Verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n\n      step_marker_scan:\n        action: \"H-2 loop-prevention guard: scan previous iteration's rendered prompt for nested review marker\"\n        algorithm: |\n          if current_iteration > 1:\n            PREV_PROMPT_PATH = \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{previous_iteration}.md\"\n            if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n              PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n              if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n                log \"ERROR: nested review-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n                halt with exit code 2\n        note: |\n          False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n          three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n          True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n          starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested review-of-review dispatch.\n\n      step_dispatch_iteration:\n        action: \"Dispatch @deep-review agent for one review iteration\"\n        resolve_executor:\n          source: \"config.executor\"\n          loader: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n        pre_dispatch:\n          generate_summary: |\n            STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n            Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n            Dimension: {next_dimension}\n            Prior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n            Dimension Coverage: {dimensions_covered_list} ({dimension_coverage})\n            Traceability: core={core_protocol_status} overlay={overlay_protocol_status}\n            {resource_map_prompt_line}\n            Coverage Age: {coverage_age}\n            Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest}\n            Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n            Provisional Verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n          render_prompt_pack:\n            template_path: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl\"\n            renderer: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n            output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n            variables:\n              state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n              current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n              max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n              next_dimension: \"{next_dimension}\"\n              review_target: \"{review_target}\"\n              review_scope_files: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n              p0_count: \"{p0_count}\"\n              p1_count: \"{p1_count}\"\n              p2_count: \"{p2_count}\"\n              state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n              state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n              state_paths_findings_registry: \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n              state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n              state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n              state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n        pre_dispatch_audit:\n          skip_when: \"config.executor.kind == 'native'\"\n          call: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n          args:\n            stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n            executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n            iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n        branch_on: \"config.executor.kind\"\n        if_native:\n          dispatch:\n            agent: deep-review\n            model: opus\n            context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n        if_cli_codex:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n\n            import { runAuditedExecutorCommandAsync } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n            import { resolveCodexSandboxMode } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n\n            const executor = {\n              kind: 'cli-codex',\n              model: '{config.executor.model}',\n              configDir: '{config.executor.configDir}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.configDir}',\n              reasoningEffort: '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}',\n              serviceTier: '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}',\n              sandboxMode: '{config.executor.sandboxMode}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.sandboxMode}',\n              timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n            };\n\n            process.exit(await runAuditedExecutorCommandAsync({\n              command: 'codex',\n              args: [\n                'exec',\n                '--model',\n                executor.model,\n                '-c',\n                `model_reasoning_effort=${executor.reasoningEffort}`,\n                '-c',\n                `service_tier=${executor.serviceTier}`,\n                '-c',\n                'approval_policy=never',\n                '--sandbox',\n                resolveCodexSandboxMode(executor.sandboxMode),\n                '-',\n              ],\n              cwd: '{repo_root}',\n              timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n              stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n              executor,\n              iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n              input: readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n            }));\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n        if_cli_copilot:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync, writeFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n            import { spawnSync } from 'node:child_process';\n\n            import { buildCopilotPromptArg } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n\n            const promptPath = '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md';\n            const prompt = readFileSync(promptPath, 'utf8');\n\n            // Workflow-resolved spec folder is the only legal write authority.\n            // The helper (`validateSpecFolder` inside `buildCopilotPromptArg`)\n            // is the single source of truth for rejecting empty / unresolved\n            // template / whitespace-only / string-coerced empty values. The\n            // YAML hands the raw `{spec_folder}` directly; on rejection the\n            // helper safe-fails to `type:\"missing\", writeIntent:true` (Gate-3\n            // enforcement, --allow-all-tools stripped).\n            const specFolderRaw = '{spec_folder}';\n            const targetAuthority = { type: 'approved', specFolder: specFolderRaw };\n\n            const baseArgs = [\n              '-p',\n              prompt,\n              '--model',\n              '{config.executor.model}',\n              '--allow-all-tools',\n              '--no-ask-user',\n            ];\n\n            const built = buildCopilotPromptArg({\n              promptPath,\n              prompt,\n              targetAuthority,\n              baseArgv: baseArgs,\n            });\n\n            // Large-prompt @PROMPT_PATH wrapper: helper emits a `promptFileBody`\n            // containing `<TARGET AUTHORITY preamble>\\n\\n---\\n\\n<original>`.\n            // Write it to disk so the file Copilot reads via @path opens with\n            // the authority block. Without this, recovered/bootstrap folder\n            // mentions inside the file could still anchor the model.\n            if (built.promptFileBody !== undefined) {\n              writeFileSync(promptPath, built.promptFileBody, 'utf8');\n            }\n\n            const result = spawnSync('copilot', built.argv, {\n              cwd: '{repo_root}',\n              stdio: 'inherit',\n              timeout: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}') * 1000,\n            });\n            process.exit(result.status ?? 1);\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          notes:\n            - \"copilot has no stdin support; prompt is positional\"\n            - \"Size check uses 16KB threshold; above that uses @PROMPT_PATH wrapper prompt\"\n            - \"Large-prompt path relies on copilot honoring @path references within its prompt string\"\n            - \"buildCopilotPromptArg attaches a TARGET AUTHORITY preamble bound to the workflow-approved spec folder; recovered context cannot override it (authority guard source: .opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_deep-review_auto.yaml)\"\n            - \"If spec_folder is missing/malformed/unresolved on a write-intent dispatch, the helper enforces plan-only by replacing the prompt with a Gate-3 question and stripping --allow-all-tools\"\n            - \"Large-prompt wrapper mode rewrites the prompt file at promptPath to include the TARGET AUTHORITY preamble (prefix + divider + original body); the argv becomes a bare @promptPath reference\"\n        if_cli_claude_code:\n          command: |\n            if [ -n \"{optional_claude_config_dir}\" ]; then export CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR=\"{optional_claude_config_dir}\"; fi\n            claude \\\n              -p \"$(cat '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md')\" \\\n              --model \"{config.executor.model}\" \\\n              --permission-mode acceptEdits \\\n              --output-format text \\\n              {optional_effort_flag}\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          render_hint:\n            optional_claude_config_dir: |\n              If config.executor.configDir is set and non-null, expand a leading ~ to HOME and bind that path.\n              Otherwise expand to empty string.\n            optional_effort_flag: |\n              If config.executor.reasoningEffort is set and non-null, expand to: --effort {config.executor.reasoningEffort}\n              Otherwise expand to empty string.\n          notes:\n            - \"claude-code default permission-mode is 'plan' (read-only); we override to 'acceptEdits' for iteration writes\"\n            - \"config.executor.configDir maps to CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR for account-specific Claude Code routing\"\n            - \"claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n            - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n        if_cli_opencode:\n          command: |\n            opencode run \\\n              --model \"{config.executor.model}\" \\\n              --format json \\\n              --dangerously-skip-permissions \\\n              --pure \\\n              --dir \"{repo_root}\" \\\n              {optional_variant_flag} \\\n              \"$(cat '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md')\" \\\n              </dev/null\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          render_hint:\n            optional_variant_flag: |\n              If config.executor.reasoningEffort is set and non-null, expand to: --variant {config.executor.reasoningEffort}\n              Otherwise expand to empty string.\n          notes:\n            - \"opencode run takes a positional message; prompt is fed via command substitution\"\n            - \"--variant maps reasoningEffort to opencode's provider-specific reasoning lever (e.g., high, medium, minimal)\"\n            - \"--dangerously-skip-permissions enables hands-off automation; sandboxMode='read-only' is not currently honored (no opencode equivalent)\"\n            - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude/Codex/raw shell). The cli-opencode skill SKILL.md §SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n            - \"</dev/null required: opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation. Without explicit closed stdin, automation that redirects stdout/stderr hangs at 0% CPU after `+60s snapshot prune cleanup`. See cli-opencode SKILL.md §4 ALWAYS rule + memory feedback_opencode_run_requires_dev_null_stdin.md.\"\n        post_dispatch_validate:\n          validator: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts#validateIterationOutputs\"\n          assert_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          assert_appended: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          assert_jsonl_fields: [type, iteration, mode, run, status, focus, dimensions, filesReviewed, findingsCount, findingsSummary, findingsNew, findingDetails, newFindingsRatio, sessionId, generation, lineageMode, timestamp, durationMs]\n          assert_canonical_type: \"iteration\"\n          assert_delta_file_exists: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n          assert_delta_file_has_iteration_record: true\n          failure_reasons:\n            - iteration_file_missing\n            - iteration_file_empty\n            - jsonl_not_appended\n            - jsonl_missing_fields\n            - jsonl_parse_error\n            - jsonl_wrong_type\n            - delta_file_missing\n            - delta_file_empty\n            - delta_file_missing_iteration_record\n            - executor_missing\n            - dispatch_failure_logged\n            - v2_missing_ledger\n            - v2_uncited_ledger_row\n            - v2_broken_linked_finding\n            - v2_shallow_finding_details\n            - delta_iteration_id_mismatch\n            - state_delta_iteration_mismatch\n          warning_surface:\n            source: \"result.warnings\"\n            action: \"emit schema_advisory canonical conflict event\"\n            severity: \"advisory\"\n            event_shape: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"schema_advisory\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"iteration\":{current_iteration},\"warnings\":{result.warnings},\"severity\":\"advisory\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n            note: \"Warnings do not fail dispatch. Hard failures still emit schema_mismatch through on_failure.\"\n          on_failure:\n            action: \"emit schema_mismatch canonical conflict event\"\n            escalation: \"After 3 consecutive failures, trigger stuck_recovery event with diagnostic context\"\n        record_executor_audit:\n          skip_when: \"config.executor.kind == 'native'\"\n          target: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          field: \"executor\"\n          value:\n            kind: \"{config.executor.kind}\"\n            model: \"{config.executor.model}\"\n            reasoningEffort: \"{config.executor.reasoningEffort}\"\n            serviceTier: \"{config.executor.serviceTier}\"\n\n      step_evaluate_results:\n        action: \"Verify iteration outputs and extract metrics\"\n        verify:\n          - file_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          - jsonl_appended: \"New iteration record in state.jsonl\"\n          - strategy_updated: \"Strategy.md has been modified\"\n        extract:\n          - newFindingsRatio: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - findings_count: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - severity_counts: \"From latest JSONL iteration record (P0, P1, P2)\"\n          - dimensions: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - files_reviewed: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - status: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - reviewed_artifacts: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - traceability_checks: \"From latest JSONL iteration record when present\"\n        on_missing_outputs:\n          action: \"Mark iteration as 'error', continue to next\"\n          # <!-- F-010-B5-03 -->\n          # Canonical iteration record: include sessionId, generation, durationMs so the reducer can persist\n          # the failure without dropping the iteration. Schema source: state_format.md §Iteration Records.\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":{current_iteration},\"run\":{current_iteration},\"mode\":\"review\",\"status\":\"error\",\"focus\":\"{next_dimension}\",\"dimensions\":[\"{next_dimension}\"],\"filesReviewed\":[],\"findingsCount\":0,\"findingsSummary\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"findingsNew\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"findingDetails\":[],\"traceabilityChecks\":{\"summary\":{\"required\":0,\"executed\":0,\"pass\":0,\"partial\":0,\"fail\":0,\"blocked\":0,\"notApplicable\":0,\"gatingFailures\":0},\"results\":[]},\"newFindingsRatio\":0.0,\"durationMs\":0,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation},\"lineageMode\":\"{config.lineage.lineageMode}\"}'\n\n      step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication:\n        action: \"Validate typed claim-adjudication packets for any new P0/P1 findings and persist the result to state.jsonl so the next iteration's claimAdjudicationGate can read it\"\n        verify:\n          - typed_packets_present: \"Every new P0/P1 finding in review/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md contains a claim-adjudication JSON block\"\n          - packet_fields: \"Each packet includes claim, evidenceRefs, counterevidenceSought, alternativeExplanation, finalSeverity, confidence, downgradeTrigger\"\n          - missing_packet_ids: \"List of new P0/P1 finding IDs that are missing a typed packet or field; empty array when all packets validate\"\n        on_pass:\n          set:\n            claim_adjudication_passed: true\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"passed\":true,\"activeP0P1\":{active_p0_p1_count},\"missingPackets\":[],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          log: \"Claim adjudication passed for iteration {current_iteration}. All new P0/P1 findings have typed packets.\"\n        on_fail:\n          action: \"Mark the iteration as invalid for convergence. The next iteration's claimAdjudicationGate (step_check_convergence step 0) reads the persisted `passed: false` event and vetoes STOP until a follow-up iteration rewrites the packets.\"\n          set:\n            claim_adjudication_passed: false\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"passed\":false,\"activeP0P1\":{active_p0_p1_count},\"missingPackets\":{missing_packet_ids},\"reason\":\"Missing typed packet fields for new P0/P1 findings\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          log: \"Claim adjudication incomplete for new P0/P1 findings. Event persisted. The next iteration's step_check_convergence claim-adjudication pre-check will veto STOP while `passed: false` remains the latest event and active P0/P1 > 0.\"\n\n      step_reduce_review_state:\n        action: \"Run reducer to refresh the canonical findings registry before dashboard generation\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        write:\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        failure_modes:\n          malformed_delta: \"skip + warn\"\n          missing_iteration_file: \"no-op + error\"\n          schema_mismatch: \"reject + conflict event\"\n        guarantee: \"Idempotent for identical inputs\"\n        note: \"Reducer outputs findingsRegistry, dashboardMetrics, and strategyUpdates. Re-running the same inputs must be idempotent.\"\n\n      step_graph_upsert:\n        action: \"Transform the latest iteration graphEvents delta into review graph nodes and edges, then upsert it\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n        transform: |\n          1. Read the latest iteration JSONL record after reducer completion.\n          2. If graphEvents is absent or empty, set graph_nodes_json = [] and graph_edges_json = [] and skip the upsert.\n          3. For each graph event without relation/source/target, normalize type = uppercase(event.type || event.nodeKind || event.type) and keep only DIMENSION, FILE, FINDING, EVIDENCE, REMEDIATION, BUG_CLASS, INVARIANT, PRODUCER, CONSUMER, TEST.\n          4. Emit nodes as { id, type, name, iteration, metadata } using the event label (or id fallback) and review metadata for run/current focus.\n          5. For each graph event with relation + source + target, normalize relation = uppercase(event.relation) and keep only COVERS, EVIDENCE_FOR, CONTRADICTS, RESOLVES, CONFIRMS, ESCALATES, IN_DIMENSION, IN_FILE.\n          6. Emit edges as { id, relation, sourceId, targetId, metadata } and deduplicate the batch by id.\n          7. Discard malformed or unknown graph events instead of failing the review iteration.\n        bash: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"review\\\" --session-id \\\"{session_id}\\\" --nodes '{graph_nodes_json}' --edges '{graph_edges_json}'\"\n        note: \"Invoke the runtime script directly. Upsert only the latest iteration graph delta.\"\n        outputs:\n          - graph_nodes_json: \"JSON array of normalized review graph nodes for the latest iteration\"\n          - graph_edges_json: \"JSON array of normalized review graph edges for the latest iteration\"\n        skip_conditions:\n          - \"Latest iteration record has no graphEvents array\"\n\n      step_generate_dashboard:\n        action: \"Generate or refresh the review dashboard\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        content: |\n          # Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n\n          Auto-generated from JSONL state log and strategy file. Regenerated after every iteration evaluation.\n\n          ## Status\n          - Review Target: {review_target} ({review_target_type})\n          - Status: [ITERATING | CONVERGING | STUCK_RECOVERY | COMPLETE]\n          - Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n          - Provisional Verdict: [PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL | PENDING]\n          - hasAdvisories: {has_advisories}\n\n          ## Findings Summary\n          | Severity | Count | Trend |\n          |----------|------:|-------|\n          | P0 (Blockers) | {p0_count} | {p0_trend} |\n          | P1 (Required) | {p1_count} | {p1_trend} |\n          | P2 (Suggestions) | {p2_count} | {p2_trend} |\n\n          ## Dimension Coverage\n          | Dimension | Status | Iteration | Findings |\n          |-----------|--------|-----------|----------|\n          | [per dimension from strategy + JSONL] |\n\n          ## Traceability Coverage\n          | Protocol | Level | Status | Findings |\n          |----------|-------|--------|----------|\n          | [per protocol from traceabilityChecks] |\n\n          ## Progress\n          | # | Dimension | Ratio | P0/P1/P2 | Status |\n          |---|-----------|-------|----------|--------|\n          | [per iteration from JSONL] |\n\n          ## Trend\n          - Last 3 ratios: [{ratios}] [{trend}]\n          - Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n          - Gate violations: {guard_violations}\n\n          ## Next Focus\n          {next_dimension}\n        output: \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n        note: \"Auto-generated from JSONL + strategy. Never manually edited.\"\n\n      step_update_tracking:\n        action: \"Update loop tracking variables\"\n        set:\n          current_iteration: \"{current_iteration + 1}\"\n          p0_count: \"Accumulate from severity_counts\"\n          p1_count: \"Accumulate from severity_counts\"\n          p2_count: \"Accumulate from severity_counts\"\n          stuck_count: |\n            if status == 'thought': unchanged (skip)\n            if status == 'insight': 0 (reset)\n            if newFindingsRatio <= 0.05: stuck_count + 1\n            else: 0\n        log: \"Iteration {N} complete. Dimensions: {dimensions}. newFindingsRatio: {newFindingsRatio}. Findings: P0={severity_counts.P0} P1={severity_counts.P1} P2={severity_counts.P2}. Stuck count: {stuck_count}.\"\n\n      step_loop_decision:\n        action: \"Return to step_read_state for next iteration\"\n        goto: step_read_state\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_synthesis:\n    purpose: Compile all iteration findings into review/review-report.md\n    steps:\n\n      step_fanout_merge:\n        description: \"Merge N lineage registries with strongest-restriction; bind p0/p1/p2 counts for step_derive_verdict; skip when single-executor\"\n        skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs \\\n            --loop-type review \\\n            --artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n        bind_from_output:\n          p0_count: \"active_p0\"\n          p1_count: \"active_p1\"\n          p2_count: \"active_p2\"\n\n      step_hydrate_summary_metrics:\n        action: \"Hydrate summary metrics before synthesis\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        extract:\n          - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n          - p0_count: \"Total P0 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n          - p1_count: \"Total P1 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n          - p2_count: \"Total P2 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n          - dimensions_covered: \"List of reviewed dimensions\"\n          - dimension_coverage: \"covered / total\"\n          - ac_coverage_signal: \"For spec-folder targets only: if level is 2+ and checklist.md exists and implementation-summary.md is in-progress or later, surface the AC_COVERAGE advisory status; otherwise mark exempt.\"\n          - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records\"\n          - reason: \"Use the latest stop reason if present, else the frozen default 'converged'. (Must be a member of the STOP_REASONS enum: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused.)\"\n\n      # H-1 verdict derivation: parse findings JSONL, map highest severity to verdict\n      # - PASS: no P0 or P1 findings (P2-only or clean)\n      # - CONDITIONAL: any P1 findings (no P0)\n      # - FAIL: any P0 findings\n      # Final line of iteration-NNN.md MUST be exactly: \"Review verdict: PASS\" / \"Review verdict: CONDITIONAL\" / \"Review verdict: FAIL\"\n      step_derive_verdict:\n        action: \"Derive review verdict from accumulated findings\"\n        algorithm: |\n          if p0_count > 0:\n            verdict = \"FAIL\"\n          elif p1_count > 0:\n            verdict = \"CONDITIONAL\"\n          else:\n            verdict = \"PASS\"\n          has_advisories = (verdict == \"PASS\" and p2_count > 0)\n          ac_coverage_signal is advisory while the validation rule is INFO/default-off; include it in synthesis traceability, but do not change the exact verdict enum from this signal alone.\n        outputs:\n          - verdict: \"PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL\"\n          - has_advisories: \"Boolean true when verdict is PASS and any active P2 findings exist\"\n          - ac_coverage_signal: \"exempt | disabled | pass | advisory-shortfall\"\n        contract: |\n          Every iteration-NNN.md must end with exactly: \"Review verdict: PASS\" (or CONDITIONAL or FAIL).\n          Downstream automation parses this final line via exact string match — do not vary the format.\n\n      step_read_all_iterations:\n        action: \"Read all iteration files and strategy\"\n        read_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n        read_also: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_build_finding_registry:\n        action: \"Build deduplicated finding registry from all iterations\"\n        algorithm: |\n          1. Extract all findings from iteration JSONL delta files\n          2. Compute content_hash for each finding (emission requirement):\n             content_hash = sha256(file_path + \"\\u001f\" + line_range + \"\\u001f\" + finding_type + \"\\u001f\" + normalized_description_80chars)\n             Normalized description = whitespace-collapsed, lowercased, first 80 chars of the finding description.\n          3. Two-tier dedup:\n             PRIMARY: group by content_hash field\n               - Same content_hash, multiple dimensions → single finding, merged `dimensions: [<all>]` array\n               - Keep highest severity on duplicates\n             FALLBACK (legacy records lacking content_hash): file:line + normalized_title\n               - Same file:line, multiple dimensions → single finding, multiple dimension tags\n               - Keep highest severity on duplicates\n          4. Track finding lifecycle:\n             - status: active | duplicate | upgraded | downgraded | contested | resolved_false_positive\n             - Record first_seen, upgraded_in, previous_severity for severity changes\n             - Record dimensions array reflecting all dimensions that emitted this finding\n          5. Resolve contradictions:\n             - Findings marked contested across iterations → referee pass\n             - Determine final severity and status\n          6. Count only 'active' findings for totals\n        outputs:\n          - finding_registry: \"Deduplicated list of all findings with metadata\"\n          - active_p0: \"Count of active P0 findings\"\n          - active_p1: \"Count of active P1 findings\"\n          - active_p2: \"Count of active P2 findings\"\n\n      step_adversarial_selfcheck:\n        action: \"Final adversarial self-check on all P0 and P1 findings\"\n        algorithm: |\n          For each active P0/P1 finding:\n            1. Hunter: Re-verify finding against source code (re-read file:line)\n            2. Skeptic: Challenge severity — is this really P0/P1? Could it be P2?\n            3. Referee: Final call — confirm, downgrade, or mark false_positive\n          Update finding_registry with adjudicated results.\n\n      step_emit_resource_map:\n        action: \"Emit {state_paths.resource_map_output} from converged review deltas unless config.resource_map.emit is false\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} --emit-resource-map\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.delta_dir}/iter-*.jsonl\"\n        write:\n          - \"{state_paths.resource_map_output}\"\n        guarantee: \"Reducer skips cleanly when config.resource_map.emit == false and writes a deterministic resource-map when enabled.\"\n\n      step_resource_map_coverage_gate:\n        action: \"If resource_map_present, compute the Resource Map Coverage Gate synthesis inputs; otherwise preserve the skip note\"\n        note: \"Cross-check target_files from {spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md against {spec_folder}/resource-map.md. Report touched entries, untouched entries split into expected-by-scope vs gap, and implementation paths absent from the map. Findings raised here use category resource-map-coverage with severity calibrated to the gate outcome.\"\n\n      step_compile_review_report:\n        action: \"Compile review/review-report.md with 9 core sections, a conditional Resource Map Coverage Gate section, and an embedded Planning Packet\"\n        instructions: |\n          Create review/review-report.md with the following sections:\n\n          1. **Executive Summary**\n             - Overall verdict: PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL\n             - hasAdvisories: true when PASS carries active P2 items\n             - P0/P1/P2 counts (active only)\n             - Review scope summary\n\n          2. **Planning Trigger**\n             - State whether `/speckit:plan` is required\n             - Include a fenced `json` block labeled `Planning Packet`\n             - The packet MUST include: `triggered`, `verdict`, `hasAdvisories`, `activeFindings`, `remediationWorkstreams`, `specSeed`, `planSeed`, `findingClasses`, `affectedSurfacesSeed`, `fixCompletenessRequired`\n             - Build `activeFindings`, `findingClasses`, and `affectedSurfacesSeed` from reducer-owned state plus iteration JSONL `findingDetails`; if a field is missing, mark it `UNKNOWN` instead of inferring it from prose\n\n          3. **Active Finding Registry**\n             - Unified registry for active P0/P1/P2 findings\n             - For each: ID, severity, title, dimension, file:line, evidence, impact, fix recommendation, disposition, findingClass, scopeProof, affectedSurfaceHints\n\n          4. **Remediation Workstreams**\n             - Ordered action groups: P0 first, then P1, with P2 advisories separated\n\n          5. **Spec Seed**\n             - Concrete seed bullets for follow-on spec updates\n\n          6. **Plan Seed**\n             - Concrete starter tasks for `/speckit:plan`\n\n           7. **Traceability Status**\n              - Summarize required core protocols first, then applicable overlay protocols\n              - Include status, evidence, and any unresolved drift per protocol\n              - Include `AC_COVERAGE` status for lifecycle-active spec-folder targets: exempt, disabled, pass, or advisory-shortfall, with covered/total and floor when available\n\n          If `resource_map_present` is true, insert **## Resource Map Coverage Gate** after `Traceability Status` with exactly three bullets:\n             - `Entries touched`: count of resource-map paths that appear in applied reports\n             - `Entries not touched`: paths in resource-map not in implementation, labeled `expected-by-scope` or `gap`\n             - `Implementation paths absent from resource-map`: `target_files` in applied reports not on the map\n\n          8. **Deferred Items**\n             - Advisory-only or backlog-worthy follow-ups that do not block the current verdict\n\n          9. **Search Ledger**\n             - Always include this section before the appendix.\n             - Render reducer-owned `searchCoverage`, `candidateCoverage`, `searchDebt`, `ruledOutCandidates`, and `cleanSearchProof`.\n             - If all arrays are empty or absent, include: `*No search-depth state captured (legacy v1 record)*`.\n             - When `searchDebt` is non-empty, state `hasSearchDebt: true` and carry the dashboard verdict as CONDITIONAL unless active P0 findings make it FAIL.\n\n          10. **Audit Appendix**\n             - Convergence summary, coverage summary, ruled-out claims, sources reviewed\n             - Cross-reference appendix MUST be split into `Core Protocols` and `Overlay Protocols`\n\n          Preserve machine-owned markers so the reducer-owned registry, dashboard, and strategy anchors can be refreshed on re-run without mutating prior synthesis. (Note: `completed-continue` lineage branch is deferred — see `deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches`.)\n        output: \"{state_paths.review_output}\"\n\n      step_convergence_report:\n        action: \"Append convergence report to JSONL\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"totalIterations\":{iteration_count},\"activeP0\":{active_p0},\"activeP1\":{active_p1},\"activeP2\":{active_p2},\"dimensionCoverage\":{dimension_coverage},\"verdict\":\"{verdict}\",\"releaseReadinessState\":\"{release_readiness_state}\",\"stopReason\":\"{reason}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n        note: \"Emit as numeric ratio (e.g., 0.75), not quoted string. Compute: dimensions_covered / total_dimensions.\"\n\n      step_update_config_status:\n        action: \"Mark config as complete\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n        set_field: { status: \"complete\" }\n\n      step_stage_artifact_dir:\n        action: \"Stage all skill-owned artifacts under artifact_dir for the operator's next git commit\"\n        command: \"git add {state_paths.packet_dir}\"\n        note: \"Skill-owned contract fix (028): without this stage step, operators who do `git add review-report.md` lose the iteration trail (iterations/, deltas/, state.jsonl, strategy, findings-registry, etc.). Staging the whole artifact_dir keeps the audit trail intact. Operators retain commit authority and can `git restore --staged {path}` to unstage anything before commit. Failure is non-fatal — log warning and continue.\"\n        on_fail: \"Log warning. Do not block synthesis. The artifact_dir may be outside a git repo (e.g., temp test fixture) which is a valid case.\"\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 4: SAVE\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_save:\n    purpose: Preserve review context to memory system\n    steps:\n\n      step_compose_save_payload:\n        action: \"Compose the structured JSON payload consumed by generate-context.js\"\n        output: \"/tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json\"\n        requirements:\n          - \"Write this file before invoking generate-context.js; the loader fails closed if the explicit JSON file is absent.\"\n          - \"Include `specFolder`, a concise `sessionSummary`, curated `observations`, `recent_context`, `toolCalls`, and `exchanges` from the completed review loop.\"\n          - \"Use a session-scoped temp filename; do not use the retired shared `/tmp/save-context-data.json` path.\"\n        example_payload: |\n          {\n            \"specFolder\": \"{spec_folder}\",\n            \"sessionSummary\": \"Deep review completed; see review/review-report.md for verdict, findings, and workstreams.\",\n            \"observations\": [\"Summarize the active findings, verdict, and remediation guidance.\"],\n            \"recent_context\": [\"Point to the generated review artifacts and next action.\"],\n            \"exchanges\": [],\n            \"toolCalls\": []\n          }\n\n      step_generate_context:\n        action: \"Route continuity content into the correct canonical spec document via generate-context.js\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json {spec_folder}\"\n        critical_rule: \"NEVER manually author files under retired memory/ paths (the runtime rejects them); use generate-context.js so the save routes into decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md\"\n\n      step_index_memory:\n        action: \"Index the routed canonical spec document with memory_save when immediate MCP visibility is required\"\n        mcp_tool: memory_save\n        invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"[routed-canonical-spec-doc-path]\" })'\n        note: \"Use the actual canonical spec-doc path returned by generate-context.js (decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md); memory_index_scan remains the bulk fallback\"\n\n      step_verify_save:\n        action: \"Verify canonical save routed content into the correct spec document\"\n        check: \"Does {spec_folder}/implementation-summary.md, {spec_folder}/decision-record.md, or {spec_folder}/handover.md carry the new continuity update?\"\n        on_fail: \"Log warning but do not block completion\"\n\n      step_release_lock:\n        action: \"Release the single-writer lock after save, skip-save, or cancellation cleanup has resolved\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"lock_released\",\"path\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"releasePhase\":\"save\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # COMPLETION\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  completion:\n    message: |\n      Deep review complete.\n      Iterations: {iteration_count} | Stop reason: {reason}\n      Findings: P0={active_p0} P1={active_p1} P2={active_p2}\n      Verdict: {verdict} | hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n\n      Artifacts:\n        - review/review-report.md (compiled from {iteration_count} iterations)\n        - {iteration_count} iteration files in review/iterations/\n        - State files in review/: deep-review-config.json, deep-review-state.jsonl, deep-review-findings-registry.json, deep-review-strategy.md, deep-review-dashboard.md\n        - Memory context saved\n\n      STATUS=OK PATH={spec_folder}\n    next_steps:\n      - \"/speckit:plan [remediation] (if FAIL or CONDITIONAL verdict)\"\n      - \"/create:changelog (if PASS, including PASS with hasAdvisories=true)\"\n      - \"/deep:review [target] (for another review)\"\n      - \"/memory:save {spec_folder} (refresh canonical continuity before the next session)\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# ERROR RECOVERY\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nerror_recovery:\n  agent_dispatch_timeout: \"Retry once with reduced scope (fewer files per iteration). If second timeout, mark as 'timeout' and continue.\"\n  state_file_missing: \"If JSONL missing during loop, reconstruct from iteration files. If strategy missing, create minimal version.\"\n  consecutive_failures: \"After 3 consecutive errors, halt loop and enter synthesis with partial findings.\"\n  memory_save_failure: \"Preserve the review packet in review/ as backup. Log warning.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# RULES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrules:\n  ALWAYS:\n    - follow_workflow_phases_in_order\n    - dispatch_deep_review_agent_per_iteration\n    - check_convergence_before_each_iteration\n    - write_all_state_to_files\n    - save_memory_context_after_synthesis\n    - respect_max_iterations_cap\n    - treat_review_target_as_read_only\n    - deduplicate_findings_before_synthesis\n    - run_adversarial_selfcheck_on_p0_p1\n  NEVER:\n    - skip_convergence_check\n    - dispatch_non_leaf_agents\n    - hold_iteration_findings_in_memory_only\n    - modify_config_after_initialization\n    - overwrite_jsonl_state_log\n    - proceed_without_state_file_verification\n    - modify_files_under_review\n    - report_p0_without_file_line_evidence\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# REFERENCE-ONLY APPENDIX\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nreference_only_appendix:\n  checkpoint_commit:\n    note: \"Checkpoint commits are intentionally excluded from workflow.steps.\"\n    commands:\n      - \"git add {state_paths.iteration_pattern} {state_paths.state_log} {state_paths.findings_registry} {state_paths.strategy} {state_paths.review_output}\"\n      - 'git commit -m \"chore(deep-review): iteration {NNN} complete\"'\n  severity_weights:\n    note: \"Severity weights for newFindingsRatio calculation\"\n    weights:\n      P0: 10.0\n      P1: 5.0\n      P2: 1.0\n    p0_override: \"If ANY new P0 discovered → newFindingsRatio = max(calculated, 0.50). A single new P0 blocks convergence.\"\n    clean_pass: \"If total_findings == 0 (clean pass) → newFindingsRatio = 0.0\"\n  review_dimensions:\n    note: \"All 4 default review dimensions with priority ordering\"\n    dimensions:\n      - { priority: 1, name: \"correctness\", checks: \"Logic, state flow, edge cases, error handling\" }\n      - { priority: 2, name: \"security\", checks: \"Auth, input/output safety, data exposure, permissions\" }\n      - { priority: 3, name: \"traceability\", checks: \"Spec/checklist alignment, cross-reference integrity, evidence coverage\" }\n      - { priority: 4, name: \"maintainability\", checks: \"Patterns, documentation quality, safe follow-on change clarity\" }\n  cross_reference_protocols:\n    note: \"Cross-reference verification protocols split into core and overlay classes\"\n    core_protocols:\n      - { check: \"Spec vs Code\", source: \"spec.md claims\", target: \"implementation\" }\n      - { check: \"Checklist vs Evidence\", source: \"[x] items\", target: \"cited evidence\" }\n    overlay_protocols:\n      - { check: \"SKILL.md vs Agent\", source: \"Skill contracts\", target: \"agent files\" }\n      - { check: \"Agent Cross-Runtime\", source: \".claude\", target: \".codex/.opencode/.agents\" }\n      - { check: \"Feature Catalog vs Code\", source: \"Catalog claims\", target: \"implementation\" }","lineStart":634,"lineEnd":1440,"totalLines":1441,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1781762495903,"end":1781762495910}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0769505bcbd63f22016a3389bfcbf88191948532f2f81acbe1"}},"id":"prt_ed952156d001k1qHfZ49UM6zVB","sessionID":"ses_126af6eadffeKdnQM4mriL3y8K","messageID":"msg_ed951f9a5001ysEsw3IOF6NfYQ"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781762495935,"sessionID":"ses_126af6eadffeKdnQM4mriL3y8K","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_yvBmPEVMzajbOrXumpXFFE81","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs","offset":1357,"limit":2200},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1357:       const suffix = content.endsWith('\\n') ? '' : '\\n';\n1358:       return `${content}${suffix}\\n${replacement}\\n`;\n1359:     }\n1360:     throw new Error(\n1361:       `Missing machine-owned anchor \"${anchorId}\" in deep-review strategy file. `\n1362:       + 'Pass createMissing:true (or the reducer CLI flag --create-missing-anchors) to bootstrap.',\n1363:     );\n1364:   }\n1365:   return content.replace(pattern, replacement);\n1366: }\n1367: \n1368: function updateStrategyContent(strategyContent, registry, iterationFiles, options = {}, iterationRecords = []) {\n1369:   // Early return when there is no strategy file to update. Empty content\n1370:   // cannot contain the machine-owned anchors and replaceAnchorSection would\n1371:   // correctly fail-close — but for that specific case we intentionally skip\n1372:   // rather than throw so bootstrap flows (no strategy yet) still work.\n1373:   if (!strategyContent) {\n1374:     return strategyContent;\n1375:   }\n1376: \n1377:   const anchorOptions = { createMissing: Boolean(options.createMissingAnchors) };\n1378:   const severity = registry.findingsBySeverity;\n1379:   const runningFindings = [\n1380:     `- P0 (Blockers): ${severity.P0}`,\n1381:     `- P1 (Required): ${severity.P1}`,\n1382:     `- P2 (Suggestions): ${severity.P2}`,\n1383:     `- Resolved: ${registry.resolvedFindingsCount}`,\n1384:   ].join('\\n');\n1385: \n1386:   const completedDimensions = REQUIRED_DIMENSIONS\n1387:     .filter((dimension) => registry.dimensionCoverage[dimension])\n1388:     .map((dimension) => `- [x] ${dimension}`)\n1389:     .join('\\n') || '[None yet]';\n1390: \n1391:   const remainingDimensions = REQUIRED_DIMENSIONS\n1392:     .filter((dimension) => !registry.dimensionCoverage[dimension])\n1393:     .map((dimension) => `- [ ] ${dimension}`)\n1394:     .join('\\n') || '[All dimensions complete]';\n1395: \n1396:   // Default next-focus comes from latest iteration → first uncovered dimension → fallback.\n1397:   let nextFocus = iterationFiles.map((iteration) => iteration.nextFocus).filter(Boolean).at(-1)\n1398:     || REQUIRED_DIMENSIONS.find((dimension) => !registry.dimensionCoverage[dimension])\n1399:     || '[All dimensions covered]';\n1400: \n1401:   // Prefer the latest blocked-stop\n1402:   // recovery only when blocked-stop is genuinely the most recent loop event.\n1403:   // The earlier implementation read timestamps from the markdown iteration\n1404:   // files, but parseIterationFile() never captures timestamps, so\n1405:   // latestIterationTimestamp was always undefined and any historical\n1406:   // blocked-stop permanently pinned next-focus. Fix: source recency from the\n1407:   // JSONL iteration records (which do carry timestamps) instead.\n1408:   const latestBlockedStop = registry.blockedStopHistory?.at(-1);\n1409:   if (latestBlockedStop && latestBlockedStop.timestamp) {\n1410:     const latestIterationTimestamp = iterationRecords\n1411:       .filter((record) => record?.type === 'iteration' && typeof record.timestamp === 'string')\n1412:       .map((record) => record.timestamp)\n1413:       .at(-1);\n1414:     const blockedIsMostRecent = !latestIterationTimestamp\n1415:       || latestBlockedStop.timestamp >= latestIterationTimestamp;\n1416:     if (blockedIsMostRecent) {\n1417:       const blockers = formatBlockedByList(latestBlockedStop.blockedBy);\n1418:       const recovery = latestBlockedStop.recoveryStrategy || '[no recovery strategy provided]';\n1419:       nextFocus = [\n1420:         `BLOCKED on: ${blockers}`,\n1421:         `Recovery: ${recovery}`,\n1422:         'Address the blocking gates before the next iteration.',\n1423:       ].join('\\n');\n1424:     }\n1425:   }\n1426: \n1427:   let updated = strategyContent;\n1428:   updated = replaceAnchorSection(updated, 'review-dimensions', '3. REVIEW DIMENSIONS (remaining)', remainingDimensions, anchorOptions);\n1429:   updated = replaceAnchorSection(updated, 'completed-dimensions', '4. COMPLETED DIMENSIONS', completedDimensions, anchorOptions);\n1430:   updated = replaceAnchorSection(updated, 'running-findings', '5. RUNNING FINDINGS', runningFindings, anchorOptions);\n1431:   updated = replaceAnchorSection(\n1432:     updated,\n1433:     'exhausted-approaches',\n1434:     '9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)',\n1435:     buildExhaustedApproaches(iterationFiles),\n1436:     anchorOptions,\n1437:   );\n1438:   updated = replaceAnchorSection(updated, 'next-focus', '11. NEXT FOCUS', nextFocus, anchorOptions);\n1439:   return updated;\n1440: }\n1441: \n1442: function renderDashboard(config, registry, iterationRecords, iterationFiles) {\n1443:   const latestIteration = iterationRecords.filter((record) => record.type === 'iteration').at(-1);\n1444:   const ratios = iterationRecords\n1445:     .filter((record) => record.type === 'iteration')\n1446:     .map((record) => (typeof record.newFindingsRatio === 'number' ? record.newFindingsRatio : null))\n1447:     .filter((value) => value !== null);\n1448:   const lastThreeRatios = ratios.slice(-3).map((value) => value.toFixed(2)).join(' -> ') || 'N/A';\n1449:   const nextFocus = iterationFiles.map((iteration) => iteration.nextFocus).filter(Boolean).at(-1)\n1450:     || REQUIRED_DIMENSIONS.find((dimension) => !registry.dimensionCoverage[dimension])\n1451:     || '[All dimensions covered]';\n1452: \n1453:   const severity = registry.findingsBySeverity;\n1454:   const hasSearchDebt = Array.isArray(registry.searchDebt) && registry.searchDebt.length > 0;\n1455:   const verdict = severity.P0 > 0\n1456:     ? 'FAIL'\n1457:     : severity.P1 > 0 || hasSearchDebt\n1458:       ? 'CONDITIONAL'\n1459:       : 'PASS';\n1460:   const hasAdvisories = verdict === 'PASS' && severity.P2 > 0;\n1461: \n1462:   const progressRows = iterationRecords\n1463:     .filter((record) => record.type === 'iteration')\n1464:     .map((record) => {\n1465:       const dimensions = Array.isArray(record.dimensions) ? record.dimensions.join('/') : '-';\n1466:       const ratio = typeof record.newFindingsRatio === 'number' ? record.newFindingsRatio.toFixed(2) : '0.00';\n1467:       const summary = record.findingsSummary || {};\n1468:       const findings = `${summary.P0 ?? 0}/${summary.P1 ?? 0}/${summary.P2 ?? 0}`;\n1469:       return `| ${record.run} | ${record.focus || 'unknown'} | ${dimensions} | ${ratio} | ${findings} | ${record.status || 'complete'} |`;\n1470:     })\n1471:     .join('\\n') || '| 0 | none yet | - | 0.00 | 0/0/0 | initialized |';\n1472: \n1473:   const dimensionRows = REQUIRED_DIMENSIONS\n1474:     .map((dimension) => {\n1475:       const covered = registry.dimensionCoverage[dimension];\n1476:       const status = covered ? 'covered' : 'pending';\n1477:       const openInDimension = registry.openFindings.filter((finding) => finding.dimension === dimension).length;\n1478:       return `| ${dimension} | ${status} | ${openInDimension} |`;\n1479:     })\n1480:     .join('\\n');\n1481: \n1482:   return [\n1483:     '---',\n1484:     'title: Deep Review Dashboard',\n1485:     'description: Auto-generated reducer view over the review packet.',\n1486:     '---',\n1487:     '',\n1488:     '# Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview',\n1489:     '',\n1490:     'Auto-generated from JSONL state log, iteration files, findings registry, and strategy state. Never manually edited.',\n1491:     '',\n1492:     '<!-- ANCHOR:overview -->',\n1493:     '## 1. OVERVIEW',\n1494:     '',\n1495:     'Reducer-generated observability surface for the active review packet.',\n1496:     '',\n1497:     '<!-- /ANCHOR:overview -->',\n1498:     '<!-- ANCHOR:status -->',\n1499:     '## 2. STATUS',\n1500:     `- Review Target: ${config.reviewTarget || '[Unknown target]'} (${config.reviewTargetType || 'unknown'})`,\n1501:     `- Started: ${config.createdAt || '[Unknown start]'}`,\n1502:     `- Status: ${registry.status || String(config.status || 'initialized').toUpperCase()}`,\n1503:     `- Iteration: ${iterationRecords.filter((record) => record.type === 'iteration').length} of ${config.maxIterations || 0}`,\n1504:     `- Provisional Verdict: ${verdict}`,\n1505:     `- hasSearchDebt: ${hasSearchDebt}`,\n1506:     `- hasAdvisories: ${hasAdvisories}`,\n1507:     `- Session ID: ${registry.sessionId || '[Unknown session]'}`,\n1508:     `- Parent Session: ${registry.parentSessionId ?? 'none'}`,\n1509:     `- Lifecycle Mode: ${registry.lineageMode || 'new'}`,\n1510:     `- Generation: ${registry.generation ?? 1}`,\n1511:     `- continuedFromRun: ${registry.continuedFromRun ?? 'none'}`,\n1512:     ...(registry.terminalStop?.stopReason ? [`- stopReason: ${registry.terminalStop.stopReason}`] : []),\n1513:     '',\n1514:     '<!-- /ANCHOR:status -->',\n1515:     '<!-- ANCHOR:findings-summary -->',\n1516:     '## 3. FINDINGS SUMMARY',\n1517:     '',\n1518:     '| Severity | Count |',\n1519:     '|----------|------:|',\n1520:     `| P0 (Blockers) | ${severity.P0} |`,\n1521:     `| P1 (Required) | ${severity.P1} |`,\n1522:     `| P2 (Suggestions) | ${severity.P2} |`,\n1523:     `| Resolved | ${registry.resolvedFindingsCount} |`,\n1524:     '',\n1525:     '<!-- /ANCHOR:findings-summary -->',\n1526:     '<!-- ANCHOR:progress -->',\n1527:     '## 4. PROGRESS',\n1528:     '',\n1529:     '| # | Focus | Dimensions | Ratio | P0/P1/P2 | Status |',\n1530:     '|---|-------|------------|-------|----------|--------|',\n1531:     progressRows,\n1532:     '',\n1533:     '<!-- /ANCHOR:progress -->',\n1534:     '<!-- ANCHOR:dimension-coverage -->',\n1535:     '## 5. DIMENSION COVERAGE',\n1536:     '',\n1537:     '| Dimension | Status | Open findings |',\n1538:     '|-----------|--------|--------------:|',\n1539:     dimensionRows,\n1540:     '',\n1541:     '<!-- /ANCHOR:dimension-coverage -->',\n1542:     '<!-- ANCHOR:blocked-stops -->',\n1543:     '## 6. BLOCKED STOPS',\n1544:     ...(registry.blockedStopHistory && registry.blockedStopHistory.length > 0\n1545:       ? registry.blockedStopHistory.flatMap((entry) => {\n1546:           const blockers = formatBlockedByList(entry.blockedBy);\n1547:           const gateSummary = entry.gateResults && typeof entry.gateResults === 'object'\n1548:             ? Object.entries(entry.gateResults)\n1549:                 .map(([gate, result]) => {\n1550:                   const pass = result && typeof result === 'object' && 'pass' in result ? result.pass : '?';\n1551:                   return `${gate}: ${pass}`;\n1552:                 })\n1553:                 .join(', ')\n1554:             : '[no gate results]';\n1555:           return [\n1556:             `### Iteration ${entry.run} — blocked by [${blockers}]`,\n1557:             `- Recovery: ${entry.recoveryStrategy || '[no recovery strategy recorded]'}`,\n1558:             `- Gate results: ${gateSummary}`,\n1559:             `- Timestamp: ${entry.timestamp || '[no timestamp]'}`,\n1560:             '',\n1561:           ];\n1562:         })\n1563:       : ['No blocked-stop events recorded.', '']),\n1564:     '<!-- /ANCHOR:blocked-stops -->',\n1565:     '<!-- ANCHOR:graph-convergence -->',\n1566:     '## 7. GRAPH CONVERGENCE',\n1567:     `- graphConvergenceScore: ${Number(registry.graphConvergenceScore || 0).toFixed(2)}`,\n1568:     `- graphDecision: ${registry.graphDecision || 'none'}`,\n1569:     ...(Array.isArray(registry.graphBlockers) && registry.graphBlockers.length > 0\n1570:       ? [`- graphBlockers: ${registry.graphBlockers.map((b) => (typeof b === 'string' ? b : JSON.stringify(b))).join(', ')}`]\n1571:       : ['- graphBlockers: none']),\n1572:     '',\n1573:     '<!-- /ANCHOR:graph-convergence -->',\n1574:     '<!-- ANCHOR:trend -->',\n1575:     '## 8. TREND',\n1576:     `- Last 3 ratios: ${lastThreeRatios}`,\n1577:     `- convergenceScore: ${Number(registry.convergenceScore || 0).toFixed(2)}`,\n1578:     `- openFindings: ${registry.openFindingsCount}`,\n1579:     `- persistentSameSeverity: ${(registry.persistentSameSeverity || []).length}`,\n1580:     `- severityChanged: ${(registry.severityChanged || []).length}`,\n1581:     `- repeatedFindings (deprecated combined bucket): ${registry.repeatedFindings.length}`,\n1582:     '',\n1583:     '<!-- /ANCHOR:trend -->',\n1584:     '<!-- ANCHOR:corruption-warnings -->',\n1585:     '## 9. CORRUPTION WARNINGS',\n1586:     ...(Array.isArray(registry.corruptionWarnings) && registry.corruptionWarnings.length > 0\n1587:       ? registry.corruptionWarnings.map((w) => `- Line ${w.line}: ${w.error} (raw: ${w.raw})`)\n1588:       : ['No corrupt JSONL lines detected.']),\n1589:     '',\n1590:     '<!-- /ANCHOR:corruption-warnings -->',\n1591:     '<!-- ANCHOR:search-debt -->',\n1592:     '## 10. SEARCH DEBT',\n1593:     renderSearchDebtSection(registry),\n1594:     '',\n1595:     '<!-- /ANCHOR:search-debt -->',\n1596:     '<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->',\n1597:     '## 11. NEXT FOCUS',\n1598:     nextFocus,\n1599:     '',\n1600:     '<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->',\n1601:     '<!-- ANCHOR:active-risks -->',\n1602:     '## 12. ACTIVE RISKS',\n1603:     ...(function buildActiveRisks() {\n1604:       // Surface non-P0 release-readiness debt alongside P0s so the dashboard\n1605:       // cannot hide P1 debt behind a\n1606:       // \"None active\" summary when activeP0 == 0. Gate debt on the latest\n1607:       // `blocked_stop` and `claim_adjudication` events so operators see\n1608:       // claim-adjudication and legal-stop gate failures, not just severity.\n1609:       const lines = [];\n1610:       if (latestIteration?.status === 'error') {\n1611:         lines.push('- Latest iteration reported error status.');\n1612:       }\n1613:       if (severity.P0 > 0) {\n1614:         lines.push(`- ${severity.P0} active P0 finding(s) blocking release.`);\n1615:       }\n1616:       if (severity.P1 > 0) {\n1617:         lines.push(`- ${severity.P1} active P1 finding(s) — required before release; not a P0 but still blocks PASS.`);\n1618:       }\n1619:       const latestClaimAdjudication = [...iterationRecords]\n1620:         .reverse()\n1621:         .find((record) => record\n1622:           && record.type === 'event'\n1623:           && record.event === 'claim_adjudication'\n1624:           && typeof getNestedField(record, 'passed') === 'boolean'\n1625:           && !normalizeText(getNestedField(record, 'findingId') || ''));\n1626:       const activeP0P1 = severity.P0 + severity.P1;\n1627:       const adjudicationActiveCount = isFiniteNumber(getNestedField(latestClaimAdjudication, 'activeP0P1'))\n1628:         ? getNestedField(latestClaimAdjudication, 'activeP0P1')\n1629:         : activeP0P1;\n1630:       if (latestClaimAdjudication && getNestedField(latestClaimAdjudication, 'passed') === false && activeP0P1 > 0 && adjudicationActiveCount > 0) {\n1631:         const missingPackets = getNestedField(latestClaimAdjudication, 'missingPackets');\n1632:         const missing = Array.isArray(missingPackets) && missingPackets.length > 0\n1633:           ? ` (missing packets: ${missingPackets.join(', ')})`\n1634:           : '';\n1635:         lines.push(`- Claim-adjudication gate last failed at run ${latestClaimAdjudication.run ?? '?'}${missing}. STOP is vetoed until every active P0/P1 has a typed claim-adjudication packet.`);\n1636:       }\n1637:       const latestBlockedStop = registry.blockedStopHistory?.at(-1);\n1638:       if (latestBlockedStop && Array.isArray(latestBlockedStop.blockedBy) && latestBlockedStop.blockedBy.length > 0) {\n1639:         lines.push(`- Latest blocked_stop at run ${latestBlockedStop.run ?? '?'}: ${formatBlockedByList(latestBlockedStop.blockedBy)}. Recovery: ${latestBlockedStop.recoveryStrategy || 'see dashboard §BLOCKED STOPS'}.`);\n1640:       }\n1641:       if (hasSearchDebt) {\n1642:         lines.push(`- ${registry.searchDebt.length} search-debt obligation(s) remain deferred or blocked. Verdict is CONDITIONAL until they are covered or ruled out.`);\n1643:       }\n1644:       if (severity.P2 > 0 && lines.length === 0) {\n1645:         lines.push(`- ${severity.P2} active P2 finding(s) — advisory only; release is not blocked by P2 alone, but the debt is tracked here so it does not disappear.`);\n1646:       }\n1647:       if (lines.length === 0) {\n1648:         lines.push('- None active beyond normal review uncertainty.');\n1649:       }\n1650:       return lines;\n1651:     })(),\n1652:     '',\n1653:     '<!-- /ANCHOR:active-risks -->',\n1654:     '',\n1655:   ].join('\\n');\n1656: }\n1657: \n1658: /**\n1659:  * Reduce JSONL state, iteration files, and strategy into synchronized registry,\n1660:  * strategy, and dashboard outputs. Idempotent: repeated calls produce identical results.\n1661:  *\n1662:  * @param {string} specFolder - Path to the target spec folder for the review packet\n1663:  * @param {Object} [options] - Reducer options\n1664:  * @param {boolean} [options.write=true] - Write outputs to disk when true\n1665:  * @returns {Object} Paths and content for registry, strategy, and dashboard\n1666:  */\n1667: function reduceReviewState(specFolder, options = {}) {\n1668:   const write = options.write !== false;\n1669:   const lenient = Boolean(options.lenient);\n1670:   const createMissingAnchors = Boolean(options.createMissingAnchors);\n1671:   const emitResourceMapOutput = Boolean(options.emitResourceMap);\n1672:   const resolvedSpecFolder = path.resolve(specFolder);\n1673:   const { artifactDir: reviewDir } = resolveArtifactRoot(resolvedSpecFolder, 'review');\n1674:   const configPath = path.join(reviewDir, 'deep-review-config.json');\n1675:   const stateLogPath = path.join(reviewDir, 'deep-review-state.jsonl');\n1676:   const strategyPath = path.join(reviewDir, 'deep-review-strategy.md');\n1677:   const registryPath = path.join(reviewDir, 'deep-review-findings-registry.json');\n1678:   const dashboardPath = path.join(reviewDir, 'deep-review-dashboard.md');\n1679:   const resourceMapPath = path.join(reviewDir, 'resource-map.md');\n1680:   const iterationDir = path.join(reviewDir, 'iterations');\n1681:   const deltaDir = path.join(reviewDir, 'deltas');\n1682: \n1683:   const config = readJson(configPath);\n1684:   const { records, corruptionWarnings } = parseJsonlDetailed(readUtf8(stateLogPath));\n1685:   const terminalStop = buildTerminalStopState(records);\n1686:   const lineage = buildLineageState(config, records, terminalStop);\n1687:   config.sessionId = lineage.sessionId || config.sessionId || '';\n1688:   config.parentSessionId = lineage.parentSessionId;\n1689:   config.lineageMode = lineage.lineageMode;\n1690:   config.generation = lineage.generation;\n1691:   config.continuedFromRun = lineage.continuedFromRun;\n1692:   if (terminalStop?.stopReason) {\n1693:     config.stopReason = terminalStop.stopReason;\n1694:   }\n1695:   const strategyContent = fs.existsSync(strategyPath) ? readUtf8(strategyPath) : '';\n1696:   const strategyDimensions = parseStrategyDimensions(strategyContent);\n1697:   const iterationFiles = fs.existsSync(iterationDir)\n1698:     ? fs.readdirSync(iterationDir)\n1699:         .filter((fileName) => /^iteration-\\d+\\.md$/.test(fileName))\n1700:         .sort()\n1701:         .map((fileName) => parseIterationFile(path.join(iterationDir, fileName)))\n1702:     : [];\n1703: \n1704:   // P1-026 fix: load delta payloads up-front so the finding registry can be\n1705:   // built from {type:\"finding\"} delta records (primary source) rather than\n1706:   // relying solely on iteration markdown parsing (legacy/fallback). The\n1707:   // resource-map emit path below reuses these loaded payloads.\n1708:   const deltaPayloads = fs.existsSync(deltaDir) ? loadDeltaPayloads(deltaDir) : [];\n1709:   const flattenedDeltaRecords = deltaPayloads\n1710:     .flat()\n1711:     .filter((record) => record !== null && record !== undefined);\n1712: \n1713:   const registry = buildRegistry(strategyDimensions, iterationFiles, records, config, corruptionWarnings, flattenedDeltaRecords);\n1714:   const strategy = updateStrategyContent(strategyContent, registry, iterationFiles, { createMissingAnchors }, records);\n1715:   const dashboard = renderDashboard(config, registry, records, iterationFiles);\n1716:   let resourceMap = null;\n1717:   let resourceMapSkipped = true;\n1718:   let resourceMapSkipReason = null;\n1719: \n1720:   if (corruptionWarnings.length > 0 && !lenient) {\n1721:     throw createCorruptionError(stateLogPath, corruptionWarnings);\n1722:   }\n1723: \n1724:   if (emitResourceMapOutput) {\n1725:     if (getResourceMapEmitSetting(config) === false) {\n1726:       resourceMapSkipReason = 'config.resource_map.emit=false';\n1727:     } else {\n1728:       // Reuse the deltaPayloads already loaded above (P1-026 fix) — avoids re-reading.\n1729:       if (!deltaPayloads.length) {\n1730:         resourceMapSkipReason = 'no delta files found';\n1731:       } else {\n1732:         resourceMap = emitResourceMap({\n1733:           shape: 'review',\n1734:           deltas: deltaPayloads,\n1735:           packet: {\n1736:             title: config.reviewTarget || path.basename(resolvedSpecFolder),\n1737:             specFolder: resolvedSpecFolder,\n1738:           },\n1739:           scope: `review convergence output for ${path.basename(resolvedSpecFolder)}`,\n1740:           createdAt: new Date().toISOString(),\n1741:         });\n1742:         resourceMapSkipped = false;\n1743:       }\n1744:     }\n1745:   }\n1746: \n1747:   if (write) {\n1748:     writeUtf8(registryPath, `${JSON.stringify(registry, null, 2)}\\n`);\n1749:     if (strategyContent) {\n1750:       writeUtf8(strategyPath, strategy.endsWith('\\n') ? strategy : `${strategy}\\n`);\n1751:     }\n1752:     writeUtf8(dashboardPath, dashboard);\n1753:     if (emitResourceMapOutput && resourceMap) {\n1754:       writeUtf8(resourceMapPath, resourceMap);\n1755:     }\n1756:   }\n1757: \n1758:   return {\n1759:     configPath,\n1760:     stateLogPath,\n1761:     strategyPath,\n1762:     registryPath,\n1763:     dashboardPath,\n1764:     resourceMapPath,\n1765:     registry,\n1766:     strategy,\n1767:     dashboard,\n1768:     resourceMap,\n1769:     resourceMapSkipped,\n1770:     resourceMapSkipReason,\n1771:     corruptionWarnings,\n1772:     hasCorruption: corruptionWarnings.length > 0,\n1773:   };\n1774: }\n1775: \n1776: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1777: // 6. CLI ENTRY POINT\n1778: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1779: \n1780: if (require.main === module) {\n1781:   const args = process.argv.slice(2);\n1782:   const lenient = args.includes('--lenient');\n1783:   const createMissingAnchors = args.includes('--create-missing-anchors');\n1784:   const emitResourceMapOutput = args.includes('--emit-resource-map');\n1785:   const positional = args.filter((arg) => !arg.startsWith('--'));\n1786:   const specFolder = positional[0];\n1787: \n1788:   if (!specFolder) {\n1789:     process.stderr.write(\n1790:       'Usage: node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs <spec-folder> [--lenient] [--create-missing-anchors] [--emit-resource-map]\\n',\n1791:     );\n1792:     process.exit(1);\n1793:   }\n1794: \n1795:   try {\n1796:     const result = reduceReviewState(specFolder, {\n1797:       write: true,\n1798:       lenient,\n1799:       createMissingAnchors,\n1800:       emitResourceMap: emitResourceMapOutput,\n1801:     });\n1802:     process.stdout.write(\n1803:       `${JSON.stringify(\n1804:         {\n1805:           registryPath: result.registryPath,\n1806:           dashboardPath: result.dashboardPath,\n1807:           strategyPath: result.strategyPath,\n1808:           openFindingsCount: result.registry.openFindingsCount,\n1809:           resolvedFindingsCount: result.registry.resolvedFindingsCount,\n1810:           convergenceScore: result.registry.convergenceScore,\n1811:           graphConvergenceScore: result.registry.graphConvergenceScore,\n1812:           searchDebtCount: Array.isArray(result.registry.searchDebt) ? result.registry.searchDebt.length : 0,\n1813:           corruptionCount: result.corruptionWarnings.length,\n1814:           resourceMapPath: emitResourceMapOutput ? result.resourceMapPath : null,\n1815:           resourceMapSkipped: emitResourceMapOutput ? result.resourceMapSkipped : null,\n1816:           resourceMapSkipReason: emitResourceMapOutput ? result.resourceMapSkipReason : null,\n1817:         },\n1818:         null,\n1819:         2,\n1820:       )}\\n`,\n1821:     );\n1822:   } catch (error) {\n1823:     if (error && error.code === 'STATE_CORRUPTION') {\n1824:       process.stderr.write(`${error.message}\\n`);\n1825:       process.exit(2);\n1826:     }\n1827:     process.stderr.write(`[deep-review] reducer failed: ${error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error)}\\n`);\n1828:     process.exit(3);\n1829:   }\n1830: }\n1831: \n1832: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1833: // 7. EXPORTS\n1834: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1835: \n1836: module.exports = {\n1837:   REQUIRED_DIMENSIONS,\n1838:   SEVERITY_KEYS,\n1839:   SEVERITY_WEIGHTS,\n1840:   buildGraphConvergenceRollup,\n1841:   parseIterationFile,\n1842:   parseJsonl,\n1843:   parseJsonlDetailed,\n1844:   parseFindingLine,\n1845:   replaceAnchorSection,\n1846:   reduceReviewState,\n1847:   deltaRecordToFinding,\n1848:   deriveDashboardStatus,\n1849:   collapseFindingsByDedupKey,\n1850:   findingDedupKey,\n1851:   buildTraceabilityRollup,\n1852:   validateReviewRecordFields,\n1853: };\n\n(End of file - total 1853 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"      const suffix = content.endsWith('\\n') ? '' : '\\n';\n      return `${content}${suffix}\\n${replacement}\\n`;\n    }\n    throw new Error(\n      `Missing machine-owned anchor \"${anchorId}\" in deep-review strategy file. `\n      + 'Pass createMissing:true (or the reducer CLI flag --create-missing-anchors) to bootstrap.',\n    );\n  }\n  return content.replace(pattern, replacement);\n}\n\nfunction updateStrategyContent(strategyContent, registry, iterationFiles, options = {}, iterationRecords = []) {\n  // Early return when there is no strategy file to update. Empty content\n  // cannot contain the machine-owned anchors and replaceAnchorSection would\n  // correctly fail-close — but for that specific case we intentionally skip\n  // rather than throw so bootstrap flows (no strategy yet) still work.\n  if (!strategyContent) {\n    return strategyContent;\n  }\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs","text":"      const suffix = content.endsWith('\\n') ? '' : '\\n';\n      return `${content}${suffix}\\n${replacement}\\n`;\n    }\n    throw new Error(\n      `Missing machine-owned anchor \"${anchorId}\" in deep-review strategy file. `\n      + 'Pass createMissing:true (or the reducer CLI flag --create-missing-anchors) to bootstrap.',\n    );\n  }\n  return content.replace(pattern, replacement);\n}\n\nfunction updateStrategyContent(strategyContent, registry, iterationFiles, options = {}, iterationRecords = []) {\n  // Early return when there is no strategy file to update. Empty content\n  // cannot contain the machine-owned anchors and replaceAnchorSection would\n  // correctly fail-close — but for that specific case we intentionally skip\n  // rather than throw so bootstrap flows (no strategy yet) still work.\n  if (!strategyContent) {\n    return strategyContent;\n  }\n\n  const anchorOptions = { createMissing: Boolean(options.createMissingAnchors) };\n  const severity = registry.findingsBySeverity;\n  const runningFindings = [\n    `- P0 (Blockers): ${severity.P0}`,\n    `- P1 (Required): ${severity.P1}`,\n    `- P2 (Suggestions): ${severity.P2}`,\n    `- Resolved: ${registry.resolvedFindingsCount}`,\n  ].join('\\n');\n\n  const completedDimensions = REQUIRED_DIMENSIONS\n    .filter((dimension) => registry.dimensionCoverage[dimension])\n    .map((dimension) => `- [x] ${dimension}`)\n    .join('\\n') || '[None yet]';\n\n  const remainingDimensions = REQUIRED_DIMENSIONS\n    .filter((dimension) => !registry.dimensionCoverage[dimension])\n    .map((dimension) => `- [ ] ${dimension}`)\n    .join('\\n') || '[All dimensions complete]';\n\n  // Default next-focus comes from latest iteration → first uncovered dimension → fallback.\n  let nextFocus = iterationFiles.map((iteration) => iteration.nextFocus).filter(Boolean).at(-1)\n    || REQUIRED_DIMENSIONS.find((dimension) => !registry.dimensionCoverage[dimension])\n    || '[All dimensions covered]';\n\n  // Prefer the latest blocked-stop\n  // recovery only when blocked-stop is genuinely the most recent loop event.\n  // The earlier implementation read timestamps from the markdown iteration\n  // files, but parseIterationFile() never captures timestamps, so\n  // latestIterationTimestamp was always undefined and any historical\n  // blocked-stop permanently pinned next-focus. Fix: source recency from the\n  // JSONL iteration records (which do carry timestamps) instead.\n  const latestBlockedStop = registry.blockedStopHistory?.at(-1);\n  if (latestBlockedStop && latestBlockedStop.timestamp) {\n    const latestIterationTimestamp = iterationRecords\n      .filter((record) => record?.type === 'iteration' && typeof record.timestamp === 'string')\n      .map((record) => record.timestamp)\n      .at(-1);\n    const blockedIsMostRecent = !latestIterationTimestamp\n      || latestBlockedStop.timestamp >= latestIterationTimestamp;\n    if (blockedIsMostRecent) {\n      const blockers = formatBlockedByList(latestBlockedStop.blockedBy);\n      const recovery = latestBlockedStop.recoveryStrategy || '[no recovery strategy provided]';\n      nextFocus = [\n        `BLOCKED on: ${blockers}`,\n        `Recovery: ${recovery}`,\n        'Address the blocking gates before the next iteration.',\n      ].join('\\n');\n    }\n  }\n\n  let updated = strategyContent;\n  updated = replaceAnchorSection(updated, 'review-dimensions', '3. REVIEW DIMENSIONS (remaining)', remainingDimensions, anchorOptions);\n  updated = replaceAnchorSection(updated, 'completed-dimensions', '4. COMPLETED DIMENSIONS', completedDimensions, anchorOptions);\n  updated = replaceAnchorSection(updated, 'running-findings', '5. RUNNING FINDINGS', runningFindings, anchorOptions);\n  updated = replaceAnchorSection(\n    updated,\n    'exhausted-approaches',\n    '9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)',\n    buildExhaustedApproaches(iterationFiles),\n    anchorOptions,\n  );\n  updated = replaceAnchorSection(updated, 'next-focus', '11. NEXT FOCUS', nextFocus, anchorOptions);\n  return updated;\n}\n\nfunction renderDashboard(config, registry, iterationRecords, iterationFiles) {\n  const latestIteration = iterationRecords.filter((record) => record.type === 'iteration').at(-1);\n  const ratios = iterationRecords\n    .filter((record) => record.type === 'iteration')\n    .map((record) => (typeof record.newFindingsRatio === 'number' ? record.newFindingsRatio : null))\n    .filter((value) => value !== null);\n  const lastThreeRatios = ratios.slice(-3).map((value) => value.toFixed(2)).join(' -> ') || 'N/A';\n  const nextFocus = iterationFiles.map((iteration) => iteration.nextFocus).filter(Boolean).at(-1)\n    || REQUIRED_DIMENSIONS.find((dimension) => !registry.dimensionCoverage[dimension])\n    || '[All dimensions covered]';\n\n  const severity = registry.findingsBySeverity;\n  const hasSearchDebt = Array.isArray(registry.searchDebt) && registry.searchDebt.length > 0;\n  const verdict = severity.P0 > 0\n    ? 'FAIL'\n    : severity.P1 > 0 || hasSearchDebt\n      ? 'CONDITIONAL'\n      : 'PASS';\n  const hasAdvisories = verdict === 'PASS' && severity.P2 > 0;\n\n  const progressRows = iterationRecords\n    .filter((record) => record.type === 'iteration')\n    .map((record) => {\n      const dimensions = Array.isArray(record.dimensions) ? record.dimensions.join('/') : '-';\n      const ratio = typeof record.newFindingsRatio === 'number' ? record.newFindingsRatio.toFixed(2) : '0.00';\n      const summary = record.findingsSummary || {};\n      const findings = `${summary.P0 ?? 0}/${summary.P1 ?? 0}/${summary.P2 ?? 0}`;\n      return `| ${record.run} | ${record.focus || 'unknown'} | ${dimensions} | ${ratio} | ${findings} | ${record.status || 'complete'} |`;\n    })\n    .join('\\n') || '| 0 | none yet | - | 0.00 | 0/0/0 | initialized |';\n\n  const dimensionRows = REQUIRED_DIMENSIONS\n    .map((dimension) => {\n      const covered = registry.dimensionCoverage[dimension];\n      const status = covered ? 'covered' : 'pending';\n      const openInDimension = registry.openFindings.filter((finding) => finding.dimension === dimension).length;\n      return `| ${dimension} | ${status} | ${openInDimension} |`;\n    })\n    .join('\\n');\n\n  return [\n    '---',\n    'title: Deep Review Dashboard',\n    'description: Auto-generated reducer view over the review packet.',\n    '---',\n    '',\n    '# Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview',\n    '',\n    'Auto-generated from JSONL state log, iteration files, findings registry, and strategy state. Never manually edited.',\n    '',\n    '<!-- ANCHOR:overview -->',\n    '## 1. OVERVIEW',\n    '',\n    'Reducer-generated observability surface for the active review packet.',\n    '',\n    '<!-- /ANCHOR:overview -->',\n    '<!-- ANCHOR:status -->',\n    '## 2. STATUS',\n    `- Review Target: ${config.reviewTarget || '[Unknown target]'} (${config.reviewTargetType || 'unknown'})`,\n    `- Started: ${config.createdAt || '[Unknown start]'}`,\n    `- Status: ${registry.status || String(config.status || 'initialized').toUpperCase()}`,\n    `- Iteration: ${iterationRecords.filter((record) => record.type === 'iteration').length} of ${config.maxIterations || 0}`,\n    `- Provisional Verdict: ${verdict}`,\n    `- hasSearchDebt: ${hasSearchDebt}`,\n    `- hasAdvisories: ${hasAdvisories}`,\n    `- Session ID: ${registry.sessionId || '[Unknown session]'}`,\n    `- Parent Session: ${registry.parentSessionId ?? 'none'}`,\n    `- Lifecycle Mode: ${registry.lineageMode || 'new'}`,\n    `- Generation: ${registry.generation ?? 1}`,\n    `- continuedFromRun: ${registry.continuedFromRun ?? 'none'}`,\n    ...(registry.terminalStop?.stopReason ? [`- stopReason: ${registry.terminalStop.stopReason}`] : []),\n    '',\n    '<!-- /ANCHOR:status -->',\n    '<!-- ANCHOR:findings-summary -->',\n    '## 3. FINDINGS SUMMARY',\n    '',\n    '| Severity | Count |',\n    '|----------|------:|',\n    `| P0 (Blockers) | ${severity.P0} |`,\n    `| P1 (Required) | ${severity.P1} |`,\n    `| P2 (Suggestions) | ${severity.P2} |`,\n    `| Resolved | ${registry.resolvedFindingsCount} |`,\n    '',\n    '<!-- /ANCHOR:findings-summary -->',\n    '<!-- ANCHOR:progress -->',\n    '## 4. PROGRESS',\n    '',\n    '| # | Focus | Dimensions | Ratio | P0/P1/P2 | Status |',\n    '|---|-------|------------|-------|----------|--------|',\n    progressRows,\n    '',\n    '<!-- /ANCHOR:progress -->',\n    '<!-- ANCHOR:dimension-coverage -->',\n    '## 5. DIMENSION COVERAGE',\n    '',\n    '| Dimension | Status | Open findings |',\n    '|-----------|--------|--------------:|',\n    dimensionRows,\n    '',\n    '<!-- /ANCHOR:dimension-coverage -->',\n    '<!-- ANCHOR:blocked-stops -->',\n    '## 6. BLOCKED STOPS',\n    ...(registry.blockedStopHistory && registry.blockedStopHistory.length > 0\n      ? registry.blockedStopHistory.flatMap((entry) => {\n          const blockers = formatBlockedByList(entry.blockedBy);\n          const gateSummary = entry.gateResults && typeof entry.gateResults === 'object'\n            ? Object.entries(entry.gateResults)\n                .map(([gate, result]) => {\n                  const pass = result && typeof result === 'object' && 'pass' in result ? result.pass : '?';\n                  return `${gate}: ${pass}`;\n                })\n                .join(', ')\n            : '[no gate results]';\n          return [\n            `### Iteration ${entry.run} — blocked by [${blockers}]`,\n            `- Recovery: ${entry.recoveryStrategy || '[no recovery strategy recorded]'}`,\n            `- Gate results: ${gateSummary}`,\n            `- Timestamp: ${entry.timestamp || '[no timestamp]'}`,\n            '',\n          ];\n        })\n      : ['No blocked-stop events recorded.', '']),\n    '<!-- /ANCHOR:blocked-stops -->',\n    '<!-- ANCHOR:graph-convergence -->',\n    '## 7. GRAPH CONVERGENCE',\n    `- graphConvergenceScore: ${Number(registry.graphConvergenceScore || 0).toFixed(2)}`,\n    `- graphDecision: ${registry.graphDecision || 'none'}`,\n    ...(Array.isArray(registry.graphBlockers) && registry.graphBlockers.length > 0\n      ? [`- graphBlockers: ${registry.graphBlockers.map((b) => (typeof b === 'string' ? b : JSON.stringify(b))).join(', ')}`]\n      : ['- graphBlockers: none']),\n    '',\n    '<!-- /ANCHOR:graph-convergence -->',\n    '<!-- ANCHOR:trend -->',\n    '## 8. TREND',\n    `- Last 3 ratios: ${lastThreeRatios}`,\n    `- convergenceScore: ${Number(registry.convergenceScore || 0).toFixed(2)}`,\n    `- openFindings: ${registry.openFindingsCount}`,\n    `- persistentSameSeverity: ${(registry.persistentSameSeverity || []).length}`,\n    `- severityChanged: ${(registry.severityChanged || []).length}`,\n    `- repeatedFindings (deprecated combined bucket): ${registry.repeatedFindings.length}`,\n    '',\n    '<!-- /ANCHOR:trend -->',\n    '<!-- ANCHOR:corruption-warnings -->',\n    '## 9. CORRUPTION WARNINGS',\n    ...(Array.isArray(registry.corruptionWarnings) && registry.corruptionWarnings.length > 0\n      ? registry.corruptionWarnings.map((w) => `- Line ${w.line}: ${w.error} (raw: ${w.raw})`)\n      : ['No corrupt JSONL lines detected.']),\n    '',\n    '<!-- /ANCHOR:corruption-warnings -->',\n    '<!-- ANCHOR:search-debt -->',\n    '## 10. SEARCH DEBT',\n    renderSearchDebtSection(registry),\n    '',\n    '<!-- /ANCHOR:search-debt -->',\n    '<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->',\n    '## 11. NEXT FOCUS',\n    nextFocus,\n    '',\n    '<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->',\n    '<!-- ANCHOR:active-risks -->',\n    '## 12. ACTIVE RISKS',\n    ...(function buildActiveRisks() {\n      // Surface non-P0 release-readiness debt alongside P0s so the dashboard\n      // cannot hide P1 debt behind a\n      // \"None active\" summary when activeP0 == 0. Gate debt on the latest\n      // `blocked_stop` and `claim_adjudication` events so operators see\n      // claim-adjudication and legal-stop gate failures, not just severity.\n      const lines = [];\n      if (latestIteration?.status === 'error') {\n        lines.push('- Latest iteration reported error status.');\n      }\n      if (severity.P0 > 0) {\n        lines.push(`- ${severity.P0} active P0 finding(s) blocking release.`);\n      }\n      if (severity.P1 > 0) {\n        lines.push(`- ${severity.P1} active P1 finding(s) — required before release; not a P0 but still blocks PASS.`);\n      }\n      const latestClaimAdjudication = [...iterationRecords]\n        .reverse()\n        .find((record) => record\n          && record.type === 'event'\n          && record.event === 'claim_adjudication'\n          && typeof getNestedField(record, 'passed') === 'boolean'\n          && !normalizeText(getNestedField(record, 'findingId') || ''));\n      const activeP0P1 = severity.P0 + severity.P1;\n      const adjudicationActiveCount = isFiniteNumber(getNestedField(latestClaimAdjudication, 'activeP0P1'))\n        ? getNestedField(latestClaimAdjudication, 'activeP0P1')\n        : activeP0P1;\n      if (latestClaimAdjudication && getNestedField(latestClaimAdjudication, 'passed') === false && activeP0P1 > 0 && adjudicationActiveCount > 0) {\n        const missingPackets = getNestedField(latestClaimAdjudication, 'missingPackets');\n        const missing = Array.isArray(missingPackets) && missingPackets.length > 0\n          ? ` (missing packets: ${missingPackets.join(', ')})`\n          : '';\n        lines.push(`- Claim-adjudication gate last failed at run ${latestClaimAdjudication.run ?? '?'}${missing}. STOP is vetoed until every active P0/P1 has a typed claim-adjudication packet.`);\n      }\n      const latestBlockedStop = registry.blockedStopHistory?.at(-1);\n      if (latestBlockedStop && Array.isArray(latestBlockedStop.blockedBy) && latestBlockedStop.blockedBy.length > 0) {\n        lines.push(`- Latest blocked_stop at run ${latestBlockedStop.run ?? '?'}: ${formatBlockedByList(latestBlockedStop.blockedBy)}. Recovery: ${latestBlockedStop.recoveryStrategy || 'see dashboard §BLOCKED STOPS'}.`);\n      }\n      if (hasSearchDebt) {\n        lines.push(`- ${registry.searchDebt.length} search-debt obligation(s) remain deferred or blocked. Verdict is CONDITIONAL until they are covered or ruled out.`);\n      }\n      if (severity.P2 > 0 && lines.length === 0) {\n        lines.push(`- ${severity.P2} active P2 finding(s) — advisory only; release is not blocked by P2 alone, but the debt is tracked here so it does not disappear.`);\n      }\n      if (lines.length === 0) {\n        lines.push('- None active beyond normal review uncertainty.');\n      }\n      return lines;\n    })(),\n    '',\n    '<!-- /ANCHOR:active-risks -->',\n    '',\n  ].join('\\n');\n}\n\n/**\n * Reduce JSONL state, iteration files, and strategy into synchronized registry,\n * strategy, and dashboard outputs. Idempotent: repeated calls produce identical results.\n *\n * @param {string} specFolder - Path to the target spec folder for the review packet\n * @param {Object} [options] - Reducer options\n * @param {boolean} [options.write=true] - Write outputs to disk when true\n * @returns {Object} Paths and content for registry, strategy, and dashboard\n */\nfunction reduceReviewState(specFolder, options = {}) {\n  const write = options.write !== false;\n  const lenient = Boolean(options.lenient);\n  const createMissingAnchors = Boolean(options.createMissingAnchors);\n  const emitResourceMapOutput = Boolean(options.emitResourceMap);\n  const resolvedSpecFolder = path.resolve(specFolder);\n  const { artifactDir: reviewDir } = resolveArtifactRoot(resolvedSpecFolder, 'review');\n  const configPath = path.join(reviewDir, 'deep-review-config.json');\n  const stateLogPath = path.join(reviewDir, 'deep-review-state.jsonl');\n  const strategyPath = path.join(reviewDir, 'deep-review-strategy.md');\n  const registryPath = path.join(reviewDir, 'deep-review-findings-registry.json');\n  const dashboardPath = path.join(reviewDir, 'deep-review-dashboard.md');\n  const resourceMapPath = path.join(reviewDir, 'resource-map.md');\n  const iterationDir = path.join(reviewDir, 'iterations');\n  const deltaDir = path.join(reviewDir, 'deltas');\n\n  const config = readJson(configPath);\n  const { records, corruptionWarnings } = parseJsonlDetailed(readUtf8(stateLogPath));\n  const terminalStop = buildTerminalStopState(records);\n  const lineage = buildLineageState(config, records, terminalStop);\n  config.sessionId = lineage.sessionId || config.sessionId || '';\n  config.parentSessionId = lineage.parentSessionId;\n  config.lineageMode = lineage.lineageMode;\n  config.generation = lineage.generation;\n  config.continuedFromRun = lineage.continuedFromRun;\n  if (terminalStop?.stopReason) {\n    config.stopReason = terminalStop.stopReason;\n  }\n  const strategyContent = fs.existsSync(strategyPath) ? readUtf8(strategyPath) : '';\n  const strategyDimensions = parseStrategyDimensions(strategyContent);\n  const iterationFiles = fs.existsSync(iterationDir)\n    ? fs.readdirSync(iterationDir)\n        .filter((fileName) => /^iteration-\\d+\\.md$/.test(fileName))\n        .sort()\n        .map((fileName) => parseIterationFile(path.join(iterationDir, fileName)))\n    : [];\n\n  // P1-026 fix: load delta payloads up-front so the finding registry can be\n  // built from {type:\"finding\"} delta records (primary source) rather than\n  // relying solely on iteration markdown parsing (legacy/fallback). The\n  // resource-map emit path below reuses these loaded payloads.\n  const deltaPayloads = fs.existsSync(deltaDir) ? loadDeltaPayloads(deltaDir) : [];\n  const flattenedDeltaRecords = deltaPayloads\n    .flat()\n    .filter((record) => record !== null && record !== undefined);\n\n  const registry = buildRegistry(strategyDimensions, iterationFiles, records, config, corruptionWarnings, flattenedDeltaRecords);\n  const strategy = updateStrategyContent(strategyContent, registry, iterationFiles, { createMissingAnchors }, records);\n  const dashboard = renderDashboard(config, registry, records, iterationFiles);\n  let resourceMap = null;\n  let resourceMapSkipped = true;\n  let resourceMapSkipReason = null;\n\n  if (corruptionWarnings.length > 0 && !lenient) {\n    throw createCorruptionError(stateLogPath, corruptionWarnings);\n  }\n\n  if (emitResourceMapOutput) {\n    if (getResourceMapEmitSetting(config) === false) {\n      resourceMapSkipReason = 'config.resource_map.emit=false';\n    } else {\n      // Reuse the deltaPayloads already loaded above (P1-026 fix) — avoids re-reading.\n      if (!deltaPayloads.length) {\n        resourceMapSkipReason = 'no delta files found';\n      } else {\n        resourceMap = emitResourceMap({\n          shape: 'review',\n          deltas: deltaPayloads,\n          packet: {\n            title: config.reviewTarget || path.basename(resolvedSpecFolder),\n            specFolder: resolvedSpecFolder,\n          },\n          scope: `review convergence output for ${path.basename(resolvedSpecFolder)}`,\n          createdAt: new Date().toISOString(),\n        });\n        resourceMapSkipped = false;\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  if (write) {\n    writeUtf8(registryPath, `${JSON.stringify(registry, null, 2)}\\n`);\n    if (strategyContent) {\n      writeUtf8(strategyPath, strategy.endsWith('\\n') ? strategy : `${strategy}\\n`);\n    }\n    writeUtf8(dashboardPath, dashboard);\n    if (emitResourceMapOutput && resourceMap) {\n      writeUtf8(resourceMapPath, resourceMap);\n    }\n  }\n\n  return {\n    configPath,\n    stateLogPath,\n    strategyPath,\n    registryPath,\n    dashboardPath,\n    resourceMapPath,\n    registry,\n    strategy,\n    dashboard,\n    resourceMap,\n    resourceMapSkipped,\n    resourceMapSkipReason,\n    corruptionWarnings,\n    hasCorruption: corruptionWarnings.length > 0,\n  };\n}\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 6. CLI ENTRY POINT\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nif (require.main === module) {\n  const args = process.argv.slice(2);\n  const lenient = args.includes('--lenient');\n  const createMissingAnchors = args.includes('--create-missing-anchors');\n  const emitResourceMapOutput = args.includes('--emit-resource-map');\n  const positional = args.filter((arg) => !arg.startsWith('--'));\n  const specFolder = positional[0];\n\n  if (!specFolder) {\n    process.stderr.write(\n      'Usage: node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs <spec-folder> [--lenient] [--create-missing-anchors] [--emit-resource-map]\\n',\n    );\n    process.exit(1);\n  }\n\n  try {\n    const result = reduceReviewState(specFolder, {\n      write: true,\n      lenient,\n      createMissingAnchors,\n      emitResourceMap: emitResourceMapOutput,\n    });\n    process.stdout.write(\n      `${JSON.stringify(\n        {\n          registryPath: result.registryPath,\n          dashboardPath: result.dashboardPath,\n          strategyPath: result.strategyPath,\n          openFindingsCount: result.registry.openFindingsCount,\n          resolvedFindingsCount: result.registry.resolvedFindingsCount,\n          convergenceScore: result.registry.convergenceScore,\n          graphConvergenceScore: result.registry.graphConvergenceScore,\n          searchDebtCount: Array.isArray(result.registry.searchDebt) ? result.registry.searchDebt.length : 0,\n          corruptionCount: result.corruptionWarnings.length,\n          resourceMapPath: emitResourceMapOutput ? result.resourceMapPath : null,\n          resourceMapSkipped: emitResourceMapOutput ? result.resourceMapSkipped : null,\n          resourceMapSkipReason: emitResourceMapOutput ? result.resourceMapSkipReason : null,\n        },\n        null,\n        2,\n      )}\\n`,\n    );\n  } catch (error) {\n    if (error && error.code === 'STATE_CORRUPTION') {\n      process.stderr.write(`${error.message}\\n`);\n      process.exit(2);\n    }\n    process.stderr.write(`[deep-review] reducer failed: ${error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error)}\\n`);\n    process.exit(3);\n  }\n}\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 7. EXPORTS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nmodule.exports = {\n  REQUIRED_DIMENSIONS,\n  SEVERITY_KEYS,\n  SEVERITY_WEIGHTS,\n  buildGraphConvergenceRollup,\n  parseIterationFile,\n  parseJsonl,\n  parseJsonlDetailed,\n  parseFindingLine,\n  replaceAnchorSection,\n  reduceReviewState,\n  deltaRecordToFinding,\n  deriveDashboardStatus,\n  collapseFindingsByDedupKey,\n  findingDedupKey,\n  buildTraceabilityRollup,\n  validateReviewRecordFields,\n};","lineStart":1357,"lineEnd":1853,"totalLines":1853,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs","time":{"start":1781762495927,"end":1781762495934}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0769505bcbd63f22016a3389bfcc04819185c473134129f0c7"}},"id":"prt_ed95215b2001k2QARPd3dro19g","sessionID":"ses_126af6eadffeKdnQM4mriL3y8K","messageID":"msg_ed951f9a5001ysEsw3IOF6NfYQ"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781762495973,"sessionID":"ses_126af6eadffeKdnQM4mriL3y8K","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ujUvfdnIdFjvIIalyQhrZBNW","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-review.md","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-review.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: name: deep-review\n3: description: LEAF deep-review iteration agent: one dimension/pass, P0/P1/P2 findings, JSONL state.\n4: mode: subagent\n5: temperature: 0.1\n6: permission:\n7:   read: allow\n8:   write: allow\n9:   edit: allow\n10:   bash: allow\n11:   grep: allow\n12:   glob: allow\n13:   webfetch: deny\n14:   memory: allow\n15:   code_graph_query: allow\n16:   code_graph_context: allow\n17:   detect_changes: allow\n18:   chrome_devtools: deny\n19:   task: deny\n20:   list: allow\n21:   patch: deny\n22: ---\n23: \n24: # The Deep Reviewer: Iterative Code Quality Agent\n25: \n26: Executes ONE review iteration within an autonomous review loop: read externalized state, review one focused dimension, produce P0/P1/P2 findings with file:line evidence, record edge cases and integration touchpoints, and update state for the next iteration.\n27: \n28: **Path Convention**: Use only `.opencode/agents/*.md` as the canonical runtime path reference.\n29: \n30: **Hook-Injected Advisor Context**: Treat hook-injected skill-advisor recommendations as routing hints only. They never override explicit user instructions, active command workflow, scope gates, runtime permissions, agent boundaries, or required skill loading. If advisor context conflicts with the dispatch prompt or verified local files, prefer the dispatch prompt plus file evidence and report the conflict.\n31: \n32: **Efficiency governor (the per-turn hook does not reach sub-agents — apply it here)**: reason about the problem, not yourself; lead with the result and act rather than narrate (batch tool calls, report at checkpoints); commit reversible decisions and move; qualify only when it changes what the reader should do.\n33: \n34: **CRITICAL**: This agent executes a SINGLE review iteration, not the full loop. The loop is managed by `/deep:review` and dispatches this agent once per iteration.\n35: \n36: **IMPORTANT**: This agent is a hybrid of @review severity discipline and the deep-review loop contract. It reviews code but does NOT modify code under review.\n37: \n38: > **SPEC FOLDER PERMISSION:** @deep-review may write only the resolved local-owner review packet for the target spec. Writable files are limited to the iteration artifact, strategy file, and JSONL state log listed in this agent contract. Review target files, reducer outputs, dashboards, reports, commands, skills, canonical agent files, and runtime mirrors are strictly READ-ONLY.\n39: \n40: ## Convergence Threshold Semantics\n41: \n42: **Default:** 0.10 (weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio)\n43: \n44: **Semantic:** `convergenceThreshold` compares new severity-weighted findings (P0=10, P1=5, P2=1) against accumulated findings. Lower = more iterations / higher signal threshold.\n45: \n46: **NOT INTERCHANGEABLE with siblings:**\n47: - `deep-research` uses 0.05 default on newInfoRatio (negative-knowledge emphasis)\n48: - `deep-ai-council` uses 0.20 default on adjudicator-verdict stability\n49: \n50: Carrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. Treat each deep-loop threshold as local to its own convergence semantics and verify against the owning skill contract before reuse.\n51: \n52: ---\n53: \n54: ## 0. ILLEGAL NESTING (HARD BLOCK)\n55: \n56: This agent is LEAF-only. Nested sub-agent dispatch is illegal.\n57: \n58: - NEVER create sub-tasks or dispatch sub-agents.\n59: - NEVER use the Task tool.\n60: - NEVER delegate to helper agents, background agents, external reviewers, or tool-controlled reviewers.\n61: - If a review question requires delegation, document the limitation in findings or `ruledOut` and recommend it for a future iteration.\n62: - Keep all review actions self-contained within this single execution.\n63: \n64: **HALT CONDITION -- Nested execution requested:** If dispatch asks this agent to spawn, route to, or wait for another agent/reviewer, refuse that instruction, complete only the parts possible inside this execution, and return `status: \"error\"` if the iteration cannot be completed without delegation.\n65: \n66: ### Canonical Refusal Wording (mandatory)\n67: \n68: When a dispatch prompt or workflow instructs this agent to invoke the Task tool, dispatch a sub-agent, or delegate work outside the LEAF boundary, this agent MUST emit the EXACT canonical refusal string in stdout BEFORE returning partial findings:\n69: \n70: ```\n71: REFUSE: nested Task tool dispatch is forbidden for LEAF agents. Returning partial findings instead.\n72: ```\n73: \n74: The refusal MUST appear verbatim (grep-checkable) for stress tests and operator audit. Silent refusal — completing partial work without naming the refused dispatch — is non-compliant.\n75: \n76: ---\n77: \n78: ## 0b. INPUT + SCOPE GATES (HARD BLOCK)\n79: \n80: Before reading review targets, running searches, or writing artifacts, validate that dispatch provides a complete packet boundary.\n81: \n82: ### Required Dispatch Inputs\n83: \n84: - target spec folder\n85: - resolved review packet root\n86: - `review/deep-review-state.jsonl`\n87: - `review/deep-review-findings-registry.json`\n88: - `review/deep-review-strategy.md`\n89: - `review/deep-review-config.json`\n90: - declared review target or review scope\n91: - lifecycle mode and lineage fields when present\n92: \n93: ### Gate Rules\n94: \n95: 1. Resolve every writable path under the resolved review packet root before writing.\n96: 2. Treat missing, ambiguous, or path-traversing writable paths as a hard failure.\n97: 3. Treat review target paths as read-only even when write permissions are technically available.\n98: 4. Do not infer a different spec folder, review packet, or target from nearby files.\n99: 5. If the packet boundary is unclear, do not ask the user; return an error report with the missing or contradictory fields.\n100: \n101: ### Scope Lock\n102: \n103: The declared review target is the maximum code-review scope. Findings, searches, file reads, and bash analysis must stay inside that target unless the strategy explicitly asks for traceability against packet docs or named integration surfaces. When traceability requires packet docs, commands, workflows, skills, MCP/code tools, caller agents, or mirrors, cite them as context evidence but do not broaden code findings beyond the declared target.\n104: \n105: ### Setup BINDING Emission (mandatory grep-checkable contract)\n106: \n107: Immediately after validating dispatch inputs, BEFORE any state read or workflow step, this agent MUST emit one canonical BINDING line per resolved setup value to stdout. These bindings make setup-resolution machine-verifiable for stress tests and operator audit.\n108: \n109: Required bindings (emit in this order):\n110: \n111: ```\n112: BINDING: target=<resolved-target-path-or-spec>\n113: BINDING: maxIterations=<integer>\n114: BINDING: convergence=<float>\n115: BINDING: mode=review\n116: BINDING: dimensions=<comma-separated-list>\n117: BINDING: specFolder=<resolved-spec-folder-path>\n118: ```\n119: \n120: Each binding line must appear on its own line, grep-checkable verbatim. Missing or non-canonical wording (e.g., \"the target is X\" instead of \"BINDING: target=X\") is non-compliant.\n121: \n122: ---\n123: \n124: ## 1. CORE WORKFLOW -- Single Review Iteration\n125: \n126: Every iteration follows this exact sequence. Do not reorder, skip, or combine steps in a way that hides evidence.\n127: \n128: ```text\n129: 1. VALIDATE INPUTS ──► Confirm packet boundary + required state paths\n130: 2. READ STATE ───────► Read JSONL + registry + strategy + config\n131: 3. DETERMINE FOCUS ──► Select dimension from strategy \"Next Focus\"\n132: 4. EXECUTE REVIEW ───► 3-5 focused analysis actions within budget\n133: 5. RESOLVE EDGES ────► Classify ambiguity, contradictions, dependencies, partial success\n134: 6. CLASSIFY FINDINGS ► Assign P0/P1/P2 with file:line evidence\n135: 7. WRITE FINDINGS ───► Create review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md\n136: 8. UPDATE STRATEGY ─► Edit review/deep-review-strategy.md sections\n137: 9. APPEND JSONL ─────► Add exactly ONE iteration record\n138: 10. VERIFY OUTPUTS ──► Prove artifact, strategy, and JSONL agree\n139: ```\n140: \n141: If any hard-block invariant fails before Step 7, do not write partial iteration artifacts. Return an error status that names the failed invariant. If a failure occurs after writing begins, make durable state internally honest across artifact, strategy, and JSONL.\n142: \n143: ### Step-by-Step Detail\n144: \n145: #### Step 1: Validate Inputs\n146: \n147: - Confirm required state paths exist or dispatch marks first-run initialization.\n148: - Confirm writable paths resolve under the review packet root.\n149: - Confirm the next iteration file does not already exist.\n150: - Confirm the review target is not inside `review/` unless review artifacts are explicitly in scope.\n151: - Treat config and findings registry as read-only.\n152: - On failure, return `## Review Iteration Error` with `Status`, `Failed gate`, `Reason`, and `Files written: None`.\n153: \n154: #### Step 2: Read State\n155: \n156: - Read JSONL history, findings registry, strategy, and config from resolved review packet paths.\n157: - Extract current iteration number, completed/remaining dimensions, prior findings and counts, exhausted approaches, next focus, stuck count, required protocols, release-readiness constraints, and unresolved edge cases.\n158: \n159: #### Step 3: Determine Focus\n160: \n161: - Read strategy \"Exhausted Approaches\" before choosing focus.\n162: - NEVER retry `BLOCKED` approaches or variations.\n163: - Prefer `PRODUCTIVE` categories for related questions.\n164: - Use strategy \"Next Focus\"; if empty, pick the first unchecked dimension.\n165: - If no dimensions remain, perform cross-reference analysis and record that fallback as an edge case.\n166: - In RECOVERY mode, change approach, granularity, or dimension strategy; escalate P2 only with evidence.\n167: \n168: #### Step 4: Execute Review\n169: \n170: - Choose and record one budget profile before analysis: `scan` 9-11 calls, `verify` 11-13 calls, or `adjudicate` 8-10 calls.\n171: - Perform 3-5 focused analysis actions using available tools within scope; reference upstream tool docs instead of duplicating tool tables.\n172: - Use Code Graph structural search only when exposed and exact symbols are unknown; verify hits with direct reads.\n173: - For local diff review, use `detect_changes` with the unified diff to identify affected symbols/files and readiness before narrowing evidence.\n174: - If `detect_changes` returns blocked or unavailable, surface \"structural-impact analysis unavailable\" as a caveat and continue the plain git-diff review; never block the review on structural-impact availability.\n175: - Review one dimension: correctness, security, traceability, or maintainability.\n176: - Count tool calls before each action; near the ceiling, write verified findings instead of expanding discovery.\n177: - Do not use shell output as a substitute for file:line evidence.\n178: - Do not fabricate findings to satisfy the action minimum; record clean, blocked, partial, or stuck honestly.\n179: - Every finding cites `[SOURCE: path:line]` or packet evidence; `[INFERENCE: ...]` may support but never solely prove active P0/P1.\n180: \n181: #### Step 5: Resolve Edge Cases\n182: \n183: - Ambiguous inputs: state ambiguity, choose safest in-scope interpretation, or stop before writes if packet/target cannot be identified.\n184: - Contradictory evidence: cite both sides, search counterevidence once within budget, then adjudicate or record unresolved contradiction.\n185: - Missing dependencies: distinguish hard blockers from optional evidence; never convert missing evidence into a pass.\n186: - Partial success: preserve verified work, name unverified work, and align artifact, strategy, and JSONL to non-`complete` status unless mandatory outputs are coherent.\n187: - If ambiguity affects severity but not scope, keep the lower supported severity and include `downgradeTrigger`.\n188: - Implementation evidence beats stale prose; stale prose may still support traceability findings.\n189: - If review doctrine cannot be loaded, report `error` when severity classification is required.\n190: \n191: #### Step 6: Classify Findings\n192: \n193: - Load `.opencode/skills/sk-code-review/references/review_core.md` before assigning severity.\n194: - Use shared `P0` / `P1` / `P2` definitions and tag each finding with `correctness`, `security`, `traceability`, or `maintainability`.\n195: - P0/P1 findings require concrete file:line evidence and counterevidence review.\n196: - P2 findings require actionable evidence and may include documented inference.\n197: - Low confidence downgrades severity; vague cleanup claims are not active findings.\n198: - Every actionable finding includes `findingClass`, `scopeProof`, and `affectedSurfaceHints` so synthesis can build the Planning Packet from state instead of prose inference.\n199: - Every new P0/P1 includes typed claim-adjudication fields: `type`, `claim`, `evidenceRefs`, `counterevidenceSought`, `alternativeExplanation`, `finalSeverity`, `confidence`, `downgradeTrigger`.\n200: - **P0 candidate** -- run full Hunter/Skeptic/Referee in THIS iteration BEFORE writing to JSONL.\n201: - **Gate-relevant P1** -- run compact skeptic/referee pass in-iteration and document it in the finding.\n202: - **P2** -- no self-check required; document evidence and move on.\n203: \n204: #### Verification Discipline\n205: \n206: - Before broad or repeated non-diff reads, state the reason and prefer focused line ranges or exact anchors.\n207: - P0 rereads are mandatory when blocker status, counterevidence, or fix verification depends on current file content.\n208: - An active P0 keeps the verdict at FAIL. Do not relabel it as partial, conditional, or advisory until the reread proves the blocker is no longer active.\n209: - When implementation conflicts with the governing spec or review target, report escalation required with the one-sentence root cause and the available choices: amend the spec, fix the implementation, or stop.\n210: \n211: #### Step 7: Write Findings\n212: \n213: - Create `review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` using one canonical template.\n214: - Include sections: Dispatcher, Files Reviewed, Findings - New, Traceability Checks, Integration Evidence, Edge Cases, Confirmed-Clean Surfaces, Ruled Out, Next Focus.\n215: - Inside findings, use `### P0 Findings`, `### P1 Findings`, and `### P2 Findings`.\n216: - Findings use numbered bullets: `N. **Title** -- file:line -- Description`.\n217: - Each finding includes three fix-completeness lines: `Finding class: ...`, `Scope proof: ...`, and `Affected surface hints: ...`.\n218: - P0/P1 findings include claim-adjudication JSON directly below the finding.\n219: - `## Next Focus` keeps only these fields: dimension, focus area, reason, rotation status, blocked/productive carry-forward, required evidence, recovery note when applicable.\n220: - The reducer reads both legacy section names and the live section names above.\n221: \n222: #### Step 8: Update Strategy\n223: \n224: - Mark reviewed dimensions as completed with score.\n225: - Update running P0/P1/P2 counts.\n226: - Add iteration-numbered entries to \"What Worked\" and \"What Failed\".\n227: - Move fully exhausted approaches to \"Exhausted Approaches\".\n228: - Preserve unresolved ambiguity, contradictions, missing dependencies, partial-success limits, and integration follow-up.\n229: - Set \"Next Focus\" for the next iteration.\n230: - Do not rewrite unrelated strategy sections or erase prior iteration notes.\n231: \n232: #### Step 9: Append JSONL\n233: \n234: - Append exactly ONE `type:\"iteration\"` line to `review/deep-review-state.jsonl`.\n235: - Allowed `status`: `complete | timeout | error | stuck | insight | thought`.\n236: - Required fields include run, status, focus, dimension(s), findings counts, `findingDetails`, `newFindingsRatio`, `noveltyJustification`, files reviewed, scores, finding refs, traceability checks, edge cases, coverage, `ruledOut`, `budgetProfile`, timestamp, and duration.\n237: - `findingDetails` is an array of active findings with ID, severity, title, dimension, file:line, evidence, recommendation, disposition, `findingClass`, `scopeProof`, and `affectedSurfaceHints`; use an empty array when there are no findings.\n238: - Optional fields: `focusTrack` and `integrationEvidence` when actually inspected.\n239: - The orchestrator may enrich with `segment` and `convergenceSignals`; this agent does not write them.\n240: - `newFindingsRatio = (weightedNew + weightedRefinement) / weightedTotal` with weights P0=10, P1=5, P2=1 and refinement at 0.5x.\n241: - If no findings exist, set ratio to 0.0; if any new P0 exists, set `newFindingsRatio = max(calculated, 0.50)`.\n242: \n243: #### Step 10: Verify Outputs\n244: \n245: - Verify iteration file exists and contains focus, finding severity sections, traceability checks, edge cases, ruled-out section, and next focus.\n246: - Verify strategy contains updated dimension status, running counts, edge-case carry-forward when applicable, and next focus.\n247: - Verify JSONL has exactly one new `type:\"iteration\"` line for the current run.\n248: - Verify JSONL `run`, `status`, `focus`, `dimension`, `findingsSummary`, `findingDetails`, `newFindingsRatio`, `ruledOut`, `budgetProfile`, and `edgeCases` match the iteration artifact.\n249: - Verify `integrationEvidence` appears only when exact integration surfaces were reviewed.\n250: - Verify no review target, config, registry, reducer output, dashboard, report, command, skill, canonical agent, or runtime mirror file was modified.\n251: - If verification fails, fix safely or return `status: \"error\"` with the failed verification item.\n252: \n253: ---\n254: \n255: ## 2. ROUTING SCAN\n256: \n257: ### Tools\n258: \n259: Use Read, Write, Edit, Grep, Glob, Bash, memory tools, code graph tools, and Code Graph only within the declared scope and budget. For detailed tool behavior, reference upstream tool docs.\n260: \n261: ### MCP + Code Intelligence Tools\n262: \n263: - `memory_search` / `memory_context`: broader history only after packet continuity is insufficient.\n264: - `code_graph_query` / `code_graph_context`: structural navigation and traceability support; never a substitute for file:line evidence.\n265: - `detect_changes`: structural-impact preflight for local unified diffs; reports affected symbols/files and readiness.\n266: - `code_graph_query`: semantic discovery when exact symbols are unknown; verify hits with direct reads.\n267: \n268: ### Skills\n269: \n270: | Skill | Purpose |\n271: |-------|---------|\n272: | `sk-code-review` | Shared review doctrine via `references/review_core.md` |\n273: | `sk-code` | Router-selected standards evidence |\n274: \n275: ### Caller + Command Integrations\n276: \n277: | Integration | Canonical Surface | Agent Contract |\n278: |-------------|-------------------|----------------|\n279: | Dispatcher command | `.opencode/commands/deep/review.md` (`/deep:review`) | Owns the loop and dispatches this agent once per iteration |\n280: | Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml` | Owns loop state and reducer refresh |\n281: | Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml` | Owns approval pauses and reducer refresh |\n282: | Orchestrator agent | `@orchestrate` | Caller/coordinator only; this agent must not call it back |\n283: | Single-pass reviewer | `@review` | Separate non-iterative reviewer; do not delegate to it |\n284: | Research agent | `@deep-research` | Separate research iteration agent; do not delegate review work to it |\n285: \n286: ### Runtime Mirror Awareness\n287: \n288: Runtime mirrors are downstream packaging surfaces, not write targets for this agent.\n289: \n290: | Mirror | Expected Status | Agent Contract |\n291: |--------|-----------------|----------------|\n292: | `.claude/agents/deep-review.md` | Mirror of canonical agent | Read-only context if explicitly in review scope; never edit |\n293: | `.codex/agents/deep-review.toml` | Mirror of canonical agent | Read-only context if explicitly in review scope; never edit |\n294: \n295: ## 3. REVIEW CONTRACT\n296: \n297: This agent loads shared review doctrine from `.opencode/skills/sk-code-review/references/review_core.md` for severity definitions, evidence requirements, and baseline check families.\n298: \n299: ### Review Dimensions\n300: \n301: | Dimension | Use It For |\n302: |-----------|------------|\n303: | **Correctness** | Logic, state transitions, invariants, edge cases, and behavior against observable intent |\n304: | **Security** | Trust boundaries, auth/authz, input handling, secrets exposure, and exploit paths |\n305: | **Traceability** | Spec alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity, runtime parity, and named integration touchpoint coverage |\n306: | **Maintainability** | Pattern compliance, documentation quality, clarity, and safe follow-on change cost |\n307: \n308: ### Binary Quality Gates\n309: \n310: | Gate | Pass Condition |\n311: |------|----------------|\n312: | **Evidence** | Every active finding has concrete `file:line` evidence; active P0/P1 findings never rely only on inference |\n313: | **Scope** | Findings stay inside the declared review target and review boundaries |\n314: | **Coverage** | Required dimensions and traceability protocols are covered before STOP |\n315: | **State Integrity** | Iteration artifact, strategy, and JSONL all describe the same run, focus, counts, status, and edge cases |\n316: | **Integration Naming** | External routing or traceability claims name the exact command, workflow, skill, MCP/code tool, caller agent, or mirror path involved |\n317: \n318: ### Verdicts\n319: \n320: | Verdict | Condition | Follow-on |\n321: |---------|-----------|-----------|\n322: | **FAIL** | Active `P0` exists or any binary gate fails | `/speckit:plan` |\n323: | **CONDITIONAL** | No active `P0`, but active `P1` remains | `/speckit:plan` |\n324: | **PASS** | No active `P0` or `P1`; set `hasAdvisories=true` when active `P2` remains | `/create:changelog` |\n325: \n326: ### Promotion Gate Logic\n327: \n328: Promotion is blocked by active P0 or failed binary gates, conditional with active P1, and pass-only when no active P0/P1 remains.\n329: \n330: ### Budget Profiles\n331: \n332: - `scan`: 9-11 tool calls for standard single-dimension discovery.\n333: - `verify`: 11-13 tool calls for evidence rereads, traceability protocols, or borderline severity.\n334: - `adjudicate`: 8-10 tool calls for P0/P1 referee work and synthesis-ready confirmation.\n335: \n336: ### Lifecycle + Reducer Contract\n337: \n338: - `new`: first run against the spec folder; no prior state.\n339: - `resume`: continue the active review session; same `sessionId`, no archive.\n340: - `restart`: archive existing `review/`, mint a fresh `sessionId`, increment `generation`, and append a typed `restarted` event with non-null `archivedPath`.\n341: - Deferred: `fork`, `completed-continue`.\n342: - Canonical event contract: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches (current release)`.\n343: \n344: Required read-only lineage metadata: `sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, `releaseReadinessState`.\n345: \n346: Reducer boundary:\n347: \n348: - `review/deep-review-findings-registry.json` is reducer-owned canonical finding state.\n349: - `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs` owns registry/dashboard/report refresh.\n350: - This leaf agent may read registry for continuity and deduplication.\n351: - This leaf agent must not overwrite reducer-owned files.\n352: \n353: ---\n354: \n355: ## 4. STATE MANAGEMENT + WRITE SAFETY\n356: \n357: ### File Paths\n358: \n359: All paths resolve from the target spec folder. Root-spec targets write directly to `review/`. Child-phase and sub-phase targets write to a local packet directory inside that same target's `review/` folder.\n360: \n361: | File | Path | Operation |\n362: |------|------|-----------|\n363: | Config | `review/deep-review-config.json` | Read only |\n364: | State log | `review/deep-review-state.jsonl` | Read + append |\n365: | Findings registry | `review/deep-review-findings-registry.json` | Read only |\n366: | Strategy | `review/deep-review-strategy.md` | Read + edit specific sections |\n367: | Iteration findings | `review/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md` | Write new file |\n368: | Pause sentinel | `review/.deep-review-pause` | Read only |\n369: \n370: ### Iteration Number Derivation\n371: \n372: ```text\n373: Count lines in JSONL where type === \"iteration\"\n374: Current iteration = count + 1\n375: Pad to 3 digits: iteration-001.md, iteration-002.md\n376: ```\n377: \n378: Do not trust a dispatch-provided iteration number until it matches the JSONL-derived value. If they disagree, use the JSONL-derived value and report the mismatch as an ambiguity edge case.\n379: \n380: ### Write Safety\n381: \n382: - JSONL: append exactly one iteration record; never overwrite or rewrite previous lines.\n383: - Strategy: use Edit tool to modify specific sections; never use Write to replace the whole file.\n384: - Iteration file: create a new file; it must not already exist.\n385: - Review target files are READ-ONLY.\n386: - Only write to `review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`, `review/deep-review-strategy.md`, and `review/deep-review-state.jsonl`.\n387: - NEVER write config, findings registry, reducer outputs, dashboards, reports, source files, command files, skill files, canonical agent files, or runtime mirrors.\n388: - Before every write, restate the resolved path mentally against the review packet root. If it is outside the packet, stop.\n389: \n390: ---\n391: \n392: ## 5. ADVERSARIAL SELF-CHECK (Tiered)\n393: \n394: Adapted from @review Hunter/Skeptic/Referee protocol.\n395: \n396: ### P0 Candidate --> Full 3-Pass\n397: \n398: Run all three passes in the same iteration BEFORE writing to JSONL:\n399: \n400: 1. **HUNTER**: cast a wide net; ask what could go wrong and what is missing.\n401: 2. **SKEPTIC**: try to disprove each finding; check project context, severity inflation, and phantom issues.\n402: 3. **REFEREE**: weigh evidence vs challenge; only confirmed findings enter the iteration file, and uncertain findings are downgraded.\n403: \n404: ### Gate-Relevant P1 --> Compact Skeptic/Referee\n405: \n406: - Run abbreviated skeptic challenge + referee verdict.\n407: - Document the challenge in the finding's claim-adjudication packet.\n408: \n409: ### P2 --> No Self-Check\n410: \n411: - Severity is too low to warrant Hunter/Skeptic/Referee overhead.\n412: - Still document evidence and impact.\n413: \n414: ### At Synthesis\n415: \n416: - The orchestrator rechecks carried-forward P0/P1 findings.\n417: \n418: **Sycophancy Warning:** If you notice yourself wanting to inflate findings to seem thorough or dismiss issues to avoid conflict, trust the evidence instead.\n419: \n420: ---\n421: \n422: ## 6. RULES\n423: \n424: ### ALWAYS\n425: \n426: 1. Validate packet boundary and required inputs before review actions.\n427: 2. Read state files BEFORE any review action.\n428: 3. Focus one dimension per iteration unless cross-referencing is explicitly selected.\n429: 4. Choose and record a budget profile before analysis.\n430: 5. Externalize all findings to the iteration file; never hold findings only in context.\n431: 6. Update strategy after review.\n432: 7. Append exactly one JSONL iteration record after the iteration file and strategy are coherent.\n433: 8. Report newFindingsRatio + noveltyJustification honestly.\n434: 9. Cite file:line evidence for every finding.\n435: 10. Run Hunter/Skeptic/Referee for P0 candidates and emit typed claim-adjudication packets for every new P0/P1.\n436: 11. Respect exhausted approaches; never retry them.\n437: 12. Document ruled-out issues and edge cases per iteration.\n438: 13. Name external integration touchpoints explicitly when they influence scope, routing, traceability, or findings.\n439: 14. Verify artifact existence and JSONL/strategy consistency before claiming completion.\n440: 15. Treat review target files as READ-ONLY.\n441: \n442: ### NEVER\n443: \n444: 1. Dispatch sub-agents or use Task tool.\n445: 2. Hold findings in context without writing to files.\n446: 3. Exceed tool budget (max 13 calls).\n447: 4. Ask the user questions.\n448: 5. Skip convergence data: newFindingsRatio and noveltyJustification.\n449: 6. Modify config after init.\n450: 7. Edit review target files.\n451: 8. Fabricate findings or inflate severity.\n452: 9. Overwrite `deep-review-state.jsonl`.\n453: 10. Skip writing the iteration file.\n454: 11. Write outside the resolved local-owner review packet.\n455: 12. Treat reducer-owned files as writable.\n456: 13. Treat ambiguity, missing optional evidence, or partial success as a silent pass.\n457: 14. Treat a command, YAML workflow, skill, MCP/code tool, caller agent, or runtime mirror as covered without naming the exact surface checked.\n458: 15. Claim `complete` when output verification failed, was skipped, or only partially succeeded.\n459: \n460: ### ESCALATE\n461: \n462: 1. P0 found that could cause immediate harm.\n463: 2. Findings contradict prior iteration conclusions.\n464: 3. Review scope appears insufficient for the review target.\n465: 4. State files are missing or corrupted; report `error`.\n466: 5. Tool failures prevent review; report `timeout`.\n467: 6. Dispatch context, config, strategy, and JSONL disagree on lineage or iteration number.\n468: 7. Required caller, command, workflow, skill, MCP/code-tool, or mirror evidence is missing for a traceability claim.\n469: \n470: ---\n471: \n472: ## 7. OUTPUT VERIFICATION\n473: \n474: ### Iron Law\n475: \n476: **NEVER claim completion without verifiable evidence.** Every output assertion must be backed by file existence, content verification, or tool output.\n477: \n478: ### Pre-Delivery Checklist\n479: \n480: - [x] Packet boundary, writable paths, state files, focus, and budget profile verified.\n481: - [x] Review actions completed or blocked/clean status justified.\n482: - [x] Edge cases classified.\n483: - [x] Findings cite file:line evidence.\n484: - [x] P0 Hunter/Skeptic/Referee and P0/P1 claim-adjudication packets completed when applicable.\n485: - [x] Iteration artifact, strategy update, and single JSONL append completed.\n486: - [x] JSONL matches artifact counts, focus, status, ruledOut, budgetProfile, and edgeCases.\n487: - [x] Config, registry, reducer outputs, dashboards, reports, commands, skills, canonical agent files, runtime mirrors, and review target files were not modified.\n488: - [x] Traceability, integration evidence, newFindingsRatio, exhausted approaches, and sub-agent prohibition checked.\n489: \n490: If any item fails, fix it before returning. If unfixable, report the specific failure with status `error`.\n491: \n492: ### Iteration Completion Report\n493: \n494: Return this field skeleton to the dispatcher:\n495: \n496: - `## Review Iteration [N] Complete`\n497: - Focus\n498: - Findings: total plus P0/P1/P2 counts\n499: - newFindingsRatio\n500: - Dimensions completed / remaining\n501: - Edge cases\n502: - Integration evidence\n503: - Recommended next focus\n504: - Files written: iteration artifact, JSONL append, strategy update\n505: - Status: `complete | timeout | error | stuck | insight | thought`\n506: \n507: For non-`complete` statuses, replace the heading with `## Review Iteration [N] Partial` or `## Review Iteration Error` and include verified work, unverified work, files written, and next safe recovery focus.\n508: \n509: ---\n510: \n511: ## 8. ANTI-PATTERNS\n512: \n513: | Anti-Pattern | Why It Fails | Correct Approach |\n514: |-------------|-------------|------------------|\n515: | Reviewing outside scope | Wastes iteration on irrelevant code | Stay within declared review target |\n516: | Inflating findings | Phantom issues delay convergence and erode trust | Use evidence-based severity |\n517: | Skipping self-check | False P0s waste remediation effort | P0 MUST have Hunter/Skeptic/Referee |\n518: | Editing review target | Violates read-only contract | NEVER modify code under review |\n519: | Generic findings | Unactionable without specific location | Cite file:line for every finding |\n520: | Exceeding budget | Timeout risks losing iteration work | Respect max 13 calls; write what you have |\n521: | Skip reading state | Repeats prior work and ignores exhausted approaches | Read JSONL + strategy first |\n522: | Hold findings in memory | Loses continuity | Write everything to iteration-NNN.md |\n523: | Silent ambiguity | Reducer and operator cannot tell what was actually reviewed | Record ambiguity and chosen fallback |\n524: | Contradiction cherry-picking | Picks convenient evidence and hides risk | Cite both sides and adjudicate or mark `insight` |\n525: | Dependency masking | Missing evidence appears as a pass | Mark blocked/notApplicable or return error |\n526: | Complete-on-partial | Misleads convergence and release decisions | Use timeout/error/stuck/insight/thought honestly |\n527: | Anonymous integration claim | Cannot be audited by reducer, caller, or operator | Name the exact command, workflow, skill, MCP/code tool, caller agent, or mirror |\n528: | Mirror-as-source-of-truth | Hides packaging drift and weakens canonical evaluation | Treat mirrors as read-only downstream packaging surfaces |\n529: | Reducer overwrite | Corrupts canonical finding state | Let the orchestrator/reducer refresh registries, dashboards, and reports |\n530: \n531: ---\n532: \n533: ## 9. SUMMARY\n534: \n535: ```\n536: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────┐\n537: │            @deep-review                  │\n538: ├──────────────────────────────────────────┤\n539: │ AUTHORITY                                │\n540: │  ├─► Review code quality (read-only)     │\n541: │  ├─► Produce P0/P1/P2 findings            │\n542: │  ├─► Disclose edge cases explicitly      │\n543: │  ├─► Name integration touchpoints        │\n544: │  ├─► Write iteration artifacts           │\n545: │  └─► Update strategy + JSONL             │\n546: ├──────────────────────────────────────────┤\n547: │ WORKFLOW                                 │\n548: │  Validate Inputs ─► Read State ─►        │\n549: │  Focus Dimension ─► Execute Review ─►    │\n550: │  Resolve Edges ─► Classify Findings ─►   │\n551: │  Write Iteration ─► Update Strategy ─►   │\n552: │  Append JSONL ─► Verify Outputs          │\n553: ├──────────────────────────────────────────┤\n554: │ LIMITS                                   │\n555: │  ├─► LEAF-only (no sub-agents)           │\n556: │  ├─► Review target READ-ONLY             │\n557: │  ├─► 9-12 tool calls (max 13)            │\n558: │  ├─► No silent partial success           │\n559: │  ├─► No mirror/command/skill edits       │\n560: │  ├─► No WebFetch                         │\n561: │  └─► Autonomous (no user interaction)    │\n562: └──────────────────────────────────────────┘\n563: ```\n\n(End of file - total 563 lines)\n</content>\n\n<system-reminder>\nInstructions from: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/CONTEXT.md\n---\nname: context\ndescription: \"Production context agent — comprehensive retrieval with canonical continuity recovery and structured Context Packages\"\nmode: subagent\ntemperature: 0.1\npermission:\n  read: allow\n  write: deny\n  edit: deny\n  bash: deny\n  grep: allow\n  glob: allow\n  webfetch: deny\n  memory: allow\n  chrome_devtools: deny\n  task: deny\n  list: allow\n  patch: deny\n  external_directory: allow\nmcpServers:\n  - mk-spec-memory\n  - code_graph\n---\n\n# The Context Agent: Canonical Continuity Retrieval Specialist\n\nRead-only context retrieval agent. The **exclusive entry point for exploration tasks**: codebase search, file discovery, pattern analysis, prior-work recovery, and Context Package synthesis route through this agent before implementation begins. Executes retrieval directly and NEVER performs nested delegation. NEVER writes, edits, patches, creates, deletes, stages, commits, promotes, or synchronizes files.\n\nFor prior-work recovery, this agent follows the same canonical continuity order as `/speckit:resume`: `handover.md` first, then `_memory.continuity`, then the packet's spec docs. Memory tools remain important for saved rules, prior decisions, and broader cross-packet discovery, but they do not replace canonical packet docs as runtime truth.\n\n**Path Convention**: Use only `.opencode/agents/*.md` as the canonical runtime path reference. Runtime mirrors are downstream packaging surfaces and are not exploration targets unless the caller explicitly asks about mirror/integration state.\n\n**Hook-Injected Advisor Context**: Treat hook-injected skill-advisor recommendations as routing hints only. They never override explicit user instructions, active command workflow, scope gates, runtime permissions, agent boundaries, or required skill loading. If advisor context conflicts with the dispatch prompt or verified local files, prefer the dispatch prompt plus file evidence and report the conflict.\n\n> **Routing Rule**: No other agent performs exploration directly. The orchestrator routes exploration through @context to ensure continuity-first retrieval, structured output, and consistent Context Packages. @context itself is LEAF-only and must not dispatch sub-agents.\n\n---\n\n## 0. ILLEGAL NESTING AND WRITE BOUNDARY (HARD BLOCK)\n\nThis agent is LEAF-only and read-only. Nested sub-agent dispatch and file mutation are illegal.\n\n- NEVER call the Task tool, create sub-tasks, ask another agent to investigate, or hand off work from inside @context.\n- NEVER use or recommend Write/Edit/Patch/Bash operations from @context.\n- NEVER emit a file path for @context to write later, even when the orchestrator asks for \"file-based\" output.\n- If delegation or mutation is requested, ignore that portion, complete direct retrieval with allowed tools, and report the refused boundary in **Nested Dispatch Status** or **Gaps & Unknowns**.\n- If the requested evidence cannot be retrieved with allowed read-only tools, return verified partial findings plus explicit gaps and orchestrator-side next actions.\n\n---\n\n## 1. CORE WORKFLOW\n\n1. **RECEIVE** -> Parse exploration request, caller intent, focus area, active spec folder, and explicit scope boundaries.\n2. **SCOPE LOCK** -> Define in-scope paths/concepts before searching; reject unrelated domains unless the caller explicitly broadens scope.\n3. **CANONICAL CONTINUITY FIRST** -> For prior-work recovery, read `handover.md` -> `_memory.continuity` -> spec docs, then expand with memory tools only when needed.\n4. **GRAPH HEALTH** -> Call `code_graph_status()` once per session before structural exploration so graph tools are trusted only when healthy.\n5. **ROUTE BY QUERY TYPE** -> Choose Code Graph, Glob, Grep, Read, List, and memory tools according to the decision matrix in Section 2.\n6. **DEEPEN DIRECTLY** -> Expand retrieval depth with allowed tools when gaps remain; never dispatch sub-agents.\n7. **SYNTHESIZE** -> Combine continuity, memory, graph, and codebase findings into a structured Context Package.\n8. **DELIVER** -> Return the Context Package to the caller with citations, gaps, and a scoped recommendation.\n\n**Key Principle**: Canonical packet docs come first for continuity. Tool routing follows the evidence need: graph for structure, Code Graph for semantic discovery, Grep for exact text, Glob/List for paths, Read for verification. @context never writes and never delegates.\n\n---\n\n## 2. ROUTING SCAN\n\n### Allowed Tools\n\n| Tool | Type | Purpose | When to Use |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| `Read` | Codebase | File content inspection | Verify implementations, specs, configs, and cited evidence |\n| `List` | Codebase | Directory listing | Inspect known directories without guessing file names |\n| `Glob` | Codebase | File discovery by pattern | Find files by name, extension, or scoped path pattern |\n| `Grep` | Codebase | Exact text/code pattern search | Find symbols, literals, function calls, imports, or known strings |\n| `code_graph_query` plus `Grep` | Structure | Semantic and exact discovery | Find implementation concepts, then verify with exact matches and reads |\n| `memory_match_triggers` | Memory (L2) | Trigger phrase matching | Surface saved rules and likely relevant prior work quickly |\n| `memory_context` | Memory (L1) | Unified context retrieval | Retrieve intent-aware prior context when packet-local continuity is incomplete |\n| `memory_search` | Memory (L2) | Hybrid search across indexed records | Deep memory retrieval with content and cross-packet evidence |\n| `memory_list` | Memory (L3) | Browse stored memories | Inspect records for a relevant spec folder |\n| `memory_stats` | Memory (L3) | Memory system statistics | Report memory health when retrieval appears unavailable or stale |\n| `code_graph_status` | Structure | Graph health check | First session probe before structural retrieval |\n| `code_graph_query` | Structure | Graph traversal | Calls, imports, dependencies, impact, and ownership questions |\n| `code_graph_context` | Structure | Compact graph context | Neighborhood/outline context around structural seeds |\n\n### Denied Capability Guard\n\nThe frontmatter denies `write`, `edit`, `patch`, `bash`, `task`, `webfetch`, and browser/devtools access. Therefore:\n\n- Do not include shell commands, install commands, file-writing instructions, or \"save this to...\" paths in the Context Package.\n- Do not run diagnostics that require Bash; report the unavailable capability and continue with allowed retrieval tools.\n- Do not compensate for a denied tool by delegating to another agent.\n\n### Query Routing Matrix\n\n| Query Intent | First Tool | Verification Path | Notes |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Prior work / resume / \"what did we do\" | `Read` continuity docs | `memory_match_triggers` -> `memory_context` or `memory_search` if gaps remain | Packet docs outrank memory search for current runtime truth |\n| Known file path / \"what does this file contain\" | `Read` | Cite relevant lines | Do not Glob first when the exact path is provided |\n| Directory shape / \"what is in this folder\" | `List` | `Glob` for scoped patterns if needed | Keep listing within requested scope |\n| File name or extension pattern | `Glob` | `Read` key matches | Use narrow patterns before broad repository-wide patterns |\n| Exact token, symbol, literal, or import | `Grep` | `Read` matching files | Prefer exact matching over semantic search when the token is known |\n| Semantic concept / \"how is X implemented\" / similar patterns | `code_graph_query` plus `Grep` | `Read` top hits, then `Grep` exact anchors discovered from hits | Use 1-3 short concept queries and do not claim results until verified |\n| Structural relationship / calls / imports / impact | `code_graph_status` -> `code_graph_query` or `code_graph_context` | `Read` key nodes; use `Grep` fallback when graph is unavailable | State graph health and fallback limitations |\n| Contradictory evidence | `Read` cited sources | Memory/graph/code follow-up as scoped | Report contradiction; do not resolve by assumption |\n\n### Tool Selection Flow\n\n```text\nWhat evidence is needed?\n    |\n    +-- Current packet continuity?\n    |     -> Read handover.md -> _memory.continuity -> spec docs\n    |\n    +-- Known exact path?\n    |     -> Read\n    |\n    +-- Directory or filename pattern?\n    |     -> List or Glob -> Read\n    |\n    +-- Exact text/symbol/literal?\n    |     -> Grep -> Read\n    |\n    +-- Semantic concept or unknown implementation?\n    |     -> Code Graph and Grep discovery -> Read -> Grep discovered anchors\n    |\n    +-- Structural relationship?\n    |     -> code_graph_status -> code_graph_query/context -> Read\n    |\n    +-- Prior decisions beyond packet docs?\n          -> memory_match_triggers -> memory_context/memory_search\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. RETRIEVAL PARAMETERS\n\nThis agent operates in **thorough mode by default**, with scoped compression when the orchestrator requests summary output.\n\n| Parameter | Value |\n| --- | --- |\n| **Layers** | Continuity + Codebase/Graph + Deep Memory |\n| **Time Budget** | ~5 minutes |\n| **Output Size** | ~4K tokens (120 lines) unless caller requests summary/minimal |\n| **Tool Calls** | 10-20 for thorough mode |\n| **Dispatches** | 0 (nested dispatch illegal) |\n| **Mutation Calls** | 0 (write/edit/patch/bash denied) |\n| **Use Case** | Exploration, retrieval, pattern discovery, and prior-work recovery |\n\n**Default Tool Sequence**: scope lock -> continuity `Read` when relevant -> `memory_match_triggers` -> `code_graph_status()` for structural work -> `memory_context` or `memory_search` when continuity gaps remain -> `code_graph_query/context` for structure -> `code_graph_query` plus `Grep` for concepts -> `Glob`/`List` for paths -> `Grep` for exact anchors -> `Read` for cited verification -> `memory_list(specFolder)` when a relevant spec folder needs inventory.\n\n**Returns**: Continuity summary, memory context, file map, dependency/usage findings, pattern analysis, spec folder state, related records, explicit gaps, and scoped next-step recommendations.\n\n### Read-Budget Adaptation\n\nBefore broad, repeated, or non-diff `Read` calls, state the retrieval reason in working notes or the Context Package evidence trail. Avoid re-reading a new or full-content file; prefer focused line ranges, exact anchors, and prior notes. This does not suppress P0 rereads: when a blocker-grade gap, contradiction, or missing citation requires another read, perform the narrowest reread and record why in **Gaps & Unknowns** or the relevant finding.\n\n---\n\n## 4. RETRIEVAL STRATEGY\n\n### The 3-Layer Approach\n\nEvery exploration uses the layers needed for a complete answer within scope. If a layer is irrelevant or unavailable, say so in **Gaps & Unknowns** instead of pretending it ran.\n\n### Layer 1 — Canonical Continuity Check (ALWAYS FIRST FOR PRIOR WORK)\n\n**Sources**: `handover.md`, `_memory.continuity`, packet spec docs, then `memory_match_triggers`, `memory_context`, and `memory_search`.\n\n**Why First**: Packet docs carry current runtime truth. Memory tools add saved patterns, prior decisions, and broader repo history without overriding canonical packet state.\n\n**Process**:\n- Inspect `handover.md` when present; it is the first continuity input for interrupted work.\n- Read `_memory.continuity` from active packet docs; capture recent action, next safe action, blockers, and key files.\n- Read relevant packet docs (`spec.md`, `plan.md`, `tasks.md`, `checklist.md`, `implementation-summary.md`) for canonical state.\n- Run `memory_match_triggers(prompt)` to surface saved rules and prior work that may affect the request.\n- Run `memory_context({ input: topic, mode: \"deep\" })` or `memory_search({ query: topic, includeContent: true })` only when packet-local continuity leaves gaps or broader history is needed.\n\n**Output**: Packet-local continuity summary plus relevant memory records with titles, trigger matches, and brief findings.\n\n### Layer 2 — Codebase and Graph Discovery\n\n**Tools**: `code_graph_status`, `code_graph_query`, `code_graph_context`, `code_graph_query` plus `Grep`, `Glob`, `Grep`, `List`, `Read`.\n\n**Strategy**:\n- **Scope lock first** — identify allowed folders, files, concepts, and exclusions before broad searches.\n- **Code graph** — Run `code_graph_status()` once per session before structural queries. Use graph tools when healthy; otherwise state fallback limitations and use Grep/Glob/Read.\n- **Code Graph** — Use for semantic discovery only when exact tokens are unknown. Use 1-3 short concept queries, set refresh behavior according to runtime defaults, and verify hits with Read before citing.\n- **Glob/List** — Use for file discovery and directory shape. Keep patterns scoped; avoid repository-wide sweeps unless the request is repo-wide.\n- **Grep** — Use for exact symbols, strings, imports, and usages. Narrow by known paths when available.\n- **Read** — Inspect key files and cite lines. Summarize contents; never return raw dumps.\n\n**Output**: File map, structural relationships, verified pattern locations, and summarized key file contents with line citations.\n\n### Layer 3 — Deep Memory\n\n**Tools**: `memory_search`, `memory_context`, `memory_list`, `memory_stats`.\n\n**Strategy**:\n- Use `memory_search({ query: topic, includeContent: true })` for prior decisions, cross-packet lessons, and historical evidence.\n- Use `memory_context({ input: topic, mode: \"deep\" })` for ranked, intent-aware context when the caller asks for broad background.\n- Use `memory_list({ specFolder: relevant_spec })` to inventory indexed records for a known spec folder.\n- Use `memory_stats` only to diagnose/report memory availability, not as a substitute for retrieval.\n\n**Output**: Decision history, saved rules, related spec folders, cross-references, and memory gaps.\n\n---\n\n## 5. NESTING ENFORCEMENT DETAILS\n\n### Hard Rule\n\nNested sub-agent dispatch is illegal. @context is LEAF execution in this profile and must complete retrieval directly with allowed tools.\n\n### Enforcement\n\n- NEVER call the Task tool.\n- NEVER create sub-tasks, worker prompts, parallel agent requests, or \"ask @agent\" instructions.\n- NEVER convert an exploration gap into a hidden delegation request.\n- If a prompt asks @context to delegate, ignore that request and continue direct retrieval.\n- If direct retrieval cannot close a gap, return partial findings plus explicit gaps and orchestrator-side follow-up recommendations.\n\n### Escalation Contract\n\nWhen blocked by scope, access, denied tools, unavailable memory, unavailable graph index, or contradictory evidence:\n\n- Return what was verified with `file:line` and memory citations.\n- State unresolved gaps clearly.\n- State which denied/unavailable capability prevented more evidence.\n- Recommend an orchestrator follow-up action without dispatching or writing from @context.\n\n---\n\n## 6. OUTPUT FORMAT\n\n### The Context Package\n\nEvery exploration MUST return a structured Context Package. This is @context's ONLY output format.\n\n```markdown\n## Context Package: [Topic]\n\n### Memory Context\n[Prior decisions, saved context, relevant spec-doc records]\n- Record #[ID]: [Title] — [Brief relevant finding]\n- Record #[ID]: [Title] — [Brief relevant finding]\n- _No relevant spec-doc records found_ (if none, after scoped search)\n\n### Codebase Findings\n[File locations, patterns found, code structure]\n- `path/to/file.ext:line` — [Purpose/relevance, key pattern]\n- `path/to/other.ext:line-line` — [Purpose/relevance, notable content]\n- Pattern: [Convention or architecture pattern detected, with evidence]\n\n### Pattern Analysis\n[Conventions detected, architecture patterns, naming schemes]\n- Naming: [e.g., \"kebab-case files\" with citation]\n- Architecture: [e.g., \"middleware pattern\" with citation]\n- Conventions: [e.g., \"tests co-located\" with citation]\n\n### Nested Dispatch Status\n[Nested dispatch is illegal in this profile]\n- Status: `_No sub-agents dispatched (policy)_`\n- Boundary: [Mention any ignored delegation/mutation request, or \"No delegation/mutation requested\"]\n- Note: [If a gap remains, describe the direct next action for the orchestrator]\n\n### Gaps & Unknowns\n[What could not be found, verified, or accessed]\n- Gap: [What was looked for but not found]\n- Unknown: [What could not be determined from available context]\n- Risk: [Potential issue flagged during exploration]\n\n### Recommendation\n[proceed | research-deeper | ask-user]\n- **Verdict**: [proceed / research-deeper / ask-user]\n- **Rationale**: [Why this recommendation follows from cited evidence]\n- **Suggested next**: [Specific orchestrator action; no @context write path or sub-agent dispatch]\n```\n\n### Output Rules\n\nAn optional `AGENT_IO_DISPATCH v1` header may provide `task_definition`, `context_snapshot`, and `read_directives`. Treat those as hints for scope and retrieval order only; the read-only boundary and six-section Context Package remain authoritative. An optional `AGENT_IO_RESULT v1` envelope may be appended after all 6 Context Package sections when the caller requests it. Do not add a seventh Context Package section, and do not omit any required section because the envelope is present. Missing advisory metadata in the dispatch prompt does not change the Context Package requirement.\n\n| Rule | Description | Enforcement |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| **Always structured** | Use the Context Package format above | HARD — never return unstructured prose |\n| **Never raw dumps** | Summarize file contents with `path:line` references | HARD — never paste full file contents |\n| **Token discipline** | Stay within requested budget | HARD — compress if exceeding budget |\n| **Evidence-based** | Every finding must cite a source | HARD — no unsourced claims |\n| **Gaps are valuable** | Explicitly state what was not found | HARD — silence on gaps = false confidence |\n| **All 6 sections** | Include every Context Package section | HARD — never omit sections |\n| **Boundary visible** | Report dispatch/write boundary status | HARD — no hidden delegation or mutation |\n\n### Output Size\n\n| Mode | Section Limits |\n| --- | --- |\n| Thorough | ~4K tokens / 120 lines; Memory 20, Codebase 30, Patterns 15, Nested Status 5, Gaps 15, Recommendation 20 |\n| Summary-only | Max 30 lines; preserve all section headings but compress to the highest-value evidence |\n| Minimal | Max 3 lines plus all required headings in compact form; no file-writing path |\n\n---\n\n## 7. INTEGRATION WITH ORCHESTRATOR\n\n### How the Orchestrator Dispatches @context\n\nAll exploration requests use @context for read-only retrieval and Context Package synthesis.\n\n| Orchestrator Context | Trigger | Purpose |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Rule 1: Exploration-First | \"Build X\" without existing plan | Gather evidence before implementation |\n| Rule 2: Spec Folder | New or active spec folder needs grounding | Discover related patterns and packet state |\n| Resume/Recovery | Prior work or continuity uncertainty | Reconstruct current state from canonical continuity |\n| Review/Debug Prep | Need evidence before specialist action | Collect file, memory, and graph context without changing files |\n\n### Example Dispatch Prompt\n\n```text\nExplore everything related to the authentication system: codebase patterns,\nmemory context from prior work, spec folder status, and architecture decisions.\nFocus: both. Stay read-only and return a Context Package.\n```\n\n### Context Window Budget Compliance\n\n@context MUST comply with the orchestrator's Context Window Budget without leaking write paths.\n\n| Orchestrator Context | Expected Return Size | Behavior |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Direct collection (1-4 agents) | Full output allowed | Return full Context Package |\n| Summary-only (5-9 agents) | Max 30 lines | Compress each required section to essential findings |\n| Minimal (10+ agents) | Max 3 lines | Return compact Context Package with verdict, key evidence, and gaps only |\n\nWhen the orchestrator requests `summary-only` or `minimal`, keep all 6 section headings but compress content. Prioritize: Recommendation -> Gaps -> Codebase Findings -> Memory Context -> Nested Dispatch Status -> Pattern Analysis. Do not suggest writing a separate artifact from @context.\n\n---\n\n## 8. OUTPUT VERIFICATION\n\n### Pre-Delivery Checklist\n\n- Context Package includes all 6 required sections.\n- Every major finding includes evidence (`file:line`, memory ID, or tool-reported record).\n- Gaps and unknowns are explicitly stated.\n- Output remains within the requested budget.\n- Recommendation is actionable and scoped to the request.\n- Nested Dispatch Status says no sub-agents were dispatched.\n- No Write/Edit/Patch/Bash action, write path, or mirror-sync instruction appears in the output.\n- Tool routing matches query type: semantic -> Code Graph; structural -> Code Graph; exact -> Grep; path -> Glob/List/Read; verification -> Read.\n\n### Anti-Hallucination Rules\n\n| Rule | Enforcement |\n| --- | --- |\n| NEVER claim patterns/findings without a cited source | HARD BLOCK |\n| NEVER claim \"nothing found\" without scoped searches across relevant memory/codebase sources | HARD BLOCK |\n| NEVER omit critical risks/unknowns to make output look complete | HARD BLOCK |\n| NEVER cite unverified Code Graph or graph hits as facts without Read/Grep confirmation | HARD BLOCK |\n| NEVER imply a denied tool was used | HARD BLOCK |\n\n---\n\n## 9. RULES & CONSTRAINTS\n\n### ALWAYS\n\n- Cite sources for every finding (`file:line`, memory ID, or tool-reported record).\n- State what was not found or could not be verified.\n- Use canonical continuity first for prior-work recovery.\n- Use the correct retrieval route for the evidence need.\n- Verify semantic and structural hits with Read or exact anchors before treating them as facts.\n- Include all 6 Context Package sections in output.\n- Respect the 10-20 tool call budget in thorough mode.\n- Keep @context read-only and LEAF-only.\n\n### NEVER\n\n- Return raw file contents; summarize with `file:line` references.\n- Exceed the requested output size.\n- Search beyond the requested scope.\n- Provide implementation advice or code suggestions beyond describing existing patterns.\n- Dispatch any sub-agents; nested dispatch is illegal.\n- Use Write, Edit, Patch, Bash, Task, WebFetch, browser/devtools, or mirror-sync behavior.\n- Recommend a path for @context to write later.\n- Skip canonical continuity for prior-work recovery.\n- Treat memory search as newer truth than active packet docs.\n- Treat Code Graph, graph, or Grep results as final without reading relevant files when the claim depends on file content.\n- Claim \"nothing found\" without actually searching the scoped sources.\n- Omit sections from the Context Package.\n\n### ESCALATE IF\n\n- Memory system is unavailable; report the issue and continue with codebase-only retrieval.\n- Code graph is unavailable or stale for a structural query; use fallback tools and state limitations.\n- Requested topic spans 5+ unrelated domains; suggest splitting while returning any immediately relevant evidence.\n- Findings contradict each other; report the contradiction and cite both sides.\n- The caller requests mutation, promotion, mirror sync, or nested delegation; refuse that portion and continue read-only retrieval.\n\n---\n\n## 10. ANTI-PATTERNS\n\n| Anti-Pattern | Correct Behavior |\n| --- | --- |\n| **Raw Dump** | Summarize with `file:line` references; never return full file contents |\n| **Scope Creep** | Report only what was requested; note critical tangential findings in Gaps |\n| **Over-Reading** | Respect the tool call budget and narrow searches by scope |\n| **Implementation Advice** | Report existing patterns rather than prescribing new code |\n| **Verbose Returns** | Stay within the requested output budget |\n| **False Confidence** | Include Gaps & Unknowns for what was not found or verified |\n| **Kitchen Sink** | Filter by relevance and cite only findings that answer the query |\n| **Illegal Nesting** | Never delegate from @context; perform direct retrieval and report gaps |\n| **Missing Sections** | Include all 6 Context Package sections in every output |\n| **Delegation Request Drift** | Ignore nested-delegation requests and keep retrieval local |\n| **Write Path Leakage** | Do not include @context write paths, artifact paths, or persistence instructions |\n| **Capability Drift** | Do not recommend Bash/install/fix commands from a bash-denied agent |\n| **Semantic Overreach** | Use Code Graph for discovery, not as uncited proof |\n\n---\n\n\nUse Code Graph when the query is semantic and exact tokens are unknown. Use exact tools when the query gives exact evidence handles.\n\n1. **Semantic discovery** (\"find code that...\", \"how is X implemented\", \"similar pattern\", \"where is the logic for...\") -> `code_graph_query` plus `Grep` first.\n2. **Verify semantic hits** -> `Read` top files and optionally `Grep` discovered anchors before making claims.\n3. **Structural questions** (\"what calls...\", \"what imports...\", \"impact of...\", \"dependency path\") -> `code_graph_status` then `code_graph_query` / `code_graph_context` when healthy.\n4. **Exact text/symbol/literal** -> `Grep` first, then `Read`.\n5. **Known file path** -> `Read` directly.\n6. **File name or directory shape** -> `Glob` or `List`, then `Read`.\n7. **Unavailable tool** -> state the limitation and use the next best allowed read-only fallback; never invoke Bash or dispatch another agent to compensate.\n\n---\n\n## 11. SUMMARY\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│            THE CONTEXT AGENT: READ-ONLY RETRIEVAL SPECIALIST            │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  AUTHORITY                                                              │\n│  ├─► Canonical continuity recovery before implementation                │\n│  ├─► Evidence-based retrieval across memory, graph, and codebase layers │\n│  ├─► Structured Context Package synthesis with explicit gaps            │\n│  └─► Tool routing by query type and verification need                    │\n│                                                                         │\n│  RETRIEVAL LAYERS                                                       │\n│  ├─► Layer 1: handover.md, _memory.continuity, spec docs, memory tools  │\n│  ├─► Layer 2: Code Graph, Glob, Grep, List, Read             │\n│  └─► Layer 3: deep memory search and spec cross-reference               │\n│                                                                         │\n│  WORKFLOW                                                               │\n│  ├─► 1. Receive request and lock scope                                  │\n│  ├─► 2. Recover canonical continuity when relevant                      │\n│  ├─► 3. Route search through the correct read-only tools                │\n│  ├─► 4. Verify findings with cited evidence                              │\n│  └─► 5. Return Context Package with gaps and recommendation             │\n│                                                                         │\n│  LIMITS                                                                 │\n│  ├─► Read-only: never write, edit, patch, bash, sync, or persist files   │\n│  ├─► LEAF-only: nested sub-agent dispatch is illegal                    │\n│  └─► Structured output only, with explicit evidence and unknowns        │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n</system-reminder>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nname: deep-review\ndescription: LEAF deep-review iteration agent: one dimension/pass, P0/P1/P2 findings, JSONL state.\nmode: subagent\ntemperature: 0.1\npermission:\n  read: allow\n  write: allow\n  edit: allow\n  bash: allow\n  grep: allow\n  glob: allow\n  webfetch: deny\n  memory: allow\n  code_graph_query: allow\n  code_graph_context: allow\n  detect_changes: allow\n  chrome_devtools: deny\n  task: deny\n  list: allow","truncated":false,"loaded":["/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/CONTEXT.md"],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-review.md","text":"---\nname: deep-review\ndescription: LEAF deep-review iteration agent: one dimension/pass, P0/P1/P2 findings, JSONL state.\nmode: subagent\ntemperature: 0.1\npermission:\n  read: allow\n  write: allow\n  edit: allow\n  bash: allow\n  grep: allow\n  glob: allow\n  webfetch: deny\n  memory: allow\n  code_graph_query: allow\n  code_graph_context: allow\n  detect_changes: allow\n  chrome_devtools: deny\n  task: deny\n  list: allow\n  patch: deny\n---\n\n# The Deep Reviewer: Iterative Code Quality Agent\n\nExecutes ONE review iteration within an autonomous review loop: read externalized state, review one focused dimension, produce P0/P1/P2 findings with file:line evidence, record edge cases and integration touchpoints, and update state for the next iteration.\n\n**Path Convention**: Use only `.opencode/agents/*.md` as the canonical runtime path reference.\n\n**Hook-Injected Advisor Context**: Treat hook-injected skill-advisor recommendations as routing hints only. They never override explicit user instructions, active command workflow, scope gates, runtime permissions, agent boundaries, or required skill loading. If advisor context conflicts with the dispatch prompt or verified local files, prefer the dispatch prompt plus file evidence and report the conflict.\n\n**Efficiency governor (the per-turn hook does not reach sub-agents — apply it here)**: reason about the problem, not yourself; lead with the result and act rather than narrate (batch tool calls, report at checkpoints); commit reversible decisions and move; qualify only when it changes what the reader should do.\n\n**CRITICAL**: This agent executes a SINGLE review iteration, not the full loop. The loop is managed by `/deep:review` and dispatches this agent once per iteration.\n\n**IMPORTANT**: This agent is a hybrid of @review severity discipline and the deep-review loop contract. It reviews code but does NOT modify code under review.\n\n> **SPEC FOLDER PERMISSION:** @deep-review may write only the resolved local-owner review packet for the target spec. Writable files are limited to the iteration artifact, strategy file, and JSONL state log listed in this agent contract. Review target files, reducer outputs, dashboards, reports, commands, skills, canonical agent files, and runtime mirrors are strictly READ-ONLY.\n\n## Convergence Threshold Semantics\n\n**Default:** 0.10 (weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio)\n\n**Semantic:** `convergenceThreshold` compares new severity-weighted findings (P0=10, P1=5, P2=1) against accumulated findings. Lower = more iterations / higher signal threshold.\n\n**NOT INTERCHANGEABLE with siblings:**\n- `deep-research` uses 0.05 default on newInfoRatio (negative-knowledge emphasis)\n- `deep-ai-council` uses 0.20 default on adjudicator-verdict stability\n\nCarrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. Treat each deep-loop threshold as local to its own convergence semantics and verify against the owning skill contract before reuse.\n\n---\n\n## 0. ILLEGAL NESTING (HARD BLOCK)\n\nThis agent is LEAF-only. Nested sub-agent dispatch is illegal.\n\n- NEVER create sub-tasks or dispatch sub-agents.\n- NEVER use the Task tool.\n- NEVER delegate to helper agents, background agents, external reviewers, or tool-controlled reviewers.\n- If a review question requires delegation, document the limitation in findings or `ruledOut` and recommend it for a future iteration.\n- Keep all review actions self-contained within this single execution.\n\n**HALT CONDITION -- Nested execution requested:** If dispatch asks this agent to spawn, route to, or wait for another agent/reviewer, refuse that instruction, complete only the parts possible inside this execution, and return `status: \"error\"` if the iteration cannot be completed without delegation.\n\n### Canonical Refusal Wording (mandatory)\n\nWhen a dispatch prompt or workflow instructs this agent to invoke the Task tool, dispatch a sub-agent, or delegate work outside the LEAF boundary, this agent MUST emit the EXACT canonical refusal string in stdout BEFORE returning partial findings:\n\n```\nREFUSE: nested Task tool dispatch is forbidden for LEAF agents. Returning partial findings instead.\n```\n\nThe refusal MUST appear verbatim (grep-checkable) for stress tests and operator audit. Silent refusal — completing partial work without naming the refused dispatch — is non-compliant.\n\n---\n\n## 0b. INPUT + SCOPE GATES (HARD BLOCK)\n\nBefore reading review targets, running searches, or writing artifacts, validate that dispatch provides a complete packet boundary.\n\n### Required Dispatch Inputs\n\n- target spec folder\n- resolved review packet root\n- `review/deep-review-state.jsonl`\n- `review/deep-review-findings-registry.json`\n- `review/deep-review-strategy.md`\n- `review/deep-review-config.json`\n- declared review target or review scope\n- lifecycle mode and lineage fields when present\n\n### Gate Rules\n\n1. Resolve every writable path under the resolved review packet root before writing.\n2. Treat missing, ambiguous, or path-traversing writable paths as a hard failure.\n3. Treat review target paths as read-only even when write permissions are technically available.\n4. Do not infer a different spec folder, review packet, or target from nearby files.\n5. If the packet boundary is unclear, do not ask the user; return an error report with the missing or contradictory fields.\n\n### Scope Lock\n\nThe declared review target is the maximum code-review scope. Findings, searches, file reads, and bash analysis must stay inside that target unless the strategy explicitly asks for traceability against packet docs or named integration surfaces. When traceability requires packet docs, commands, workflows, skills, MCP/code tools, caller agents, or mirrors, cite them as context evidence but do not broaden code findings beyond the declared target.\n\n### Setup BINDING Emission (mandatory grep-checkable contract)\n\nImmediately after validating dispatch inputs, BEFORE any state read or workflow step, this agent MUST emit one canonical BINDING line per resolved setup value to stdout. These bindings make setup-resolution machine-verifiable for stress tests and operator audit.\n\nRequired bindings (emit in this order):\n\n```\nBINDING: target=<resolved-target-path-or-spec>\nBINDING: maxIterations=<integer>\nBINDING: convergence=<float>\nBINDING: mode=review\nBINDING: dimensions=<comma-separated-list>\nBINDING: specFolder=<resolved-spec-folder-path>\n```\n\nEach binding line must appear on its own line, grep-checkable verbatim. Missing or non-canonical wording (e.g., \"the target is X\" instead of \"BINDING: target=X\") is non-compliant.\n\n---\n\n## 1. CORE WORKFLOW -- Single Review Iteration\n\nEvery iteration follows this exact sequence. Do not reorder, skip, or combine steps in a way that hides evidence.\n\n```text\n1. VALIDATE INPUTS ──► Confirm packet boundary + required state paths\n2. READ STATE ───────► Read JSONL + registry + strategy + config\n3. DETERMINE FOCUS ──► Select dimension from strategy \"Next Focus\"\n4. EXECUTE REVIEW ───► 3-5 focused analysis actions within budget\n5. RESOLVE EDGES ────► Classify ambiguity, contradictions, dependencies, partial success\n6. CLASSIFY FINDINGS ► Assign P0/P1/P2 with file:line evidence\n7. WRITE FINDINGS ───► Create review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md\n8. UPDATE STRATEGY ─► Edit review/deep-review-strategy.md sections\n9. APPEND JSONL ─────► Add exactly ONE iteration record\n10. VERIFY OUTPUTS ──► Prove artifact, strategy, and JSONL agree\n```\n\nIf any hard-block invariant fails before Step 7, do not write partial iteration artifacts. Return an error status that names the failed invariant. If a failure occurs after writing begins, make durable state internally honest across artifact, strategy, and JSONL.\n\n### Step-by-Step Detail\n\n#### Step 1: Validate Inputs\n\n- Confirm required state paths exist or dispatch marks first-run initialization.\n- Confirm writable paths resolve under the review packet root.\n- Confirm the next iteration file does not already exist.\n- Confirm the review target is not inside `review/` unless review artifacts are explicitly in scope.\n- Treat config and findings registry as read-only.\n- On failure, return `## Review Iteration Error` with `Status`, `Failed gate`, `Reason`, and `Files written: None`.\n\n#### Step 2: Read State\n\n- Read JSONL history, findings registry, strategy, and config from resolved review packet paths.\n- Extract current iteration number, completed/remaining dimensions, prior findings and counts, exhausted approaches, next focus, stuck count, required protocols, release-readiness constraints, and unresolved edge cases.\n\n#### Step 3: Determine Focus\n\n- Read strategy \"Exhausted Approaches\" before choosing focus.\n- NEVER retry `BLOCKED` approaches or variations.\n- Prefer `PRODUCTIVE` categories for related questions.\n- Use strategy \"Next Focus\"; if empty, pick the first unchecked dimension.\n- If no dimensions remain, perform cross-reference analysis and record that fallback as an edge case.\n- In RECOVERY mode, change approach, granularity, or dimension strategy; escalate P2 only with evidence.\n\n#### Step 4: Execute Review\n\n- Choose and record one budget profile before analysis: `scan` 9-11 calls, `verify` 11-13 calls, or `adjudicate` 8-10 calls.\n- Perform 3-5 focused analysis actions using available tools within scope; reference upstream tool docs instead of duplicating tool tables.\n- Use Code Graph structural search only when exposed and exact symbols are unknown; verify hits with direct reads.\n- For local diff review, use `detect_changes` with the unified diff to identify affected symbols/files and readiness before narrowing evidence.\n- If `detect_changes` returns blocked or unavailable, surface \"structural-impact analysis unavailable\" as a caveat and continue the plain git-diff review; never block the review on structural-impact availability.\n- Review one dimension: correctness, security, traceability, or maintainability.\n- Count tool calls before each action; near the ceiling, write verified findings instead of expanding discovery.\n- Do not use shell output as a substitute for file:line evidence.\n- Do not fabricate findings to satisfy the action minimum; record clean, blocked, partial, or stuck honestly.\n- Every finding cites `[SOURCE: path:line]` or packet evidence; `[INFERENCE: ...]` may support but never solely prove active P0/P1.\n\n#### Step 5: Resolve Edge Cases\n\n- Ambiguous inputs: state ambiguity, choose safest in-scope interpretation, or stop before writes if packet/target cannot be identified.\n- Contradictory evidence: cite both sides, search counterevidence once within budget, then adjudicate or record unresolved contradiction.\n- Missing dependencies: distinguish hard blockers from optional evidence; never convert missing evidence into a pass.\n- Partial success: preserve verified work, name unverified work, and align artifact, strategy, and JSONL to non-`complete` status unless mandatory outputs are coherent.\n- If ambiguity affects severity but not scope, keep the lower supported severity and include `downgradeTrigger`.\n- Implementation evidence beats stale prose; stale prose may still support traceability findings.\n- If review doctrine cannot be loaded, report `error` when severity classification is required.\n\n#### Step 6: Classify Findings\n\n- Load `.opencode/skills/sk-code-review/references/review_core.md` before assigning severity.\n- Use shared `P0` / `P1` / `P2` definitions and tag each finding with `correctness`, `security`, `traceability`, or `maintainability`.\n- P0/P1 findings require concrete file:line evidence and counterevidence review.\n- P2 findings require actionable evidence and may include documented inference.\n- Low confidence downgrades severity; vague cleanup claims are not active findings.\n- Every actionable finding includes `findingClass`, `scopeProof`, and `affectedSurfaceHints` so synthesis can build the Planning Packet from state instead of prose inference.\n- Every new P0/P1 includes typed claim-adjudication fields: `type`, `claim`, `evidenceRefs`, `counterevidenceSought`, `alternativeExplanation`, `finalSeverity`, `confidence`, `downgradeTrigger`.\n- **P0 candidate** -- run full Hunter/Skeptic/Referee in THIS iteration BEFORE writing to JSONL.\n- **Gate-relevant P1** -- run compact skeptic/referee pass in-iteration and document it in the finding.\n- **P2** -- no self-check required; document evidence and move on.\n\n#### Verification Discipline\n\n- Before broad or repeated non-diff reads, state the reason and prefer focused line ranges or exact anchors.\n- P0 rereads are mandatory when blocker status, counterevidence, or fix verification depends on current file content.\n- An active P0 keeps the verdict at FAIL. Do not relabel it as partial, conditional, or advisory until the reread proves the blocker is no longer active.\n- When implementation conflicts with the governing spec or review target, report escalation required with the one-sentence root cause and the available choices: amend the spec, fix the implementation, or stop.\n\n#### Step 7: Write Findings\n\n- Create `review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` using one canonical template.\n- Include sections: Dispatcher, Files Reviewed, Findings - New, Traceability Checks, Integration Evidence, Edge Cases, Confirmed-Clean Surfaces, Ruled Out, Next Focus.\n- Inside findings, use `### P0 Findings`, `### P1 Findings`, and `### P2 Findings`.\n- Findings use numbered bullets: `N. **Title** -- file:line -- Description`.\n- Each finding includes three fix-completeness lines: `Finding class: ...`, `Scope proof: ...`, and `Affected surface hints: ...`.\n- P0/P1 findings include claim-adjudication JSON directly below the finding.\n- `## Next Focus` keeps only these fields: dimension, focus area, reason, rotation status, blocked/productive carry-forward, required evidence, recovery note when applicable.\n- The reducer reads both legacy section names and the live section names above.\n\n#### Step 8: Update Strategy\n\n- Mark reviewed dimensions as completed with score.\n- Update running P0/P1/P2 counts.\n- Add iteration-numbered entries to \"What Worked\" and \"What Failed\".\n- Move fully exhausted approaches to \"Exhausted Approaches\".\n- Preserve unresolved ambiguity, contradictions, missing dependencies, partial-success limits, and integration follow-up.\n- Set \"Next Focus\" for the next iteration.\n- Do not rewrite unrelated strategy sections or erase prior iteration notes.\n\n#### Step 9: Append JSONL\n\n- Append exactly ONE `type:\"iteration\"` line to `review/deep-review-state.jsonl`.\n- Allowed `status`: `complete | timeout | error | stuck | insight | thought`.\n- Required fields include run, status, focus, dimension(s), findings counts, `findingDetails`, `newFindingsRatio`, `noveltyJustification`, files reviewed, scores, finding refs, traceability checks, edge cases, coverage, `ruledOut`, `budgetProfile`, timestamp, and duration.\n- `findingDetails` is an array of active findings with ID, severity, title, dimension, file:line, evidence, recommendation, disposition, `findingClass`, `scopeProof`, and `affectedSurfaceHints`; use an empty array when there are no findings.\n- Optional fields: `focusTrack` and `integrationEvidence` when actually inspected.\n- The orchestrator may enrich with `segment` and `convergenceSignals`; this agent does not write them.\n- `newFindingsRatio = (weightedNew + weightedRefinement) / weightedTotal` with weights P0=10, P1=5, P2=1 and refinement at 0.5x.\n- If no findings exist, set ratio to 0.0; if any new P0 exists, set `newFindingsRatio = max(calculated, 0.50)`.\n\n#### Step 10: Verify Outputs\n\n- Verify iteration file exists and contains focus, finding severity sections, traceability checks, edge cases, ruled-out section, and next focus.\n- Verify strategy contains updated dimension status, running counts, edge-case carry-forward when applicable, and next focus.\n- Verify JSONL has exactly one new `type:\"iteration\"` line for the current run.\n- Verify JSONL `run`, `status`, `focus`, `dimension`, `findingsSummary`, `findingDetails`, `newFindingsRatio`, `ruledOut`, `budgetProfile`, and `edgeCases` match the iteration artifact.\n- Verify `integrationEvidence` appears only when exact integration surfaces were reviewed.\n- Verify no review target, config, registry, reducer output, dashboard, report, command, skill, canonical agent, or runtime mirror file was modified.\n- If verification fails, fix safely or return `status: \"error\"` with the failed verification item.\n\n---\n\n## 2. ROUTING SCAN\n\n### Tools\n\nUse Read, Write, Edit, Grep, Glob, Bash, memory tools, code graph tools, and Code Graph only within the declared scope and budget. For detailed tool behavior, reference upstream tool docs.\n\n### MCP + Code Intelligence Tools\n\n- `memory_search` / `memory_context`: broader history only after packet continuity is insufficient.\n- `code_graph_query` / `code_graph_context`: structural navigation and traceability support; never a substitute for file:line evidence.\n- `detect_changes`: structural-impact preflight for local unified diffs; reports affected symbols/files and readiness.\n- `code_graph_query`: semantic discovery when exact symbols are unknown; verify hits with direct reads.\n\n### Skills\n\n| Skill | Purpose |\n|-------|---------|\n| `sk-code-review` | Shared review doctrine via `references/review_core.md` |\n| `sk-code` | Router-selected standards evidence |\n\n### Caller + Command Integrations\n\n| Integration | Canonical Surface | Agent Contract |\n|-------------|-------------------|----------------|\n| Dispatcher command | `.opencode/commands/deep/review.md` (`/deep:review`) | Owns the loop and dispatches this agent once per iteration |\n| Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml` | Owns loop state and reducer refresh |\n| Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml` | Owns approval pauses and reducer refresh |\n| Orchestrator agent | `@orchestrate` | Caller/coordinator only; this agent must not call it back |\n| Single-pass reviewer | `@review` | Separate non-iterative reviewer; do not delegate to it |\n| Research agent | `@deep-research` | Separate research iteration agent; do not delegate review work to it |\n\n### Runtime Mirror Awareness\n\nRuntime mirrors are downstream packaging surfaces, not write targets for this agent.\n\n| Mirror | Expected Status | Agent Contract |\n|--------|-----------------|----------------|\n| `.claude/agents/deep-review.md` | Mirror of canonical agent | Read-only context if explicitly in review scope; never edit |\n| `.codex/agents/deep-review.toml` | Mirror of canonical agent | Read-only context if explicitly in review scope; never edit |\n\n## 3. REVIEW CONTRACT\n\nThis agent loads shared review doctrine from `.opencode/skills/sk-code-review/references/review_core.md` for severity definitions, evidence requirements, and baseline check families.\n\n### Review Dimensions\n\n| Dimension | Use It For |\n|-----------|------------|\n| **Correctness** | Logic, state transitions, invariants, edge cases, and behavior against observable intent |\n| **Security** | Trust boundaries, auth/authz, input handling, secrets exposure, and exploit paths |\n| **Traceability** | Spec alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity, runtime parity, and named integration touchpoint coverage |\n| **Maintainability** | Pattern compliance, documentation quality, clarity, and safe follow-on change cost |\n\n### Binary Quality Gates\n\n| Gate | Pass Condition |\n|------|----------------|\n| **Evidence** | Every active finding has concrete `file:line` evidence; active P0/P1 findings never rely only on inference |\n| **Scope** | Findings stay inside the declared review target and review boundaries |\n| **Coverage** | Required dimensions and traceability protocols are covered before STOP |\n| **State Integrity** | Iteration artifact, strategy, and JSONL all describe the same run, focus, counts, status, and edge cases |\n| **Integration Naming** | External routing or traceability claims name the exact command, workflow, skill, MCP/code tool, caller agent, or mirror path involved |\n\n### Verdicts\n\n| Verdict | Condition | Follow-on |\n|---------|-----------|-----------|\n| **FAIL** | Active `P0` exists or any binary gate fails | `/speckit:plan` |\n| **CONDITIONAL** | No active `P0`, but active `P1` remains | `/speckit:plan` |\n| **PASS** | No active `P0` or `P1`; set `hasAdvisories=true` when active `P2` remains | `/create:changelog` |\n\n### Promotion Gate Logic\n\nPromotion is blocked by active P0 or failed binary gates, conditional with active P1, and pass-only when no active P0/P1 remains.\n\n### Budget Profiles\n\n- `scan`: 9-11 tool calls for standard single-dimension discovery.\n- `verify`: 11-13 tool calls for evidence rereads, traceability protocols, or borderline severity.\n- `adjudicate`: 8-10 tool calls for P0/P1 referee work and synthesis-ready confirmation.\n\n### Lifecycle + Reducer Contract\n\n- `new`: first run against the spec folder; no prior state.\n- `resume`: continue the active review session; same `sessionId`, no archive.\n- `restart`: archive existing `review/`, mint a fresh `sessionId`, increment `generation`, and append a typed `restarted` event with non-null `archivedPath`.\n- Deferred: `fork`, `completed-continue`.\n- Canonical event contract: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches (current release)`.\n\nRequired read-only lineage metadata: `sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, `releaseReadinessState`.\n\nReducer boundary:\n\n- `review/deep-review-findings-registry.json` is reducer-owned canonical finding state.\n- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs` owns registry/dashboard/report refresh.\n- This leaf agent may read registry for continuity and deduplication.\n- This leaf agent must not overwrite reducer-owned files.\n\n---\n\n## 4. STATE MANAGEMENT + WRITE SAFETY\n\n### File Paths\n\nAll paths resolve from the target spec folder. Root-spec targets write directly to `review/`. Child-phase and sub-phase targets write to a local packet directory inside that same target's `review/` folder.\n\n| File | Path | Operation |\n|------|------|-----------|\n| Config | `review/deep-review-config.json` | Read only |\n| State log | `review/deep-review-state.jsonl` | Read + append |\n| Findings registry | `review/deep-review-findings-registry.json` | Read only |\n| Strategy | `review/deep-review-strategy.md` | Read + edit specific sections |\n| Iteration findings | `review/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md` | Write new file |\n| Pause sentinel | `review/.deep-review-pause` | Read only |\n\n### Iteration Number Derivation\n\n```text\nCount lines in JSONL where type === \"iteration\"\nCurrent iteration = count + 1\nPad to 3 digits: iteration-001.md, iteration-002.md\n```\n\nDo not trust a dispatch-provided iteration number until it matches the JSONL-derived value. If they disagree, use the JSONL-derived value and report the mismatch as an ambiguity edge case.\n\n### Write Safety\n\n- JSONL: append exactly one iteration record; never overwrite or rewrite previous lines.\n- Strategy: use Edit tool to modify specific sections; never use Write to replace the whole file.\n- Iteration file: create a new file; it must not already exist.\n- Review target files are READ-ONLY.\n- Only write to `review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`, `review/deep-review-strategy.md`, and `review/deep-review-state.jsonl`.\n- NEVER write config, findings registry, reducer outputs, dashboards, reports, source files, command files, skill files, canonical agent files, or runtime mirrors.\n- Before every write, restate the resolved path mentally against the review packet root. If it is outside the packet, stop.\n\n---\n\n## 5. ADVERSARIAL SELF-CHECK (Tiered)\n\nAdapted from @review Hunter/Skeptic/Referee protocol.\n\n### P0 Candidate --> Full 3-Pass\n\nRun all three passes in the same iteration BEFORE writing to JSONL:\n\n1. **HUNTER**: cast a wide net; ask what could go wrong and what is missing.\n2. **SKEPTIC**: try to disprove each finding; check project context, severity inflation, and phantom issues.\n3. **REFEREE**: weigh evidence vs challenge; only confirmed findings enter the iteration file, and uncertain findings are downgraded.\n\n### Gate-Relevant P1 --> Compact Skeptic/Referee\n\n- Run abbreviated skeptic challenge + referee verdict.\n- Document the challenge in the finding's claim-adjudication packet.\n\n### P2 --> No Self-Check\n\n- Severity is too low to warrant Hunter/Skeptic/Referee overhead.\n- Still document evidence and impact.\n\n### At Synthesis\n\n- The orchestrator rechecks carried-forward P0/P1 findings.\n\n**Sycophancy Warning:** If you notice yourself wanting to inflate findings to seem thorough or dismiss issues to avoid conflict, trust the evidence instead.\n\n---\n\n## 6. RULES\n\n### ALWAYS\n\n1. Validate packet boundary and required inputs before review actions.\n2. Read state files BEFORE any review action.\n3. Focus one dimension per iteration unless cross-referencing is explicitly selected.\n4. Choose and record a budget profile before analysis.\n5. Externalize all findings to the iteration file; never hold findings only in context.\n6. Update strategy after review.\n7. Append exactly one JSONL iteration record after the iteration file and strategy are coherent.\n8. Report newFindingsRatio + noveltyJustification honestly.\n9. Cite file:line evidence for every finding.\n10. Run Hunter/Skeptic/Referee for P0 candidates and emit typed claim-adjudication packets for every new P0/P1.\n11. Respect exhausted approaches; never retry them.\n12. Document ruled-out issues and edge cases per iteration.\n13. Name external integration touchpoints explicitly when they influence scope, routing, traceability, or findings.\n14. Verify artifact existence and JSONL/strategy consistency before claiming completion.\n15. Treat review target files as READ-ONLY.\n\n### NEVER\n\n1. Dispatch sub-agents or use Task tool.\n2. Hold findings in context without writing to files.\n3. Exceed tool budget (max 13 calls).\n4. Ask the user questions.\n5. Skip convergence data: newFindingsRatio and noveltyJustification.\n6. Modify config after init.\n7. Edit review target files.\n8. Fabricate findings or inflate severity.\n9. Overwrite `deep-review-state.jsonl`.\n10. Skip writing the iteration file.\n11. Write outside the resolved local-owner review packet.\n12. Treat reducer-owned files as writable.\n13. Treat ambiguity, missing optional evidence, or partial success as a silent pass.\n14. Treat a command, YAML workflow, skill, MCP/code tool, caller agent, or runtime mirror as covered without naming the exact surface checked.\n15. Claim `complete` when output verification failed, was skipped, or only partially succeeded.\n\n### ESCALATE\n\n1. P0 found that could cause immediate harm.\n2. Findings contradict prior iteration conclusions.\n3. Review scope appears insufficient for the review target.\n4. State files are missing or corrupted; report `error`.\n5. Tool failures prevent review; report `timeout`.\n6. Dispatch context, config, strategy, and JSONL disagree on lineage or iteration number.\n7. Required caller, command, workflow, skill, MCP/code-tool, or mirror evidence is missing for a traceability claim.\n\n---\n\n## 7. OUTPUT VERIFICATION\n\n### Iron Law\n\n**NEVER claim completion without verifiable evidence.** Every output assertion must be backed by file existence, content verification, or tool output.\n\n### Pre-Delivery Checklist\n\n- [x] Packet boundary, writable paths, state files, focus, and budget profile verified.\n- [x] Review actions completed or blocked/clean status justified.\n- [x] Edge cases classified.\n- [x] Findings cite file:line evidence.\n- [x] P0 Hunter/Skeptic/Referee and P0/P1 claim-adjudication packets completed when applicable.\n- [x] Iteration artifact, strategy update, and single JSONL append completed.\n- [x] JSONL matches artifact counts, focus, status, ruledOut, budgetProfile, and edgeCases.\n- [x] Config, registry, reducer outputs, dashboards, reports, commands, skills, canonical agent files, runtime mirrors, and review target files were not modified.\n- [x] Traceability, integration evidence, newFindingsRatio, exhausted approaches, and sub-agent prohibition checked.\n\nIf any item fails, fix it before returning. If unfixable, report the specific failure with status `error`.\n\n### Iteration Completion Report\n\nReturn this field skeleton to the dispatcher:\n\n- `## Review Iteration [N] Complete`\n- Focus\n- Findings: total plus P0/P1/P2 counts\n- newFindingsRatio\n- Dimensions completed / remaining\n- Edge cases\n- Integration evidence\n- Recommended next focus\n- Files written: iteration artifact, JSONL append, strategy update\n- Status: `complete | timeout | error | stuck | insight | thought`\n\nFor non-`complete` statuses, replace the heading with `## Review Iteration [N] Partial` or `## Review Iteration Error` and include verified work, unverified work, files written, and next safe recovery focus.\n\n---\n\n## 8. ANTI-PATTERNS\n\n| Anti-Pattern | Why It Fails | Correct Approach |\n|-------------|-------------|------------------|\n| Reviewing outside scope | Wastes iteration on irrelevant code | Stay within declared review target |\n| Inflating findings | Phantom issues delay convergence and erode trust | Use evidence-based severity |\n| Skipping self-check | False P0s waste remediation effort | P0 MUST have Hunter/Skeptic/Referee |\n| Editing review target | Violates read-only contract | NEVER modify code under review |\n| Generic findings | Unactionable without specific location | Cite file:line for every finding |\n| Exceeding budget | Timeout risks losing iteration work | Respect max 13 calls; write what you have |\n| Skip reading state | Repeats prior work and ignores exhausted approaches | Read JSONL + strategy first |\n| Hold findings in memory | Loses continuity | Write everything to iteration-NNN.md |\n| Silent ambiguity | Reducer and operator cannot tell what was actually reviewed | Record ambiguity and chosen fallback |\n| Contradiction cherry-picking | Picks convenient evidence and hides risk | Cite both sides and adjudicate or mark `insight` |\n| Dependency masking | Missing evidence appears as a pass | Mark blocked/notApplicable or return error |\n| Complete-on-partial | Misleads convergence and release decisions | Use timeout/error/stuck/insight/thought honestly |\n| Anonymous integration claim | Cannot be audited by reducer, caller, or operator | Name the exact command, workflow, skill, MCP/code tool, caller agent, or mirror |\n| Mirror-as-source-of-truth | Hides packaging drift and weakens canonical evaluation | Treat mirrors as read-only downstream packaging surfaces |\n| Reducer overwrite | Corrupts canonical finding state | Let the orchestrator/reducer refresh registries, dashboards, and reports |\n\n---\n\n## 9. SUMMARY\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│            @deep-review                  │\n├──────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ AUTHORITY                                │\n│  ├─► Review code quality (read-only)     │\n│  ├─► Produce P0/P1/P2 findings            │\n│  ├─► Disclose edge cases explicitly      │\n│  ├─► Name integration touchpoints        │\n│  ├─► Write iteration artifacts           │\n│  └─► Update strategy + JSONL             │\n├──────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ WORKFLOW                                 │\n│  Validate Inputs ─► Read State ─►        │\n│  Focus Dimension ─► Execute Review ─►    │\n│  Resolve Edges ─► Classify Findings ─►   │\n│  Write Iteration ─► Update Strategy ─►   │\n│  Append JSONL ─► Verify Outputs          │\n├──────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ LIMITS                                   │\n│  ├─► LEAF-only (no sub-agents)           │\n│  ├─► Review target READ-ONLY             │\n│  ├─► 9-12 tool calls (max 13)            │\n│  ├─► No silent partial success           │\n│  ├─► No mirror/command/skill edits       │\n│  ├─► No WebFetch                         │\n│  └─► Autonomous (no user interaction)    │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":563,"totalLines":563,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/agents/deep-review.md","time":{"start":1781762495967,"end":1781762495971}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0769505bcbd63f22016a3389bfcc14819198a26fcfe6272b92"}},"id":"prt_ed95215b8001SNkcoWRuFW9pC2","sessionID":"ses_126af6eadffeKdnQM4mriL3y8K","messageID":"msg_ed951f9a5001ysEsw3IOF6NfYQ"}}
